Anton Irv VR I/2 , VR II/2 , VR II/3 ( 17 September 1886 -- 27 April 1919 ) was a highly decorated Estonian combat soldier and military officer during World War I and in the Estonian War of Independence .
Naser Orić ( born 3 March 1967 ) is a former Bosnian military officer who commanded Army of the Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina ( ARBiH ) forces in the Srebrenica enclave in eastern Bosnia surrounded by Bosnian Serb forces , during the Bosnian War .
Stabfeldwebel Johann Risztics ( aka Janos Risztics ) was the Austro - Hungarian World War I flying ace credited with seven reliably confirmed aerial victories .
Sergeant Frank Potter ( 1891 -- 11 September 1917 ) was a British World War I observer who became a flying ace , being credited with seven aerial victories .
General Sir Ouvry Lindfield Roberts GCB KBE DSO ( 3 April 1898 -- 16 March 1986 ) was an officer in the British Army and the British Indian Army during World War I and World War II .
James E. Croft ( November 13 , 1833 -- May 26 , 1914 ) was a soldier in the Union Army during the American Civil War who received the Medal of Honor for his actions during the Battle of Allatoona .
Georg Stumme ( 29 July 1886 -- 24 October 1942 ) was a World War II German general most notable for his brief command of the Axis forces at the beginning of the Second Battle of El Alamein .
Joachim Pötter ( 1 January 1913 -- 17 November 19921992 ) was a German World War II bomber pilot .
Stapleton Crutchfield served as a Confederate artillerist in the American Civil War .
Ralph Puckett Jr. ( born 8 December 1926 in Tifton , Georgia ) led the Eighth Army Ranger Company during the Korean War .
Frank Glasgow Tinker ( July 14 , 1909 -- June 13 , 1939 ) was an American mercenary fighter pilot for the Spanish Republican Air Force , during the Spanish Civil War .
Thomas Holland , 1st Earl of Kent , 2nd Baron Holand , KG ( c. 1314 -- 26 December 1360 ) was an English nobleman and military commander during the Hundred Years ' War .
Sir Robert Barrie KCB , KCH ( 5 May 1774 -- 7 June 1841 ) was a British officer of the Royal Navy noted for his service in the War of 1812 .
During his Luftwaffe career , Wilhelm Balthasar was credited with 47 victories , including 7 in the Spanish Civil War , and 13 destroyed on the ground .
Cyrus Bussey ( October 5 , 1833 -- March 2 , 1915 ) was an American soldier and politician , serving as a Brigadier General in the Union Army during the American Civil War .
Captain Saurabh Kalia ( 1976 - -1999 ) was an officer of the Indian Army who was killed during the Kargil War while being held as a prisoner of war by the Pakistani security forces .
Trịnh Thị Ngọ ( born in 1931 ) , also known as Hanoi Hannah , is a Vietnamese radio personality best known for her work during the Vietnam War , when she made English - language broadcasts for North Vietnam directed at US troops .
Robert Elliott Burns ( May 10 , 1892 -- June 5 , 1955 ) was a World War I veteran who gained notoriety after escaping from a Georgia chain gang and writing his memoirs , I Am a Fugitive from a Georgia Chain Gang ! , exposing the cruelty and injustice of the chain gang system .
USS Bibb ( 1853 ) was a Coast Survey vessel that performed survey work during the American Civil War .
Leutnant Wilhelm Fahlbusch was an early World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories , shared with his observer Hans Rosencrantz .
Mario Berti ( 1881 - -1964 ) was an Italian officer during World War I and a general in the Spanish Civil War and World War II .
Jean Baptiste Joseph , chevalier de Laumoy ( 1750 - -1832 ) French engineer , fought in the American Revolutionary War , and was on the staff of Lafayette and was captured with him , by the Austrians .
Heinrich Hartmann Wirz better known as Henry Wirz ( November 25 , 1823 -- November 10 , 1865 ) was a Swiss - born Confederate officer in the American Civil War .
Anthony Swofford ( born August 12 , 1970 ) is an American writer and former U.S. Marine , best known for his 2003 book Jarhead , based heavily on his accounts of various situations encountered in the Persian Gulf War .
Simo Kecojević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Симо Кецојевић ; 1888 - -1953 ) was a Serbian freedom fighter , having participated in the irregular guerrilla forces in the Kosovo Vilayet between 1910 and 1912 , then as regular soldier in the Balkan Wars , World War I and World War II .
The 15th ( Scottish ) Infantry Division was an infantry division of the British Army that served with distinction in both World War I and World War II . In the Great War the 15th ( Scottish ) Division was formed from men volunteering for Kitchener 's New Armies and served on the Western Front for three years .
Nantaje ( fl . 1872 -- 1875 ) , also called Nantahe , was an Apache Indian scout in the U.S. Army who served under Lieutenant Colonel George Crook during the Apache Wars .
During World War II , Rudolf Scheffel was credited 7 aerial victories and the destruction of 50 + tanks in 259 missions .
Hans - Hermann Sturm ( 12 June 1917 -- 24 October 2012 ) was an Hauptmann ( captain ) in the Wehrmacht during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany .
The Black Spectre was Carson Knowles , a Vietnam War veteran whose father was a politician .
USS Auk ( AM-38 ) was an Lapwing - class minesweeper acquired by the U.S. Navy after World War I for the task of removing mines that had been placed during the war .
Lieutenant Colonel Duncan Frederick Campbell , DSO ( 28 April 1876 Simcoe , Ontario -- 4 September 1916 ) was Unionist MP for North Ayrshire who died in World War I. He served with the Lancashire Fusiliers in the Second Boer War 1899 - -1901 , and was present at the Relief of Ladysmith .
John Schiller ( March 7 , 1830 -- June 3 , 1926 ) ( born John Schilling ) was an enlisted soldier in the U.S. Army during the American Civil War .
At the beginning of the Cambodian-- Vietnamese War , Lê Trọng Tấn was commander of Vietnamese armed forces in the southern border of Vietnam from December 1978 to February 1979 .
Karl Weniger ( 24 May 1899 -- 1 October 1941 ) was a Kapitän zur See with the Kriegsmarine during World War II and a posthumous recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Rudolf Hallensleben ( 2 June 1916 -- 19 April 1945 ) was a highly decorated Oberstleutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Marcus Claudius Marcellus ( /mɑrˈsɛləs/ ; c. 268 -- 208 BC ) , five times elected as consul of the Roman Republic , was an important Roman military leader during the Gallic War of 225 BC and the Second Punic War .
François Joseph Lefebvre ( /ˈlˌfɛvrə/ ; 25 October 1755 -- 14 September 1820 ) , Duc de Dantzig , was a French military commander during the Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars and one of the original eighteen Marshals of the Empire created by Napoleon .
Count of the Empire Pierre - Louis Dupas ( 1761 - -1823 ) was a French soldier who rose to prominence during the French Revolutionary Wars , was noted for his association with Napoleon Bonaparte , and rose to the top military rank of General of Division during the Napoleonic Wars .
Jean de Clermont ( d. 19 September 1356 ) , Lord of Chantilly and of Beaumont , was a Marshal of France ( 1352 ) who was killed fighting in the Hundred Years ' War at the Battle of Poitiers .
Admiral Sir Charles Adam , FRSE KCB ( 6 October 1780 -- 19 September 1853 ) was a British naval officer who served during the Napoleonic Wars .
Maurice Challe ( 5 September 1905 -- 18 January 1979 ) was a French general during the Algerian War , one of four generals who took part in the Algiers putsch .
Jeffries Peak ( 64 ° 43′S 62 ° 0′W ) is a peak standing southward of Wilhelmina Bay , between Leonardo Glacier and Blanchard Glacier on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Berkner Bank ( 75 ° S 48 ° W ) is an undersea bank in the Weddell Sea named after Lloyd V. Berkner , an engineer who sailed with Admiral Byrd on the Byrd Antarctic Expedition to Antarctica , 1928 - -1930 .
Morris Cliff ( 80 ° 20′S 81 ° 49′W ) is a steep , east - facing cliff between the Marble Hills and Independence Hills in the Heritage Range of the Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Henderson Hill ( 77 ° 34′21``S 163 ° 11′27''E ) is an ice free summit 0.8 nautical miles ( 1.5 km ) northeast of Mount Falconer , rising to 700 metres ( 2,300 ft ) on the north side of Taylor Valley in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Wilkes Basin is a large subglacial basin situated generally southward of George V Coast and westward of Prince Albert Mountains in East Antarctica .
Holoviak Glacier ( 71 ° 22′S 72 ° 9′W ) is a glacier flowing west into the head of Mendelssohn Inlet , facing towards the Wilkins Ice Shelf on the north side of the Beethoven Peninsula , lying in the southwestern portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Collins Point is a small but prominent headland 1.4 km ( 0.87 mi ) west - south - west of Fildes Point , on the south side of Port Foster , Deception Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Belimel Bay ( Bulgarian : залив Белимел , `` Zaliv Belimel '' \'za - liv ' be - li - mel\ ) is a 5.9 km wide bay indenting for 3.9 km the southwest coast of Trinity Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Krakken Mountain ( 71 ° 32′S 12 ° 9′E ) is a mountain 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) north of Sandseten Mountain and just northwest of Gneysovaya Peak in the Westliche Petermann Range of the Wohlthat Mountains , Antarctica .
Marie Byrd Land is the portion of West Antarctica lying east of the Ross Ice Shelf and the Ross Sea and south of the Pacific Ocean , extending eastward approximately to a line between the head of the Ross Ice Shelf and Eights Coast .
The Mayer Crags ( 84 ° 53′S 168 ° 45′W ) form a rugged V - shaped massif in Antarctica .
Grimley Glacier ( 69 ° 9′S 64 ° 40′W ) is a tributary glacier , 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) long and 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) wide , lying 3 nautical miles north of Sunfix Glacier and flowing east - northeast into Casey Glacier in northern Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Kendall Basin ( 80 ° 15′S 25 ° 39′W ) is an ice - free cirque at the northwest end of the Herbert Mountains , in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Lesidren Island ( Bulgarian : остров Лесидрен , `` Ostrov Lesidren '' ' os - trov ' le - si - dren ) is the second largest and southernmost island in the Zed group off the north coast of Varna Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Meserve Glacier ( 77 ° 32′S 162 ° 21′E ) is a hanging glacier on the south wall of Wright Valley , Victoria Land , Antarctica , between Bartley Glacier and Hart Glacier .
Lyddan Island is an ice - covered island located at the southwestern extremity of the Riiser - Larsen Ice Shelf , separating it from the Brunt Ice Shelf , about 20 nautical miles ( 37 km ) off the Princess Martha Coast of Antarctica .
The Dwyer Nunataks ( 68 ° 13′S 58 ° 27′E ) are a scattered group of low peaks and ridges about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) long and 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) wide , lying 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southeast of Mount Gjeita in the Hansen Mountains of Antarctica .
Lagarrigue Cove ( 64 ° 39′S 62 ° 34′W ) is a small cove south of Spigot Peak , Errera Channel , on the Danco Coast of Antarctica .
The Huldreskorvene Peaks ( 72 ° 0′S 6 ° 5′E ) are a group of summit peaks and crags just north of Skorvehalsen Saddle and west of Tussenobba Peak in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Kulen Mountain ( 72 ° 39′S 3 ° 18′W ) is a projecting - type mountain on the northwest side of Jøkulskarvet Ridge , in the Borg Massif of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
McLeod Massif ( 70 ° 46′S 68 ° 0′E ) is a large rock massif just south of Manning Massif in the eastern part of the Aramis Range , Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .
Bebresh Point ( Bulgarian : нос Бебреш , `` Nos Bebresh '' \'nos ' be - bresh\ ) is a point projecting 1.3 km from the northwest coast of Liège Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica forming the north side of the entrance to Palakariya Cove and the west side of the entrance to Boisguehenneuc Bay .
Mount Dickerson is a prominent mountain , standing 6 km ( 4 mi ) east of Mount Kirkpatrick in the Queen Alexandra Range in East Antarctica .
Mount Insel ( 77 ° 23′37``S 161 ° 30′21''E ) is the highest point in the northeastern part of the Insel Range , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Feola ( 77 ° 30′S 162 ° 37′E ) is a mountain rising to 1,800 metres ( 5,900 ft ) at the head of Denton Glacier in the Asgard Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Davis Anchorage ( 68 ° 34′S 77 ° 55′E ) is an anchorage in Antarctica about 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) in extent with general depths of 10 to 13 fathoms ( 18 to 24 m ) , lying off Breidnes Peninsula , Vestfold Hills .
Dugdale Glacier ( 71 ° 38′S 169 ° 50′E ) is a glacier about 25 nautical miles ( 46 km ) long , draining northeast from the Admiralty Mountains into Robertson Bay on the north coast of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Klakkane Islands are a group of small islands lying 3 kilometres ( 1.5 nmi ) east of Farrington Island in the William Scoresby Archipelago , Antarctica .
Hargrave Hill ( 64 ° 1′S 60 ° 11′W ) is a hill at the south side of Wright Ice Piedmont , 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) northeast of the mouth of Henson Glacier , in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Kalafut Nunatak ( 77 ° 46′S 145 ° 36′W ) is a nunatak which marks the southeast end of the Haines Mountains , in the Ford Ranges of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Alvarez Glacier ( 70 ° 53′S 162 ° 20′E ) is a tributary glacier in the Explorers Range of the Bowers Mountains in Antarctica .
Mason Spur ( 78 ° 33′S 164 ° 25′E ) is an elevated spur , partially ice - covered and over 1,300 metres ( 4,300 ft ) high , which projects eastward from Mount Morning in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Knallen Peak ( 72 ° 16′S 3 ° 56′W ) is a small rock peak 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) west of Pyramiden Nunatak , at the east side of the head of Schytt Glacier in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Lenfant Bluff ( 70 ° 22′S 160 ° 3′E ) is a rock bluff marking the south side of the mouth of Svendsen Glacier , in the Usarp Mountains of Antarctica .
The Mixon Rocks ( 76 ° 43′S 159 ° 23′E ) are rock outcrops about 2.5 nautical miles ( 5 km ) west of Gadarene Ridge in the Allan Hills of Oates Land , Antarctica .
Mattox Bastion ( 77 ° 38′S 160 ° 56′E ) is one of the peaks of the Inland Forts , surmounting the northeastern part of Flory Cirque in the Asgard Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Phelps Promontory ( 62 ° 28′55``S 60 ° 7′15''W ) is a large ice piedmont promontory forming the north extremity of Varna Peninsula on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica north of Zhelyava Hill .
Manna Glacier ( 69 ° 45′S 159 ° 40′E ) is a broad depression - glacier located north of Stevenson Bluff and Mount Steele in the Wilson Hills of Antarctica .
The Guyou Islands ( 65 ° 3′S 63 ° 24′W ) are a small group of islands lying 3 km ( 2 mi ) northeast of Sonia Point in Flandres Bay , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Rwanda ( /ruːˈɑːndə/ or /ruːˈændə/ ( listen ) ; Kinyarwanda : U Rwanda ( u.ɾɡwanda ) ) , officially the Republic of Rwanda ( Kinyarwanda : Repubulika y'u Rwanda ; French : République du Rwanda ) , is a sovereign state in central and east Africa and one of the smallest countries on the African mainland .
Albone Glacier ( 64 ° 13′S 59 ° 42′W ) is a deeply entrenched narrow glacier on the east side of Wolseley Buttress flowing southward from Detroit Plateau on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Prydz Bay is a deep embayment of Antarctica between the Lars Christensen Coast and Ingrid Christensen Coast .
Havola Escarpment is an isolated , snow - covered escarpment about 30 nautical miles ( 60 km ) northwest of the Thiel Mountains in Antarctica .
Gauntlet Ridge is a flat - topped , mainly ice - covered ridge , or peninsula , which separates the mouths of Nascent Glacier and Ridgeway Glacier where they discharge into Lady Newnes Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Macalester ( 79 ° 41′S 84 ° 20′W ) is a prominent peak rising to 2,480 metres ( 8,140 ft ) in the central part of the Soholt Peaks , Heritage Range , Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
Mount Etchells ( 80 ° 17′S 28 ° 20′W ) is one of the La Grange Nunataks in the Shackleton Range of Antarctica , rising to about 900 metres ( 3,000 ft ) to the west of Mount Beney .
McCarroll Peak ( 66 ° 3′S 62 ° 46′W ) is a rock peak , 1,105 metres ( 3,625 ft ) high , standing at the south side of Richthofen Pass on the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Kinsella Peak is a peak along the south side of Gale Ridge , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) west of Mount Cowart , in the Neptune Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Davies Bay ( 69 ° 18′S 158 ° 34′E ) is a bay on the coast , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) wide , between Drake Head and Cape Kinsey , Antarctica .
Halpern Point ( 63 ° 18′S 57 ° 50′W ) is a point on the northern coast of Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica , directly south of the eastern part of the Duroch Islands .
East Egerton ( 80 ° 50′S 158 ° 6′E ) is a prominent peak , 2,815 metres ( 9,240 ft ) high , rising 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) east of Mount Egerton in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
Cape Marsh ( 65 ° 15′S 59 ° 28′W ) is a prominent cape consisting of a rock cliff over 235 metres ( 770 ft ) high , marking the southeastern extremity of Robertson Island on the edge of the Larsen Ice Shelf off Antarctica .
The Recovery Glacier ( 81 ° 10′S 28 ° 00′W ) is a glacier flowing west along the southern side of the Shackleton Range in Antarctica .
The David Range ( 67 ° 54′S 62 ° 30′E ) is a mountain range 5 miles ( 8 km ) west of the Masson Range , which it parallels , in the Framnes Mountains of Antarctica .
Tangra Mountains ( in Bulgarian Тангра планина , ' Tangra planina ' \'tan - gra pla - ni-'na\ ) ( 62 ° 40′00``S 60 ° 06′00''W ) form the principal mountain range of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount Matthias ( 71 ° 13′S 164 ° 41′E ) is a mountain rising to 1,610 metres ( 5,280 ft ) 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) east - northeast of Mount Dockery in the Everett Range of the Concord Mountains , Antarctica .
Grindley Plateau ( 84 ° 9′S 166 ° 5′E ) is a high icecapped plateau in the central Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica , bordered by the peaks of Mount Mackellar , Mount Bell and Mount Kirkpatrick .
Kottmeier Mesa ( 77 ° 39′S 162 ° 9′E ) is a prominent 2,120-metre ( 6,960 ft ) high mesa , 2.8 nautical miles ( 5.2 km ) northwest of Mount J. J. Thomson in the Asgard Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount McMahon ( 70 ° 52′S 65 ° 9′E ) is a mountain about 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) west of Mount Bewsher in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Hetty Rock is the largest of several rocks in Walker Bay off John Beach in western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Planet Heights ( 71 ° 13′S 68 ° 47′W ) is a series of summits running along an ice - free ridge , extending 24 nautical miles ( 44 km ) in a north - south direction between the southernmost extremity of the LeMay Range and George VI Sound in the east part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mineral Hill ( 63 ° 29′S 57 ° 3′W ) is a round - topped hill , 445 metres ( 1,460 ft ) high , with ice - free , talus - covered slopes , standing 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) west of Trepassey Bay on Tabarin Peninsula , Antarctica .
Cheal Point is a rocky headland 2 km ( 1.2 mi ) east - south - east of Return Point , the south - western extremity of Coronation Island , in the South Orkney Islands of Antarctica .
Lockyer Island is an island 2.5 mi long , lying off the south shore of James Ross Island in the SW entrance to Admiralty Sound in Antarctica .
Breaker Island is a small rocky island lying in Arthur Harbour close south - west of Norsel Point , off the south - west coast of Anvers Island in the Palmer Archipelago of Antarctica .
Ferguslie Peninsula is a peninsula 2.4 km ( 1.5 mi ) long , lying between Browns Bay and Macdougal Bay on the north coast of Laurie Island , in the South Orkney Islands of Antarctica .
The Dennistoun Glacier is a glacier , 50 miles ( 80 km ) long , draining the northern slopes of Mounts Black Prince , Royalist and Adam in the Admiralty Mountains of Victoria Land in Antarctica .
Lunar Crag ( 71 ° 8′S 68 ° 42′W ) is one of the rock - exposed summits within the Planet Heights mountain range , rising to about 1,200 metres ( 4,000 ft ) at the head of Pluto Glacier on the east side of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Melcon Peak ( 77 ° 27′S 160 ° 25′E ) is an ice - covered peak rising to 2,500 metres ( 8,200 ft ) 1.1 nautical miles ( 2 km ) south of Shapeless Mountain in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Yamato Glacier ( 71 ° 25′S 35 ° 35′E ) is a glacier about 6 miles ( 10 km ) wide , flowing west between Mount Fukushima and Mount Eyskens in the Queen Fabiola Mountains of Antarctica .
Sitalk Peak ( Vrah Sitalk \'vr&h si-'talk\ ) is a rocky peak of elevation 600 m in Levski Ridge , Tangra Mountains , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

Nathaniel Davison ( c.1736 - -1809 ) was an English diplomat , known for his writings on Egyptian archaeology .

Sir Bevil Granville ( died 1706 ) was an English soldier who served as Governor of Pendennis Castle in Cornwall and as Governor of Barbados .
Guido Fibbia ( 1 October 1917 -- 1 July 1988 ) was an Italian Second World War fighter pilot in the Regia Aeronautica and in the Aeronautica Nazionale Repubblicana .
Sir James Long , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1617 -- 22 January 1692 ) was an English politician and Royalist soldier .
Arthur Midy is a French painter born on 18 March 1877 in Saint - Quentin and died on 18 March 1944 in Le Faouët .
Terry Major - Ball ( 2 July 1932 -- 13 March 2007 ) was the elder brother of the former British Prime Minister John Major , who during his brother 's seven - year premiership had a brief career as a television and radio personality and newspaper columnist .
Andrew Vivian ( 1759 - -1842 ) was a British mechanical engineer , inventor , and mine captain of the Dolcoath mine in Cornwall , England .
Lord George Gordon ( 26 December 1751 -- 12 November 1793 ) was a British politician best known for lending his name to the Gordon Riots of 1780 .
Egon Eis , born Egon Eisler ( 6 October 1910 -- 6 September 1994 ) was an Austrian screenwriter .
Malinovskii Ioanikii Aleksieevich ( 04 ( 16 ) . ХІ.1868 , Ostroh of Volyn guberniya -- 12 . І. 1932 , Kyiv ) -- historian of law , legal scholar , academician of All - Ukrainian Academy of Sciences ( Ukr . Abbr . `` VUAN '' ) .
Baldwin FitzGilbert ( died 1090 ) ( alias Baldwin the Sheriff , Baldwin of Exeter , Baldwin de Meulles / Moels and Baldwin du Sap ) was an Anglo - Norman magnate and one of the 52 Devon Domesday Book tenants - in - chief of King William the Conqueror .
Aodh mac Conchobar Maenmaige Ua Conchobair , Prince of Connacht and Irish Crusader , died 1219 .
Philip Dixon Hardy ( 1794 - 1875 ) was an Irish poet , bookseller , printer and publisher .
Johanne Reutz Gjermoe ( 4 January 1896 -- 4 February 1989 ) was a Norwegian economist and politician , a proponent for women 's rights and peace activist .
Hugh Holmes QC ( 17 February 1840 -- 19 April 1916 ) was an Irish Conservative Party then after 1886 a Unionist Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the United Kingdom Parliament and subsequently a Judge of the High Court and Court of Appeal in Ireland .
Rowland De Winton Aldridge ( 1906 - -1997 ) ( commonly known as Winton Aldridge ) was a British architect , architectural historian and artist .
Lucius Israel Barber ( October 7 , 1806 - February 16 , 1889 ) was a politician in the Wisconsin Territory and Connecticut .
Anastasia of Greater Poland ( Polish : Anastazja Mieszkówna ; b. ca . 1164 - d. aft . 31 May 1240 ) , was a Polish princess member of the House of Piast and by marriage Duchess of Pomerania .
Sava Dobroplodni ( Bulgarian : Сава Доброплодни ; 3 December 1820 -- 19 April 1894 ) , born Sava Hadzhiiliev ( Сава Хаджиилиев ) , was a Bulgarian writer , teacher and theatrical worker of the Bulgarian National Revival and an honorary member of the Bulgarian Academy of Sciences .
Mary Melissa Hoadley Dodge ( 1861 -- 24 December 1934 ) was an American heiress who moved to England and sponsored many causes during her life , including women 's suffrage , Theosophy and the arts .
Giles of Lessines OP ( died c. 1304 ) was a thirteenth - century Dominican scholastic philosopher , a pupil of Thomas Aquinas .
John Minter Morgan ( 1782 - -1854 ) , was an author and philanthropist .
Yrjö Norta ( originally Nyberg , 18 March 1904 -- 11 November 1988 ) was a Finnish film director , screenwriter , editor , cinematographer and sound editor .
Pandeli Sotiri ( 1842 - -1892 ) was an Albanian activist that acted as director of the first Albanian school of modern times in Korçë .
J. Nicholas Podier ( died 1 July 1988 ) was a Liberian soldier and government official in the 1980s .
Johann Friedrich Krummnow ( or Krumnow ) ( 1811 -- 3 October 1880 ) was a German - born settler in Australia .
Joseph Bernard Clark ( 1868 - 1940 ) was a British ornamental plasterer and co - founder of the specialist plasterwork company of Clark & Fenn .
Frank Edward Tylecote CBE ( 23 May 1879 -- 7 October 1965 ) was a British doctor , and one of the first physicians to draw attention to the connection between smoking and lung cancer .
Jan Baptist van Heil ( 1604 in Brussels --1685 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter .
Sir William Carson ( baptised 4 June 1770 -- 26 February 1843 ) , often called `` The Great Reformer '' , was an important doctor and businessman in Newfoundland .
Sayyid Baraka ( 1343 - -1403 ) was a holy man of the commercial city of Tirmidh , and spiritual teacher and friend to the 14th century warlord Timur .
Philip George Houthem Gell ( 20 October 1914 -- 3 May 2001 ) was an immunologist working in postwar Britain .
Iacob Dybwad Sømme ( 5 September 1898 -- 3 March 1944 ) was a Norwegian ichthyologist and resistance member .
Czeslaw Znamierowski ( 23 May 1890 -- 9 August 1977 ) was a renowned Soviet Lithuanian painter , known for his large artworks and love of nature .
Charles Edward Sims ( 4 May 1925 - 8 August 1983 ) was the State Librarian of Kansas from 1973 to 1975 .
William Galeon ( died 1507 ) , was a learned English Augustinian .
Mariangiola Criscuolo ( c. 1548 - -1630 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance period , active mainly in her natal city of Naples .
J. Vreeland Moore ( 1824 - - July 8 , 1903 ) was a brigadier general of the 1st New Jersey Regiment who played a major role in the history of Leonia , New Jersey .
John Hayls , also Hailes ( 1600 - -1679 ) , was an English Baroque - era portrait painter , principally known for his portrait of Samuel Pepys .
Rev. Hamnet Holditch , also spelled Hamnett Holditch ( 1800 -- 12 December 1867 ) , was an English mathematician who was president of Gonville and Caius College , Cambridge .
Geoffrey de Burgh ( c. 1180 -- 8 December 1228 ) was a medieval Bishop of Ely .
Carlo Portelli ( died 1574 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance period , active mainly in Florence .
Alexander Brownlie Docharty ( 1862 - 1940 ) was a Scottish painter , mainly in oils .
Henry Hayes Vowles ( born at Victoria Park Farm , 26 June 1843 , Bath , England and died 13 November 1905 , Gloucester , England ) was an English author , theologian and a Wesleyan Minister .
İsfendiyar Bey ( full name : İzzettin İsfendiyar ) was the bey ( ruler ) of Candaroğlu Beylik an Anatolian beylik between 1385 and 1440 .
Giovanni Battista Crivelli ( died March 1652 ) was an Italian composer .
Virginia Wales Johnson ( 28 December 1849 , in Brooklyn , New York -- 16 January 1916 ) was a United States novelist .
Sulim Yamadayev was shot in Dubai on 28 March 2009 , and died in hospital on 30 March 2009 .
Lydia Gould ( born 1952 - 1957 ) is a racing cyclist specialising in cross country and marathon mountain bike racing , and is a prolific medallist at the national championships and national points series .
George Thomas Bryan Palmer ( 1899 - -1990 ) was an Australian Rugby Union player who coached the Wallabies .
Constantine Coronini ( September 19 , 1881 - 1924 , Harbin , China ) was a Russian Orthodox ( later Greek Catholic ) priest .
João , Prince of Brazil ( Lisbon , 30 August 1688 - Lisbon , 17 September 1688 ) was the first child of Pedro II of Portugal and Maria Sophia of Neuburg .
Nicholas Ling ( fl.1570 - -1607 ) was a London publisher , bookseller , and editor who published several important Elizabethan works , including the first and second quartos of Shakespeare 's Hamlet .
Sigmund Rascher ( 12 February 1909 -- 26 April 1945 ) was a German SS doctor .
Fortunato Pio Castellani ( 6 May 1794 -- 1 January 1865 ) was a 19th - century Italian jeweller and founder of Castellani , an Italian jewellery company .
Stephen Fumio Hamao ( 濱尾 文郎 Hamao Fumio ) ( 9 March 1930 -- 8 November 2007 ) was a Japanese Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and was the President of the Pontifical Council for the Pastoral Care of Migrants and Itinerants until it merged with other elements of the Roman Curia .
Zhou Baozhong ( Chinese : 周保中 ; pinyin : Zhōu Bǎozhōng ; 1902 - -1964 ) was a commander of the Northeast Anti - Japanese United Army resisting the pacification of Manchukuo by the Empire of Japan .
Sir Husein Hasanally Abdoolcader , CBE ( b. 10 September 1890 , in Surat , Bombay Presidency , British India ; d. 16 June 1974 ) was a barrister and politician in Malaya .
Hakaru Masumoto ( 1895 - -1987 ) was a pioneer in metal and alloy research .
Yu Eung - bu ( died 1456 ) was a military official of the early Joseon Dynasty and is remembered as one of the six martyred ministers .
Paul Pons ( 1864 - -1915 ) , stage name le Colosse , was a French wrestler .
Hans Holtermann ( c. 1709 -- 1781 ) , also known as Hans Henrik Holtermann or Hans Henriksen Holtermann , was a Norwegian businessman and landowner .
On the 8 March 1995 , Naomi Feinbrun - Dothan died just before her ninety - fifth birthday .
Owen Lloyd George , 3rd Earl Lloyd - George of Dwyfor , DL ( 28 April 1924 -- 29 July 2010 ) was a British Peer .
Niall mac Cernaig Sotal ( died 701 ) was a king in southern Brega of the Uí Chernaig sept of Lagore of the Síl nÁedo Sláine .
René Guilbaud ( 8 October 1890 -- 18 June 1928 ) was an early-20th - century French military aviator .
Mohib Omar al - Jadaan was killed by an explosive device in Atme on 5 January 2015 , near the Turkish border .
Daniel Isaac Eaton ( 1753 - -1814 ) was an English radical author , publisher and activist .
Bran Mut mac Conaill ( died 693 ) was a king of Leinster from the Uí Dúnlainge branch of the Laigin .
Stephen Gold ( died 12 January 2015 ) was a hacker and journalist who in the mid-1980s was convicted -- and then acquitted -- of accessing the personal message account of Prince Philip .
Ben Barrell ( 14 May 1885 -- 14 July 1969 ) was an English first - class cricketer who represented Lancashire .
Sir Harry Gilbert Barling , 1st Baronet CB CBE FRCS ( 30 April 1855 -- 27 April 1940 ) was an English surgeon .
John Van Zandt ( died 1847 ) was an abolitionist who aided the Underground Railroad resistance movement in Ohio after having been a slaveholder in Kentucky .
Melchor Casco de Mendoza ( 1581 - 1658 ) was a Spanish noblemen , Alcalde , and Alferez real of Buenos Aires .
Vally Weigl ( 11 September 1894 -- 25 December 1982 ) was an Austrian - American composer and music therapist .
Major - General Sir Theodore Fraser KCB , CSI , CMG ( 15 June 1865 -- 22 May 1953 ) , was a British soldier of the Royal Engineers , serving for most of his career with the Indian Army .
Hugh Moss Gerald Forsgate , CBE , JP ( Chinese : 霍士傑 , 22 February 1919 -- 21 October 2001 ) was a director and general manager of Hong Kong and Kowloon Wharf and Godown Company Limited , member and chairman of the Urban Council , and chairman of the Kowloon--
Józef Berger ( 14 March 1901 in Orłowa - 11 June 1962 in Bratislava ) was a Polish Lutheran pastor , theologian and politician from the region of Zaolzie , Czechoslovakia .
Maksim Sedej ( 26 May 1909 -- 13 May 1974 ) was a Slovene painter , one of the key figures of the mid-20th - century art scene in Slovenia .
Douglas Marsden - Jones CBE born Marsden Douglas Jones ( 1893 -- 5 January 1955 ) was a Welsh international rugby union forward who played club rugby for Cardiff and London Welsh .
Giselbert of Luxembourg ( c. 1007 -- 14 August 1059 ) was count of Salm and of Longwy , then count of Luxemburg from 1047 to 1059 .
Friedrich Held ( 21 July 1812 -- 25 January 1872 ) was a German malacologist .
Susan Baird ( 26 May 1940 -- 24 January 2009 ) was the Labour Party Councillor for the Braidfauld ward of the City of Glasgow , Scotland .
Harry Winter ( 24 September 1914 -- 3 December 2001 ) , born Horst Winter , was a German - Austrian singer , musician and band director .
After being incapacitated for several years as the result of a dancing injury , Penelope Spencer died of pneumonia on 3 October 1993 .
Mahmud al - Hasan ( Urdu : محمود الحسن‎ , Maḥmūdu'l - Ḥasan ) also known as Mahmud Hasan ( 1851 -- 30 November 1920 ) was a Deobandi Sunni Muslim scholar who was active against British rule in India .
Barney Ramsden ( Sheffield , 8 November 1917 -- California , 1990 ) was a professional footballer who played as a defender for Liverpool , Sunderland and Hartlepools United .
Barbara Hemphill ( -- 1858 ) was an Irish writer of novels .
Giovanni Nanni , also Giovanni de ' Ricamatori , better known as Giovanni da Udine ( 1487 - -1564 ) , was an Italian painter and architect born in Udine .
Sir Walter Calverley , 1st Baronet ( 1670 -- 15 October 1749 ) was an English aristocrat .
Patrick Hines ( 1930 - -1985 ) , born Mainer Patrick Hines , was an American actor who portrayed Kapellmeister Bonno in the 1984 film Amadeus .
Robert Barlow ( 18 February 1813 -- 16 February 1883 ) was a cartographer and topographical draftsman from England who spent most of his career there with the Ordnance Survey of Great Britain .
John Howard Parnell ( 1843 -- 3 May 1923 ) was an older brother of the Irish Nationalist leader Charles Stewart Parnell and after his brother 's death was himself a Parnellite Nationalist Member of Parliament , for South Meath from 1895 to 1900 .
Josef Karl Rädler ( 1844 - -1917 ) was a porcelain painter from Austria , described as `` ... one of the most exciting self - taught artists to be discovered in recent years . ''
Napuc Chi ( died ca . 1541 ) , often known by his title Ah Kin Chi ( where Ah Kin , or in modern orthography Aj K'in is a title meaning `` priest '' or `` sacerdote '' ) was a Yucatec Maya noble from Maní .
Arnold Pressburger ( 27 August 1885 -- 17 February 1951 ) was an Austrian Jewish film producer who produced 79 films between 1913 and 1951 .
Felipe Diricksen , also Diriksen or Deriksen , ( 1590 - 1679 ) , was a Spanish Baroque painter primarily of portraits and religious paintings , and a member of a family of Flemish painters .
James Watney ( 18 December 1800 - -1884 ) was a brewer and landowner who resided at Haling Park , Croydon , and Beddington , Surrey .
Charalambos Vilaetis ( Greek : Χαράλαμπος Βιλαέτης , 1781 - -1821 ) was a Greek revolutionary leader .
Sir Thomas Erpingham KG ( c. 1355 - -1428 ) was an English knight who became famous as the commander of King Henry V 's longbow wielding archers at the Battle of Agincourt .
Minggatu ( Mongolian script : ᠮᠢᠨᠭᠭᠠᠲᠦ ; Chinese : 明安图 ; pinyin : Ming'antu , c.1692-c . 1763 ) , full name Sharabiin Myangat ( Mongolian : Шаравын Мянгат ) was a Mongolian astronomer , mathematician , and topographic scientist at the Qing court .
Jean - Baptiste Oudry ( 17 March 1686 -- 30 April 1755 ) was a French Rococo painter , engraver , and tapestry designer .
John George Gibson PC , QC ( 13 February 1846 - 28 June 1923 ) , was an Irish lawyer and Conservative politician .
Peter M. Arthur ( 1831 - 17 July 1903 ) was a Scottish immigrant to the United States who was leader of the Brotherhood of Locomotive Engineers ( BLE ) for many years .
Anna Pierce Hobbs Bixby , born Anna Pierce ( 1812 - -1873 ) , was a midwife , herbologist , and frontier doctor in southern Illinois .
Charlotte Lennox , Duchess of Richmond ( née Lady Charlotte Gordon ; 20 September 1768 -- 5 May 1842 ) , was a British peeress best known as the hostess of the Duchess of Richmond 's ball .
Alice Curwen ( c. 1619 - -1679 ) was an English Quaker missionary , who wrote an autobiography published , along with correspondence , as part of A Relation of the Labour , Travail and Suffering of that Faithful Servant of the Lord , Alice Curwen(1680 ) .
Major General Deshamanya Alexander Richard Udugama , MBE , psc , CSR ( 11 November 1911 -- 14 May 1995 ) was a Sri Lankan military leader , politician and diplomat .
Elisabeth Berenberg ( 2 December 1749 -- 16 January 1822 ) was a Hamburg heiress , merchant banker and a member of the Berenberg family .
François Dupré ( 1888 -- 26 June 1966 ) was a French , hotelier , art collector , and owner of the thoroughbred horse breeding and racing farm , Haras d'Ouilly .
William Trail ( 23 June 1746 -- 3 February 1831 ) was a mathematician from Scotland in the 18th century , known by his text books .
William Stanley , 6th Earl of Derby , KG ( 1561 -- 29 September 1642 ) was an English nobleman .
Robert Ashley Vines ( 16 January 1891 -- 10 August 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with University in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Princess Xu Zhaopei ( 徐昭佩 ) ( died 549 ) was an imperial princess of the Chinese Liang Dynasty .
Luella Bates ( b. Luella Born , October 17 , 1897 - d. Luella Coates , November 25 , 1985 ) was the first woman truck driver .
John Knox Bokwe ( 15 March 1855 -- 22 February 1922 ) was a South African journalist , Presbyterian minister and one of the most celebrated Xhosa hymn writers and musician .
Robert Petre , 7th Baron Petre ( 1689 -- 22 March 1713 ) was a British peer , the son of Thomas Petre , 6th Baron Petre ( 1633 - -1706 ) and his wife Mary Clifton , daughter of Sir Thomas Clifton .
Hugo Valentin ( 1888 - -1963 ) was a Swedish historian , scholar and leading Zionist .
George Whitney Calhoun ( September 16 , 1890 -- December 6 , 1963 ) was a sports and telegraph editor for the Press - Gazette of Green Bay , Wisconsin , USA .
Gongsun Du ( died 204 ) , courtesy name Shengji , was a military general and warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
William Goodlad ( c. 1576 - -1639 ) was a 17th - century English whaler .
Thomas Cockson , or Coxon ( bap . 1569 -- fl . 1609 - 30 or 1636 -- d. 1641 ) , was one of the earliest English engravers .
Archimandrite Monsignor Victor J. Pospishil ( 1915 -- 2006 ) was a Ukrainian Catholic priest and a leading scholar on Canon law and the Eastern Catholic churches .
Ravi Chopra ( 27 September 1946 -- 12 November 2014 ) was an Indian movie producer and director .
Nestore Leoni ( L'Aquila , Abruzzo , February 14 , 1862 - 1947 ) was an Italian painter and illuminator of manuscripts ( miniatore ) .
Édouard Vanzeveren ( 27 April 1905 -- 12 May 1948 ) was a French freestyle swimmer .
Lauchlan Maclean , 2nd Laird of Brolas ( 1650 - -1687 ) was the second Laird of Brolas .
Alick Horsnell ( 1882 - -1916 ) was an architect , draughtsmen and artist working in London during the early years of the 20th Century .
After his death on 27 June 1922 , Malick Sy was succeeded by his son Seydi Ababacar Sy as the khalife général des Tidjanes from 1922 to 1957 .
Jane Savage ( born 1752/1753 , died 1824 ) was an English harpsichordist and composer .
William Hamlin ( 15 October 1772 -- 22 November 1869 ) , an entrepreneur , was an early American engraver and the first engraver for the state of Rhode Island .
John W. Keys III ( 1941 - -2008 ) was the director of the United States Bureau of Reclamation from 2001 to 2006 .
Mehli Mehta ( 25 September 1908 -- 19 October 2002 ) was an Indian conductor and violinist .
Colonel William Thomas Reay CBE VD ( 10 November 1858 - -11 November 1929 ) was an Australian journalist , newspaper editor and politician .
Alexander Savvas ( 1907 - 1981 ) was a Greek Professor of Medicine at the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki , Faculty of Anatomy .
Benjamin Harrison III ( 1673 -- April 10 , 1710 ) was an early member of the Harrison Family of Virginia , serving as the colony 's Attorney General , Treasurer , and Speaker of the House of Burgesses .
Maharajapuram Viswanatha Iyer ( Tamil : மகாராஜபுரம் விசுவநாதையர் ) ( 1896 - -1970 ) was one of the great Indian Carnatic vocalists .
James Fussell IV ( 1748 - -1832 ) was an iron magnate operating the Old Ironstone Works , Mells in Vallis Vale between Mells and Great Elm in Somerset .
Miles Dewey Davis , Jr. ( March 1 , 1898 - -1962 ) was an afluent American dentist and father of jazz legend Miles Davis .
John Brereton ( ca . 1571/1572 - ca . 1632 ) was a gentleman adventurer and chronicler of the 1602 voyage to the New World led by Bartholomew Gosnold .
James Thomas Hooper ( 1 September 1897 -- 9 February 1971 ) was a British collector of ethnographic artifacts of the Inuit , Native American , Oceanic and African peoples .
Samuel Colver ( September 10 , 1817 -- February 15 , 1891 ) was one of the first pioneers of the U.S. state of Oregon .
Edvard Heiberg ( 11 June 1911 , in Oslo -- 10 June 2000 , in Oslo ) was a Norwegian director and engineer .
Arthur Dacres ( 1624 - -1678 ) was an English physician and academic , briefly Gresham Professor of Geometry .
Theodoros Natsinas ( Greek : Θεόδωρος Νάτσινας ; 8 July 1872 - 2 February 1949 ) was a Greek teacher .
Fartein Valen - Sendstad ( 1918 - -1984 ) was a Norwegian historian and museologist .
Gaetano Bavagnoli ( 1879 - -1933 ) was an Italian conductor who was particularly known for his work within the field of opera .
Richard Southby ( 1623 - 7 January 1704 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 and from 1679 to 1689 .
Henri Smets ( Wezembeek - Oppem , 1895 - Brussel , 1994 ) was a Belgian cross country athlete .
Henry John Stephen Smith ( 2 November 1826 -- 9 February 1883 ) was a mathematician remembered for his work in elementary divisors , quadratic forms , and Smith--
Jacques Hardel ( died March 1678 ) was a French composer and harpsichordist .
Hallgerður Gísladóttir ( 28 September 1952 -- 1 February 2007 ) was an Icelandic ethnologist and poet .
Edmund Kean ( 4 November 1787 -- 15 May 1833 ) was a celebrated Shakespearean stage actor born in England , who performed in London , Belfast , New York , Quebec , and Paris among other places .
John Dooley Reigh ( died Manchester , 25 February 1914 ) was a cartoonist whose work generally supported Irish nationalism .
Barnabe Googe or Goche ( 11 June 1540 -- 7 February 1594 ) ( also spelled Barnaby Goodge ) was a poet and translator , one of the earliest English pastoral poets .
Nicholas O'Shea ( 1866 - -1912 ) was an Irish hurler who played as midfielder for the Dublin senior team .
George Loftus Noyes ( 1864 - -1954 ) was a Canadian born artist who gained fame in the early 20th century as an American Impressionist .
Albrecht Glockendon the Elder ( c. 1432 , Nuremberg -- 1474 . Also spelled Albert Glockenton ) was a German engraver and manuscript illuminator .
Michele Maylender ( Hungarian : Maylender Mihály ) ( September 11 , 1863 -- 1911 ) was an Italian politician ( inside the Hungarian Crown 's states ) who was the founder of the Autonomist Association , known also as Autonomist Party in Fiume .
Ulloor S. Parameswara Iyer ( 6 June 1877 -- 15 June 1949 ) ( commonly known as Ulloor ) was a Malayalam poet and historian .
Ave Ninchi ( 14 December 1915 -- 10 November 1997 ) was an Italian supporting actress who played character roles on stage , television , and in over 98 feature films that included Tomorrow Is Too Late ( 1949 ) and Louis Malle 's Lacombe Lucien ( 1974 ) .
Joseph B. Hagey ( 1810 - -1876 ) was the Bishop of the Mennonite Church in Ontario from 1852 until his death in 1876 .
Winétt de Rokha was the mid - career pen name of the Chilean poet and writer Luisa Victoria Anabalón Sanderson ( July 7 , 1894 -- August 7 , 1951 ) .
Mika Ahola ( 13 December 1974 -- 15 January 2012 ) was a Finnish enduro rider and a five - time world champion .
Alexander Travis ( 23 August 1790 -- 2 December 1852 ) was a Baptist preacher and a prominent member of the Alabama Baptist State Convention .
William Henry Leggett ( February 24 , 1816 -- April 11 , 1882 ) was a botanist and journalist , who founded the Torrey Botanical Bulletin .
Sir David Hardie ( 4 June 1856 -- 11 November 1945 ) was an Australian medical practitioner .
Max Loehr ( 4 December 1903 - 16 September 1988 ) was an art historian and professor of Chinese art at Harvard University from 1960 to 1974 .
Ángel Rambert ( 12 June 1936 -- 25 October 1983 ) was an Argentine - born French footballer .
Alfred Owen Crozier ( 1863 - -1939 ) was a Midwest attorney who wrote eight books on the political , legal , and monetary problems of the United States .
Donatus , Romulus , Secundian , and 86 Companions ( died c. 304 ) were a group of Christians who were martyred at Gruaro ( at the time called Concordia ) , near Venice , during the Diocletian persecution .
G. S. Gai ( Govind Swamirao Gai ) ( March 3 , 1917 -- February 5 , 1995 ) was an Indian epigraphist , historical linguist , and historian , known for his expertise in early - medieval Kannada language inscriptions .
Charles Southwell ( 1814 -- 7 August 1860 ) was a radical English journalist and freethinker .
Christina Reinira van Reede ( 14 August 1776 , Utrecht - 18 December 1847 , The Hague ) was a Dutch courtier and noble orangist heroine .
Sir John Vanden - Bempde - Johnstone , 2nd Baronet ( 28 August 1799 -- 24 February 1869 ) was a British Member of Parliament .
Helen Iglauer Glueck ( 1907 - -1995 ) was an American physician known for her research in blood chemistry that linked bleeding disorders in newborns with lack of Vitamin K in breast milk .
Anton Rolandsson Martin ( 3 August 1729 at Mijntenhoff Manor , Reval--30 January 1785 in Åbo ) was a Swedish botanist .
Jean - Baptiste Rondelet ( 4 June 1743 -- 25 September 1829 ) was an architectural theorist of the late Enlightenment era and chief architect of the church of Sainte - Geneviève after the death of Jacques Germain Soufflot of cancer in 1780 .
Richard Overton Hunziker ( 6 Jul 1916 -- 29 May 1971 ) was a decorated World War II fighter pilot and later United States Air Force major general .
The Reverend William Darwin Fox ( 23 April 1805 -- 8 April 1880 ) was an English clergyman , naturalist , and a second cousin of Charles Darwin .
Pedro Rodriguez Flores Díaz ( 1609 - 1682 ) was a Spanish military , landowner .
Henry Francis Lyte ( 1 June 1793 -- 20 November 1847 ) was an Anglican divine , hymn - writer and poet .
Marion Vera Cuthbert ( 1896 - -1989 ) was a writer and intellectual associated with the Harlem Renaissance .
Thomas Ludford Bellamy ( 1770 - -1843 ) was an English singer , also for a time a theatre manager .
Sergeant Major Henry H. Black ( 9 February 1929 -- 24 August 2012 ) , USMC retired , was the seventh Sergeant Major of the Marine Corps ( 1975 - -1977 ) .
Nathaniel Plimer ( 1757 - -1822 ) was an English miniature portrait painter .
Liu Shouwen ( 劉守文 ) ( died 910 ) was a warlord who ruled Yichang Circuit ( 義昌 , headquartered in modern Cangzhou , Hebei ) as its military governor ( Jiedushi ) late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and early during Tang 's succeeding dynasty Later Liang .
Carl Conjola ( 1773 - -1831 ) was a German landscape painter in water colours and oil .
Vytautas Norkus ( 28 January 1921 -- 29 January 2014 ) was a Lithuanian - born American basketball player .
Rogelio Nores Martínez ( 1906 - -1975 ) was an Argentine engineer and politician .
Jack Rigby ( 1924 - -1997 ) was a footballer who played as a centre half in the Football League for Manchester City .
Pearce Bailey ( 1865 - -1922 ) was an American neurologist and psychiatrist , educated at Princeton and Columbia Universities .
Josef Leopold Zvonař ( 22 January 1824 -- 23 November 1865 ) was a Czech composer , pedagogue , and big music critic .
Ruy González de Clavijo ( died 2 April 1412 ) was a Castilian traveller and writer .
Gustaf Cronhielm ( 18 July 1664 , Stockholm -- 3 June 1737 ) was a Swedish nobleman and politician .
Otto , Lord of Lippe ( c. 1300 -- c. 1360 ) was the ruling Count of Lippe - Lemgo from 1344 until his death .
Cathal O'Byrne ( 1867 -- 1 August 1957 ) was an Irish singer , poet and writer .
Subutai revealed the plot and Puresh , his son Atämaz and many Moksha warriors were killed sleeping after midnight of 9 April 1241 .
Tanyus Shahin Saadeh al - Rayfouni ( also spelled Tanios Chahine Saadé Al Rayfouné , given name also spelled Taniyus or Tanius ) ( 1815 - -1895 ) was a Maronite muleteer from Mount Lebanon who led a peasants ' revolt in the area of Keserwan in 1859 .
Anderson Gray McKendrick ( 8 September 1876 -- 30 May 1943 ) was a Scottish physician and epidemiologist pioneered the use of mathematical methods in epidemiology .
Herbert Money ( 29 November 1899 -- 9 January 1996 ) was a pioneering educator who had a significant and lasting impact on the growth and life of the evangelical church in Peru and South America .
Edmund Veckenstedt ( 1840 - -1903 ) was an educator , ethnologist and folklorist who published many works , sometimes under the pseudonym Heinrich Veltheim .
Saint Benedict of Aniane ( c. 747 -- 12 February 821 ) , born Witiza and called the Second Benedict , was a Benedictine monk and monastic reformer , who left a large imprint on the religious practice of the Carolingian Empire .
Tormod Skagestad ( 9 August 1920 -- 4 January 1997 ) was a Norwegian poet , novelist , playwright , actor and theatre director .
Dai Zhou ( died 633 ) , courtesy name Xuanyin , posthumously known as Duke Zhong of Dao , was a Chinese official who lived in the Sui dynasty and early Tang dynasty .
Maarten de Niet Gerritzoon ( born 16 March 1904 in Bodegraven -- died 25 July 1979 in The Hague ) was a Dutch politician .
Könchek ( died 1308 ) was Khan of the Chagatai Khanate ( 1307 - -1308 ) .
Lord Edward FitzGerald ( 15 October 1763 -- 4 June 1798 ) was an Irish aristocrat and revolutionary who died of wounds received while resisting arrest on a charge of treason .
Augustin van de Werve ( 1764 - -1793 ) , baron of Lichtaert , formed part of a very old , important and noble family of Antwerp .
Malik Akhmedilov ( Russian : Малик Ахмедилов ; c. 1976 -- 11 August 2009 ) , also known as Abdulmalik Akhmedilov , was a Russian investigative journalist based in the southern Republic of Dagestan .
Archbishop André Perraudin ( 7 October 1914 - 25 April 2003 ) was a Swiss Catholic clergyman who lived in Rwanda for nearly fifty years .
Bernard Laidebeur ( 11 July 1942 -- 21 April 1991 ) was a French athlete , who mainly competed in the 100 metres .
Teresio Maria Languasco ( 1651 - -1698 ) was an Italian painter and an Augustinian monk .
Jean Victor Tharreau or Jean Victor Thareau ( 15 January 1767 , Le May - sur - Èvre -- 26 September 1812 ) , was a General of Division in the Army of the French Empire .
Cyril Furmstone Evans ( born 1892 in Croydon , Surrey , UK , died 1959 ) was a 20th - century wireless telegraphist notable for his involvement in the Titanic tragedy .
Euphemia F. Vsevolozhskaya ( 1630 - 1657 ) , was a Russian noble , the fiancee of Tsar Alexis of Russia .
Elias Lee Francis III ( ca . 1945 -- 7 July 2003 ) was a Laguna Pueblo - Anishinaabe poet , educator , and founder of the Wordcraft Circle of Native Writers and Storytellers .
Alfred P. Southwick ( 1826 - -1898 ) , was a steam - boat engineer , dentist and inventor from Buffalo , New York .
Wendy Boase ( 14 October 1944 -- 15 March 1999 ) born in Melbourne , Australia , she was one of the co - founders of the children 's publishing company Walker Books .
Friedrich Julius Stahl ( 16 January 1802 -- 10 August 1861 ) , German constitutional lawyer , political philosopher and politician .
Sir Philip Hoby ( also Hobby or Hobbye ) ( 1505 -- 31 May 1558 ) was a 16th - century English Ambassador to the Holy Roman Empire and Flanders .
Robert Prentiss Daniel ( November 2 , 1902 -- January 1968 ) was an African - American educator and college administrator .
Carl Axel Mothander ( 1886 - 1965 ) a former Swedish reserve officer ; major in the White Finnish Army in the Finnish War of Independence 1917/18 , organizer of the Finnish White Army 's field hospitals promoted to major ; commander of the Swedish volunteers in the Estonian War of Independence promoted to lieutenant colonel .
Henry C. Dudley ( 1813 - -1894 ) , known also as Henry Dudley , was an English - born North American architect , known for his Gothic Revival churches .
Theodore Cardwell Barker ( 19 July 1923 -- 22 November 2001 ) , usually known as Theo Barker , was a British social and economic historian .
Riccardo Cassin ( 2 January 1909 -- 6 August 2009 ) was an Italian mountaineer , developer of mountaineering equipment and author .
Charles Concordia ( born 20 June 1908 - died 25 December 2003 ) was a noted American electrical engineer specializing in electrical power engineering and the early history of computer hardware .
Dr. Bartholomew Woodlock DD ( 1819 - 1902 ) was an Irish Catholic priest , educator and bishop , a founder of the Society of Saint Vincent de Paul in Ireland .
Khenpo Jigme Phuntsok ( Tib . འཇིགས་མེད་ཕུན་ཚོགས་འབྱུང་གནས་ , Wyl . ' jigs med phun tshogs ' byung gnas ; 1933 - -2004 ) was a Nyingma lama from Serthar of Kham .
Spencer Timothy Hall ( 16 December 1812 -- 26 April 1885 ) was an English writer and mesmerist .
Major general Jaroslav Čihák ( 24 July 1891 -- 30 April 1944 ) was an Austro - Hungarian army officer from 1914 and Russian legionary from 1916 ( command platoon and battalion ) .
Saint Hunna ( Una ) ( died 679 ) is a French saint .
Tiberius Julius Synges , also known as Synges ( flourished 3rd century -- died 276 ) was a prince and Roman Client King of the Bosporan Kingdom .
Brigadier - General John Carnac ( 1716 -- 29 November 1800 ) was a British officer who served three times as Commander - in - Chief of India .
Alija Sirotanović ( 14 August 1914 -- 16 May 1990 ) was a Yugoslav miner , Hero of Socialist Labour and perhaps the most famous of all Yugoslav udarniks .
Mujdin Aliu ( 1974 - -1999 ) was a Macedonian Albanian soldier who gained prominence in the Kosovo War .
Nahapet Kuchak ( Armenian : Նահապետ Քուչակ ) ( died 1592 ) was an Armenian medieval poet , one of the first ashughs .
László Deseő ( 26 June 1893 - 25 June 1948 ) was a Hungarian military officer and diplomat , who served as artillery commander of the Hungarian Second Army 's First Corps during the Second World War .
Russell Cornell Leffingwell ( 1878 - -1960 ) was an American banker who led the Council on Foreign Relations from 1944 until 1953 .
Olavi Reimas ( real name Unto Kalervo Eskola , 14 March 1914 − 9 June 1995 ) was a Finnish actor .
Lloyd Saxon Graham ( January 14 , 1922 -- May 19 , 2012 ) was a prominent American epidemiologist .
Ben E. Rich ( 1855 - -1913 ) was a leading missionary and spokesman for The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) in the early 20th - century .
James J. Baldwin ( 1888 - 1955 ) , commonly known as J.J. Baldwin , was an American architect who designed numerous courthouse buildings and other works in several U.S. states .
George Claydon ( 4 September 1933 -- 4 October 2001 ) was a British actor notable for his dwarfism .
Thomas Birtwistle , Thomas ( 16 October 1833 , Great Harwood , Lancashire -- 22 March 1912 , Accrington ) was a trade unionist and factory inspector .
Peter Nicolay Skibsted died on 18 April 1832 in Copenhagen , and is buried in the churchyard of the Danish Naval Church ved Holmen .
Adolf Gottstein ( 2 November 1857 in Breslau - 3 March 1941 ) was a German social hygienist and epidemiologist .
Catherine , Lady Walpole ( née Shorter ; 1682 -- 20 August 1737 ) was the first wife of British politician and Prime Minister Robert Walpole from 30 July 1700 until her death in Chelsea in 1737 .
Mangalam Muthuswamy ( 1937 - -2007 ) was one of the notable vainikas in recent times .
Patrick Francis McGill ( 1913 - -1977 ) , known as Paddy McGill or P. F. McGill was a journalist and nationalist politician in Ireland .
Ed Tweddell ( c. 1941 -- 4 August 2005 ) was an Australian businessperson best known for his stint as CEO of Australia 's largest indigenous pharmaceutical manufacturer F H Faulding and as Chairman of Ansell .
Raoul Ploquin ( died 29 November 1992 ) was a French film producer , production manager and screenwriter .
Stephanie of Lampron ( ca . 1220/1225 -- soon after April 1 , 1249 , buried at Santa Sophia , Nicosia ) , was a queen consort of Cyprus , wife of Herny I de Lusignan , king of Cyprus .
John Biscoe ( 28 June 1794 -- 1843 ) was an English mariner and explorer who commanded the first expedition known to have sighted the areas named Enderby Land and Graham Land along the coast of Antarctica .
Charles - Richard Lambert ( died 1862 ) was a black American musician , conductor and music educator .
Fu Gongshi ( 輔公祏 ; died 624 ) was an agrarian rebel leader who served as Du Fuwei 's lieutenant during the disintegration of the Chinese dynasty Sui Dynasty , who later followed Du in submitting to Tang Dynasty .
Henry Cheyne , 1st Baron Cheyne ( 31 May 1540 -- 3 September 1587 ) was an English politician .
Charles Scott Haley ( November 8 , 1884 -- 1958 ) , a mining engineer , was an expert in the field of placer gold deposits .
André Thomkins ( 1930 - 8 November 1985 ) was a Swiss painter , illustrator , and poet .
Antonio Ascari ( 15 September 1888 -- 26 July 1925 ) was an Italian Grand Prix motor racing champion .
Kwok Chan ( 1904 -- 17 June 1967 ) was a Hong Kong businessman and member of the Executive Council of Hong Kong .
Sir James Stansfeld PC ( 5 October 1820 -- 17 February 1898 ) , was a British politician .
James Otto Lewis ( February 3 , 1799 -- November 2 , 1858 ) was an American engraver and painter who was noted for his portraits of Native Americans and other figures of the American frontier .
Andreas Leo Ateng Suripto ( 8 August 1942 -- 6 May 2003 ) , better known as Ateng and also known by the Chinese name Kho Tjeng Lie ( 邱诚烈 ) , was a popular Indonesian actor and comedian .
Charalambos Tseroulis ( Greek : Χαράλαμπος Τσερούλης , Missolonghi , 1 June 1879 -- 2 May 1929 ) was a distinguished Greek infantry officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General .
Gëzim Erebara ( 19 May 1929 -- 12 February 2007 ) was an Albanian film director , screen player , translator and cinematography historian of the second half of the 20th century .
Sir Charles Cockerell , 1st Baronet ( 18 February 1755 -- 6 January 1837 ) was an Somerset - born Englishman who prospered as an official of the British East India Company and became a politician .
Ratanchand Hirachand Doshi ( 1902 - -1981 ) was a scion of Walchand group , a noted industrialist , philanthropist , freedom fighter , and Jain social leader .
Leopold Casper ( 31 May 1859 -- 16 March 1959 ) was a German physician and urologist born in Berlin .
Ethel Leginska née Liggins ( 13 April 1886 -- 26 February 1970 ) was a British pianist , composer , conductor and music educator , having among her students harpsichordist Gavin Williamson , a long - time student of Artur Schnabel and Theodor Leschetizky , James Henry Fields , Daniel Pollack and Bruce Sutherland .
The Blessed Stephana de Quinzanis , T.O.S.D. , ( variant spellings include Stephanie , Stefana ; also , Quinzani ) ( 1457 -- 2 January 1530 ) was an Italian Dominican Sister , stigmatic and mystic .
Tasos Neroutsos ( 1826 - -1892 ) was a Greek physician and scholar .
Mikołaj Kiczka ( died 1429 ) was a Polish noble , diplomat and priest .
Alice Comyn , Countess of Buchan , Lady Beaumont ( 1289 -- 3 July 1349 ) was a Norman - Scottish noblewoman , a member of the powerful Comyn family which supported the Balliols , claimants to the disputed Scottish throne against their rivals , the Bruces .
John Raithby ( 1766 - -1826 ) , lawyer , born in 1766 , was eldest son of Edmund Raithby of Edenham , Lincolnshire .
Chen Shixiang ( 陈世骧 ; 1905 - -1988 ) , also known as Sicien H. Chen , was a Chinese entomologist .
The Honourable George Charles Grantley Fitzhardinge Berkeley ( 10 February 1800 -- 20 February 1881 ) , known as Grantley Berkeley , was a British politician , writer and sportsman .
Sir Edward Hoblyn Warren Bolitho KBE CB DSO ( 1882 -- 18 December 1969 ) was a Cornish landowner and politician .
Henry Otto Wix ( 1866 - -1922 ) , also known as Otto Wix , was a German - born landscape and portrait painter who emigrated to the United States in the late 1890s .
Ann Harriet Hughes ( 1852 -- 25 April 1910 ) was a Welsh language novelist , under the pen - name Gwyneth Vaughan .
George Gordon , 4th Earl of Huntly ( 1514 -- 28 October 1562 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Dr. Gyula Krajczár ( 1953 - -1998 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as mayor of Komárom between 1990 and 1998 .
James Frederic Elton ( 1840 - -1877 ) was an English explorer in Africa .
Kong Rong ( 153 - -208 ) , courtesy name Wenju , was a politician , scholar and minor warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Ya'akov Hazan ( Hebrew : יעקב חזן‎‎ , 4 June 1899 -- 22 July 1992 ) was an Israeli politician and social activist .
Marguerite III de Neufchâtel , ( 1480 - 1544 ) , was a German - Roman monarch as Princess Abbess of the Imperial Remiremont Abbey in France .
Jože Šmit ( 1 February 1922 -- 7 February 2004 ) was a Slovene poet , translator , editor and journalist .
Abraham Follett Osler ( 22 March 1808 -- 26 April 1903 ) , known as A. Follett Osler , was a pioneer in the measurement of meteorological and chronological data in Birmingham , England .
Zhang Lichang ( July 1939 -- 10 January 2008 ) was a Chinese politician .
Annesley Dias ( Sinhala : ඇනස්ලි ඩයස් ) ( 31 January 1927 to 12 June 2009 ) was a popular Sri Lankan comedian .
Iestyn ap Gwrgant ( ˈjɛstɪn ap ˈgʊrgant ) ( or Jestyn ap Gwrgant ) ( English : Justin , son of Gwrgant ) ( c. 1045 -- 1093 ) was the last ruler of the Welsh kingdom of Morgannwg , which encompassed the counties of Glamorgan and Monmouthshire .
Sándor Képíró ( 18 February 1914 -- 3 September 2011 ) was a gendarmerie captain during World War II accused of war crimes committed by Hungarian forces , and found not guilty .
Hugh Emlyn Hooson , Baron Hooson QC ( 26 March 1925 -- 21 February 2012 ) was a Welsh Liberal Democrat politician .
The Rt Rev Allen Goodings ( born 7 May 1925 , died 15 December 1992 ) was the tenth Bishop of Quebec .
Mary Catherine Ferguson ( 1823 - -1905 ) was an author and biographer in Dublin , Ireland .
Virginia Rich ( 1914 - -1985 ) was a mystery author who pioneered the `` culinary mystery '' subgenre .
Georgi Bolshakov ( 1922 - -1989 ) was a Soviet GRU officer under journalist cover who was posted to Washington , D.C. , twice , most significantly in the early 1960s .
Ripley Hitchcock , born James Ripley Wellman Hitchcock , ( 1857 - -1918 ) was a prominent American editor .
Frederick W. Garber ( 1877 - -1950 ) was an American architect in Cincinnati , Ohio and the principal architect in the Garber & Woodward firm with Clifford B. Woodward ( 1880 - -1932 ) .
Trần Thuận Tông , ( 1378 - -1399 ) , given name Trần Ngung , was the eleventh emperor of the Trần Dynasty who reigned in Đại Việt from 1388 to 1398 .
Harry Baisden ( aka Harry Bastin , né Cyrus Harry Baisden ; 18 April 1893 Lester Prairie , Minnesota -- 4 December 1926 Augusta , Georgia ) was an American composer of popular music , arranger , pianist , and an acclaimed dance orchestra leader .
George Smith Duncan ( 11 July 1852 -- 4 September 1930 ) was a tramway and mining engineer best known for his work on cable trams , and for his work in the gold mining industry .
Rev. Rufus Halley ( died 28 August 2001 ) was a Roman Catholic missionary of the Society of St. Columban who spent more than 20 years promoting ecumenical dialogue between Christians and Muslims in Asia .
Professor Michael J. O'Kelly ( 1915 -- October 1982 ) was an Irish archaeologist who excavated and restored Newgrange , a Late Stone Age passage tomb in the Boyne Valley , County Meath , Ireland , now a UNESCO World Heritage Site .
Rakhaldas Bandyopadhyay ( 12 April 1885 -- 23 May 1930 ) , also known as R. D. Banerji , was an Indian historian and a native Indian pioneer in the fields of Indian archaeology , epigraphy and palaeography .
Masao Mimatsu ( 三松正夫 ) ( 9 July 1888 -- 8 December 1977 ) was a Japanese postmaster who recorded the growth of the Showashinzan mountain in 1944 - -1945 .
Bertie Reginald Mills ( 23 February 1900 -- 22 January 1994 ) , known as Paddy Mills , was a professional footballer who scored 139 goals in 358 appearances in the Football League playing for Hull City ( in two spells ) , Notts County and Birmingham .
George Gilman Rushby ( 1900 in England -- 1968 in Africa ) , was an elephant hunter , poacher , prospector , farmer , forestry officer , and game warden .
Theodor Martin Peter Ziesemer ( 26 May 1899 -- 28 November 1961 ) was an Australian dairy farmer and wheat farmer .
Julius Briganticus ( died AD 69 ) was a Batavian who commanded auxiliary cavalry in the Roman Army .
William Morton Payne ( February 14 , 1858 , Newburyport -- 1919 ) was an American educator , literary critic and writer .
Paleologo Zaccaria ( 1235 - -1314 ) was the Lord of Chios and Phocaea , as well as other Aegean islands from 1307 until his death .
Ignace François Broutin ( La Bassée , 1690 - -1751 ) was a French military officer , commander of Fort Rosalie among the Natchez people , and later an architect in colonial Louisiana .
Sir John Fogge ( c.1417 - -1490 ) was an English courtier , soldier and supporter of the Woodville family under Edward IV who became an opponent of Richard III .
Don Flowers ( 1908 - -1968 ) was an American cartoonist best known for his syndicated panel Glamor Girls .
Jaladi Raja Rao ( Telugu : జాలాది రాజా రావు ) ( 9 August 1932 -- 14 October 2011 ) was a versatile writer , playwright and lyricist in Telugu cinema .
Lily Laskine ( 31 August 1893 -- 4 January 1988 ) was one of the most prominent harpists of the twentieth century .
Xu Yushi ( 許圉師 ) ( died 679 ) , formally Duke Jian of Ping'en ( 平恩簡公 ) , was briefly a chancellor of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
Charles Brandon , 3rd Duke of Suffolk ( 1537/1538 -- 14 July 1551 ) , known as Lord Charles Brandon until shortly before his death , was the son of the 1st Duke of Suffolk and the suo jure 12th Baroness Willoughby de Eresby .
John Egerton , 1st Earl of Bridgewater KB , PC ( 1579 -- 4 December 1649 ) was an English peer and politician from the Egerton family .
Luka Mislej ( 16 October 1658 -- 5 February 1727 ) was a Carniolan stonemason and sculptor .
Teodor Keko ( 1958 - -2002 ) was an Albanian writer , journalist , and politician .
Jacques Tavernier or Le Lyonnais ( 1625 - -1673 ) was a French privateer and buccaneer supposedly active in the Caribbean during the mid-17th century .
Peder Krabbe Gaarder ( 23 April 1814 -- 5 August 1883 ) was a Norwegian jurist and political theorist .
Thomas Hughes Jones ( 1895 - -1966 ) was a Welsh poet and writer from Ceredigion ( Cardiganshire ) in West Wales .
Ernest Warburton ( 10 June 1937 in Irlam -- 7 August 2001 in London ) was a noted musicologist who specialized in the music of Johann Christian Bach .
Albert Hermann Vermeer ( 1911 - -1980 ) , known as Al Vermeer , was an American cartoonist .
Charles Bayliss ( 1850 - 4 June 1897 ) , photographer , was born in Hadleigh , Suffolk , England in 1850 .
Urushibara Mokuchu ( 漆原木虫 ) ( 1888 - -1953 ) , given name Yoshijirô , was a Japanese print maker known for his many black - and - white prints of horses .
Lloyd Bertram ( 10 October 1903 -- 12 April 1971 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Umbarra , or King Merriman ( died 1904 ) was an Aboriginal elder of the Djirringanj / Yuin people of the Bermagui area on the South Coast of New South Wales .
Herman of Hauteville ( Ermanno in Italian ) ( c. 1045 -- 1097 ) was the younger son of Humphrey , count of Apulia and Calabria ( 1051 - -1057 ) , and his Lombard wife , Gaitelgrima of Salerno , also known as Altrude .
Gyula Kabos ( 19 March 1887 , Budapest -- 6 October 1941 , New York ) was a Hungarian actor and comedian , widely known for his comedic movie roles in the late 1930s .
William Wilding Galloway ( 1853 or 1854 - 27 September 1936 ) was an English businessman in the cotton industry .
Jack Mangan ( 6 May 1927 - 17 September 2013 ) was an Irish former Gaelic footballer who played as a goalkeeper for the Galway senior team .
Antonio Brioschi ( fl . c. 1725 -- 1750 ) was an Italian symphony composer who wrote at least twenty six symphonies ; most of which were preserved in the collection of Pierre Philibert de Blancheton .
Nicolai Hanson ( 24 August 1870 -- 14 October 1899 ) was a Norwegian zoologist and Antarctic explorer .
Kanety Krishna Menon ( 1942 - 2012 ) was a Telugu writer with about 80 short stories and 6 novels to his credit .
Kelly Ray Masters ( June 16 , 1897 -- 1987 ) , was an American writer using the pen name Zachary Ball .
Sir Charles William Siemens FRSA ( originally Carl Wilhelm Siemens ; 4 April 1823 -- 19 November 1883 ) was a German - born engineer who for most of his life worked in Britain and later became a British subject .
Yaacov Bar - Siman - Tov ( 1946 - 2013 ) was a prominent international relations and conflict resolution scholar .
Henry Levin ( 5 June 1909 -- 1 May 1980 ) began as a stage actor and director but was most notable as an American film director of over fifty feature films .
Fred Blackham ( 6 April 1873 -- 31 January 1967 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Shalom Zysman ( Hebrew : שלום זיסמן‎ , born 14 March 1914 , died 12 February 1967 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the General Zionists between 1951 and 1955 .
William Mellor ( 1888 - -1942 ) was a left - wing British journalist .
Horatio Nelson , 3rd Earl Nelson ( 7 August 1823 -- 25 February 1913 ) was a British politician .
Park Jong - yang(korean:박정양 , hanja:朴定陽 , 1841 - -1904 ) was a Korean Joseon dynasty politician and edification activist .
Lawrence Edwin Blazey ( 1902 - -1999 ) was an American artist and teacher , listed in `` Who 's Who in American Art '' .
Adoniram Judson Gordon ( 1836 - -1895 ) was an American Baptist preacher , writer , composer , and founder of Gordon College and Gordon--
Mary Julia Baldwin ( 4 October 1829 -- 1 July 1897 ) was a Virginia educator for whom Mary Baldwin College in Staunton , Virginia , is named .
Guido Martino ( 1895 in Naples - 1922 ) was an Italian follower of Benito Mussolini .
Victor Hasselblad ( March 8 , 1906 -- August 5 , 1978 ) was a Swedish inventor and photographer , known for inventing the Hasselblad 6x6 cm medium format camera .
Peter Oakley ( 20 August 1927 -- 23 March 2014 ) was a pensioner from Bakewell , Derbyshire , England .
Won - il Rhee ( Hangul : 이원일 ; hanja : 李圓一 ; 2 November 1960 -- 11 January 2011 ) was a South Korean digital art curator .
Robert L. Ketter ( 1929 - -1989 ) , was an authority on earthquake engineering research and a former president of the State University of New York at Buffalo ( UB ) .
Occo of Schleswig ( also Aage , Aagge , Ogge ) was the bishop of the Diocese of Schleswig between 1141 and 1145 and again from 1161 to 1167 .
Richard de la Pole ( 1480 -- 24 February 1525 ) was a pretender to the English crown .
Lothar Lutze ( 7 September 1927 -- 4 March 2015 ) was a Polish - born German scholar , writer , translator , Indologist and the Emeritus Professor of the Department of Modern Languages and Literatures at the Heidelberg University .
Ben Essing ( 1935 - -1994 ) was a Dutch impresario from Blokker , Netherlands .
Martha Blount ( 1690 - -1762 ) was an English woman , a friend of many English literary figures , especially Alexander Pope .
June Harwood ( June 16 , 1933 -- January , 2015 ) was an American painter based in California who made a name for herself in the 1960s as an inventive artist of the hard - edge movement .
Badr al - Jamali ( Arabic : بدر الجمالى‎‎ , 1015 - -1094 ) was a vizier , Amir al - Juyush ( امير الجيوش , Commander of Forces ) , Badi al - Duat ( بدى الدعاة , Chief Missionary ) and prominent statesman for the Fatimids under the Caliphate and Imamate of Al - Mustansir .
George Montagu , 1st Duke of Montagu KG , PC , FRS ( 26 July 1712 -- 23 May 1790 ) styled Lord Brudenell until 1732 and known as The Earl of Cardigan between 1732 and 1766 , was a British peer .
Jack Thorogood ( 4 April 1911 -- 1970 ) was an English professional footballer who scored 26 goals in 98 appearances in the Football League playing for Birmingham and Millwall .
Thomas Raeburn White ( 1875 - -1959 ) was a prominent attorney , political reformer , newspaper publisher and law professor in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
William Stevens Robinson ( 7 December 1818 , Concord , Massachusetts -- 11 March 1876 , Malden , Massachusetts ) was a United States journalist .
Felice Ficherelli ( 30 August 1605 -- 5 March 1660 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , born in San Gimignano and active mainly in Tuscany .
Oskar Minkowski ( 13 January 1858 -- 18 July 1931 ) held a professorship at the University of Breslau and is most famous for his research on diabetes .
Roberto Cantoral García ( 7 June 1935 -- 7 August 2010 ) was a Mexican composer , singer and songwriter .
Sir John Gostwick ( c.1480 - -15 April 1545 ) was an English courtier , administrator and MP .
Netta Rheinberg MBE ( 24 October 1911 at Willesden , Middlesex -- 18 June 2006 ) played for the English women 's cricket team in a single Test , but was a notable figure in the women 's game as an administrator and journalist .
Lalith William Samarasekera Athulathmudali ( Sinhala:ලලිත් ඇතුලත්මුදලි ; 26 November 1936 -- 23 April 1993 ) known as Lalith Athulathmudali was a prominent Sri Lankan politician of the United National Party and former Cabinet Minister of Trade , National Security , Agriculture , Education and deputy minister of defence .
Terry Bonchaka ( c. 1982 -- 29 October 2003 ) was a Ghanaian hiplife artist who after a performance died in a car accident .
John Henry Clarke ( 1853 -- 24 November 1931 ) was a prominent English classical homeopath .
Ross Gilmore Marvin ( 1880 - -1908 ) was an Arctic explorer who took part in Robert Peary 's 1905 - -1906 and 1908 - -1909 expeditions .
Laurier Lévesque ( October 13 , 1929 -- September , 2005 ) was a Canadian educator and a politician in the Province of New Brunswick .
Hugh Philp ( 1786 - -1856 ) was one of the most celebrated golf club makers of his era .
Jan Jiří Benda , also Johann Georg Benda ( baptized 16 April or August 30 , 1713 in Benátky nad Jizerou -- 1752 in Potsdam ) , was a Bohemian violinist and composer active in Germany .
Peregrine Bertie , 2nd Duke of Ancaster and Kesteven PC ( 29 April 1686 -- 1 January 1742 ) , styled The Honourable Peregrine Bertie between 1686 and 1704 , Lord Willoughby de Eresby between 1704 and 1715 and Marquess of Lindsey between 1715 and 1723 , was a British nobleman and statesman .
Sir Thomas Foote , 1st Baronet ( 1598 -- 12 October 1687 ) was a wealthy Citizen and grocer of London .
Li Chongjun ( 李重俊 ) ( died 7 August 707 ) , formally Crown Prince Jiemin ( 節愍太子 ) , was a crown prince of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , during the second reign of his father Emperor Zhongzong .
Jæger Dokk ( 12 December 1921 -- 17 June 2000 ) was a Norwegian insurance leader .
William T.B. Sanford ( died 1863 ) was a road builder , a landowner and the second postmaster of Los Angeles , California , after it became a part of the United States .
Edmund Robert Harris ( c. 1804 -- 27 May 1877 ) was an English lawyer from Preston , Lancashire , UK who was the principal benefactor of the Harris Museum , Harris Institute or Art School , Harris Technical School and the Harris Orphanage .
James Colville , 1st Lord Colville of Culross ( 1551 - -1629 ) was a Scottish soldier and courtier who served in the British Army .
Peter Diamand , CBE ( 8 June 1913 -- 16 January 1998 ) was an arts administrator and director of the Edinburgh Festival , carrying out that role from 1965 to 1978 .
Dr. Timothy Lin ( Chinese : 林道亮 ) ( 18 January 1911 - 11 October 2009 ) was a Chinese - born Old Testament scholar , master of Biblical languages , seminary professor , pastor , and president of China Evangelical Seminary in Taipei , Taiwan .
Aloisia Brial ( died 1972 ) was a queen of Uvea , ruling from 1953 until 1958 .
Emma Gelders Sterne ( 1894 - -1971 ) was an American author of children 's books , with a historical and literary focus .
Cú Chuimne ( died 747 ) was a monk of Iona .
Georg August Goldfuss ( Goldfuß , 18 April 1782 -- 2 October 1848 ) was a German palaeontologist , zoologist and botanist .
Erasmus Oswald Schreckenfuchs ( 1511 - -1579 ) was an Austrian humanist , astronomer and Hebraist .
Saint Sabbas Stratelates ( Sava Stratelat , Sabas Stratilat , Savva Stratilatus ) , Sabbas the General of Rome ( died 272 , Tiber River , Rome ) -- early Christian warrior saint and martyr , was Roman military general under emperor Aurelian .
Giovanni Nicotera ( 9 September 1828 -- 13 June 1894 ) was an Italian patriot and politician .
William Bell Scott ( 12 September 1811 -- 22 November 1890 ) was a Scottish artist in oils and watercolour and sometimes printmaking .
Johann Franz Schenk von Stauffenberg ( 1658 - -1740 ) was Prince - Bishop of Constance from 1704 to 1740 and Prince - Bishop of Augsburg from 1737 to 1740 .
Dave Arrell ( 5 April 1913 -- 22 March 1990 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Yannis Varveris ( Greek : Γιάννης Βαρβέρης ; 1955 -- 25 May 2011 ) was an award winning Greek poet , critic and translator .
Gustav Tafel ( October 13 , 1830 -- 1908 ) was a German - born colonel in the Union Army during the American Civil War , and the mayor of Cincinnati , Ohio , from 1897 to 1900 .
Thomas Newcomb ( 1682?--1765 ) was an English clergyman and teacher , known as a poet .
Robert Dwyer Joyce ( 1830 - 1883 ) was an Irish poet , writer , and collector of traditional Irish music .
Joanne Campbell ( 8 February 1964 -- 20 December 2002 ) was a British actress and drama therapist best known for playing Liz in the 1980s sitcom Me and My Girl and Josephine Baker on stage in This Is My Dream .
Henryk Ignacy Kamieński ( 31 July 1777 , Hruszwicy -- 26 May 1831 at Ostrołęka ) was a Polish brigadier general .
Sampson the Hospitable ( died c. 530 ) was a citizen of Constantinople who devoted his time to serving the poor of the city .
