John Bourchier , 1st Baron Berners , KG ( died May 1474 ) was an English peer .
H. Ramachandra Shastry ( 1906 -- 1992 ) was an Indian Carnatic flautist .
Werner Mark Linz ( 6 April 1935 -- 9 February 2013 ) was a German - American publisher who specialised in educational and international publishing in the Americas , Europe and the Middle East .
Willem Swidde ( Amsterdam c. 1660 - Stockholm 1697 ) was a Dutch draughtsman and engraver , active in Sweden .
Dayan Michoel Fisher ( c. 1910 -- January 7 , 2004 ) was a distinguished Orthodox rabbi , orator and exceptional Talmudic scholar , with complete mental mastery of the entire Talmud .
Edward Kellogg Baird ( July 13 , 1876 - 1951 ) , was an attorney and the president of the Century Opera Company .
Dame Gladys Marea Hartman , DBE ( 22 June 1920 -- 29 August 1994 ) was a British athletics sports administrator .
Vernon Steele ( 18 September 1882 -- 23 July 1955 ) was a Chilean - born British actor known for his appearances on the Broadway stage and in American films .
Věra Kohnová ( 1929 - -1942 ) was a Jewish girl from Czechoslovakia .
Rudolf Levy ( 1875 - -1944 ) was a renowned painter who worked with and was a student of Henri Matisse .
Ira Lawson Fiscus ( 1866 - 1949 ) was one of the first professional football players .
Fergus Scandal mac Crimthainn ( died 582 ) was a king of Munster from the Eóganacht Airthir Cliach branch of the Eoganachta , the ruling dynasty of Munster .
Bonafos Caballeria ( died 1464 ) was an anti - Jewish writer .
Thomas Fonnereau ( 27 October 1699 , in London -- 20 March 1779 ) was a British businessman and politician , the eldest son of the merchant Claude Fonnereau .
Sigurd Bødtker ( 2 February 1866 -- 6 March 1928 ) was a Norwegian theatre critic .
Henry Spencer Ashbee ( 21 April 1834 -- 29 July 1900 ) was a book collector , writer , and bibliographer , notorious for his massive , clandestine three volume bibliography of erotic literature written under the pseudonym of Pisanus Fraxi .
Mykola Koltsov ( Ukrainian : Микола Михайлович Кольцов ; 11 May 1936 -- 27 December 2011 ) was a Soviet footballer and Ukrainian football children and youth trainer .
Marcel Lanquetuit ( 8 June 1894 -- 21 May 1985 ) was a French composer , organist , conductor , improviser and teacher of music .
Timothy Read ( fl . 1626 -- 1647 ) was a comic actor of the Caroline era , and one of the most famous and popular performers of his generation .
Gerald Massey ( /ˈmæsi/ ; 29 May 1828 -- 29 October 1907 ) was an English poet and writer on Spiritualism and Ancient Egypt .
George Plant ( 1904 - -1942 ) was an IRA member who was executed by the Irish Government in 1942 .
Yusuf Salim ( 1929 - -2008 ) , born Joseph Blair , was an American jazz pianist and composer .
Ammar Ali Mohamed Ibrahim Ali Al Sherei ( Arabic : عمار علي محمد إبراهيم علي الشريعي‎ ) or more commonly known as Ammar El Sherei ( 16 April 1948 -- 7 December 2012 ) was an Egyptian music icon , performer and composer .
Joe Youlden ( 21 November 1883 -- 17 August 1959 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Giacinto Facchetti ( Italian pronunciation : ( dʒaˈtʃinto fakˈketti ) ; 18 July 1942 -- 4 September 2006 ) was an Italian football player .
Sir Thomas Myddelton , 2nd Baronet ( ca . 1651 -- 5 February 1684 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1679 and 1681 .
Deliar Noer ( 9 February 1926 -- 17 June 2008 ) was a Muslim scholar , politician , lecturer and former director of State University of Jakarta .
Rabbi Chaim Tzvi Teitelbaum , ( December 28 , 1879 -- January 21 , 1926 ) , ( 6 shevat 5686 on the Hebrew calendar ) , the Sigheter Rebbe , author of Atzei Chaim , was the oldest son of Rabbi Chananya Yom Tov Lipa Teitelbaum the Kedushas Yom Tov .
Hagbard Jonassen ( 24 May 1903 -- 1 March 1977 ) was a Danish botanist , quaternary geologist , war resister and nuclear disarmament proponent .
Thomas Stearn ( born 20 November 1796 at Cambridge ; died 21 March 1862 at Cambridge ) was an English professional cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1825 to 1840 .
Joe Bray ( 26 October 1886 -- 22 July 1955 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
José Benito Lamas ( Montevideo , 12 January 1787 - 9 May 1857 ) was a Roman Catholic priest from the Banda Oriental .
Harriet Sundström , ( 23 December 1872 -- 28 April 1961 in Stockholm ) was a Swedish artist .
Richard Kilby ( Kilbye ) ( 1560 - -1620 ) was an English scholar and priest .
Árpád Weisz ( also spelt Veisz ; 16 April 1896 -- 31 January 1944 ) was a Hungarian football player and manager .
Henry John Wallack ( 1790 -- 30 August 1870 ) was a British actor , stage manager , and brother of actor James William Wallack .
Kurt Lubinski ( October 19 , 1899 -- 1969 ) was a Jewish German and Dutch photojournalist .
John la Zouche , 7th Baron Zouche , 8th Baron St Maur ( 1459 - -1526 ) was a Yorkist nobleman , noted for his loyalty to Richard III , under whom he fought at the Battle of Bosworth .
James Nayler ( or Naylor ; 1616 - -1660 ) was an English Quaker leader .
Anastas Byku ( died 1878 ) was a 19th - century Albanian publisher and journalist .
Peter Ingram Weir ( 1864 - -1943 ) was a Scottish artist noted for his watercolour paintings of Scottish landscapes .
Stanley Stanley Van Ness ( February 28 , 1933 - -September 26 , 2007 ) was an American jurist who worked for a number of state agencies in New Jersey , USA .
William Whitshed ( 1679 - -1727 ) was an Irish politician and judge who held office as Solicitor - General and Lord Chief Justice of Ireland ; just before his death he moved to become Chief Justice of the Irish Common Pleas .
Mary Theresa Wiedefeld ( February 2 , 1886 -- November 1983 ) was the seventh president ( formerly principal ) of State Teachers College at Towson ( now Towson University ) .
Pilar Hidalgo - Lim ( 1893 - -1973 ) was a Filipino educator and civic leader .
Matts Evert Kulenius ( 8 March 1879 , Terjärv - 4 February 1958 ) was a Finnish schoolteacher and politician .
Louis Wollbrinck ( 1867 - 1928 ; spelling variations include `` Wollbrink '' and `` Wolbrinck '' ) was a civil servant , entrepreneur and builder in St. Louis , Missouri during the Gilded Age .
Philip Holzman ( 1922 - -2004 ) was the Esther and Sidney R. Rabb Professor of Psychology at Harvard University and a supervising and training analyst at the Boston Psychoanalytic Society and Institute .
Allan Gwynne - Jones CBE DSO RA ( 27 March 1892 -- 5 August 1982 ) was an English painter .
Lieutenant - Colonel Sir Emmanuel Hoyle , 1st Baronet OBE , JP ( 23 September 1866 -- 9 May 1939 ) , was a British woollen cloth manufacturer .
Diethard Hellmann ( 28 December 1928 -- 14 October 1999 ) was a German Kantor and an academic in Leipzig , Mainz and Munich .
Baltazar Nicolai Garben ( 19 February 1794 -- 21 April 1867 ) was a Norwegian architect and government minister .
Wincenty Kowalski ( 1892 - -1984 ) was a Polish military commander and a general of the Polish Army .
Huguccio was an Italian canon lawyer ( d. 1210 ) .
Fanny Davies ( 27 June 1861 -- 1 September 1934 ) was a British pianist who was particularly admired in Beethoven , Schumann , Brahms , and the early schools , but was also a very early London performer of the works of Debussy and Scriabin .
George Thomas Orlando Bridgeman JP ( 21 August 1823 -- 25 November 1895 ) was a Church of England clergyman and antiquary , the second son of George Bridgeman , 2nd Earl of Bradford .
Abdul Mannan Syed ( 3 August 1943 -- 5 September 2010 ) was a Bangladeshi poet , author and researcher .
Wally Messenger ( 1891 - -1961 ) was an Australian rugby league footballer of the 1910s .
Hajo Meyer ( 12 August 1924 -- 23 August 2014 ) was a Jewish German - Dutch physicist and an anti - Zionist political activist .
David Patillo White ( 1828 - 1903 ) was a shape note singing teacher , composer , and a co - issuer , with his father , of the 1870 Sacred Harp .
Umberto Ongania ( Venice 1867 - 1942 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of vedute of his native city .
Charles Milton Bell ( 1848 -- 1893 ) was an American photographer who was noted for his portraits of Native Americans and other figures of the United States in the late 1800s .
John Hans Stroh ( 15 May 1916 -- 17 September 1996 ) was an Australian health advocate , businessman and researcher .
Alonso de Cordova y Figueroa ( ? - August 9 , 1698 ) Spanish soldier born in Concepción , Chile , son of Alonso de Figueroa y Córdoba and father of the historian Pedro de Cordova y Figueroa .
Ludvig Kristensen Daa ( 19 August 1809 -- 12 June 1877 ) was a Norwegian historian , ethnologist , auditor , editor of magazines and newspapers , educator and politician .
Jirhangga ( Manchu : ; Chinese : 吉爾杭阿 ) ( ? -- June 1 , 1856 ) belonged to Bordered Yellow Banner .
Thomas Pell ( 1612/13 - -1669 ) was an English - born physician who bought the area known as Pelham , New York , as well as land that now includes the eastern Bronx and southern Westchester County , New York , and founded the town of Westchester at the head of navigation on Westchester Creek in 1654 .
George Alexander McGuire ( 28 March 1866 - -10 November 1934 ) was the first Bishop , Metropolitan Archbishop of the African Orthodox Church ( AOC ) .
Sir William McNair Snadden , 1st Baronet JP ( 15 January 1896 -- 23 November 1959 ) was a Scottish Tory politician .
Lieutenant General Sir Jasper Nicolls KCB ( 15 July 1778 -- 4 May 1849 ) was Commander - in - Chief , India .
Jason McRoy ( 26 November 1971 -- 24 August 1995 ) was an English professional mountain bike racer .
Michael Sigismund Frank ( 1 June 1770 -- 16 January 1847 ) was a Catholic artist and rediscoverer of the lost art of glass - painting .
Jenő Lasztovicza ( 21 December 1961 -- 8 January 2015 ) was a Hungarian horticultural engineer , politician and member of the National Assembly ( MP ) for Tapolca ( Veszprém County Constituency IV then III ) from 1998 until his death in early 2015 .
John Maxwell , 9th Lord Maxwell ( c.1583 -- 21 May 1613 ) was a Scottish Catholic nobleman .
Zhang Mancheng ( died 184 ) was a Yellow Turban rebel general during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Agostinho José da Mota ( b. 18 June 1824 Rio de Janeiro , d. 21 August 1878 Rio de Janeiro ) was a Brazilian painter and teacher .
Christiana Hartley ( 1872 -- 14 December 1948 ) was an English social and welfare rights activist , philanthropist and Liberal Party politician .
Eliezer Cogan ( 1762 - -1855 ) , was an English scholar and divine .
Minamoto no Kintada ( 889 - -948 , Japanese : 源 公忠 , also 源公忠朝臣 Miyamoto no Kintada Ason ) was a middle Heian waka poet and nobleman .
Dušan Grabrijan ( 1899 - -1952 ) was a Slovenian - Bosnian architect , architectural theorist and professor .
Publius Sulpicius Quirinius ( c. 51 BC -- AD 21 ) was a Roman aristocrat .
William de Aldeburgh , 2nd Baron Aldeburgh ( bef . 1358 -- 20 August 1391 ) was a British peer , the son of William de Aldeburgh , 1st Baron Aldeburgh .
Alan Clare ( Born Alan Jaycock ) ( 31 May 1921 -- 29 November 1993 ) was a British jazz pianist .
Georg Dietrich Leyding ( or Leiding ) ( German : ( ˈlaɪdɪŋ ) ; 23 February 1664 -- 10 May 1710 ) was a German composer and organist associated with the North German school .
Abraham Newland ( born c. 1730 , died 21 November 1807 aged 77 ) was the chief cashier at the Bank of England from 1782 to 1807 .
Jackie Oakes ( 6 December 1919 -- 3 December 1995 ) was a Scottish footballer who played for Wolverhampton Wanderers , Queen of the South , Blackburn Rovers and Manchester City .
Per Maltby ( 1933 -- 2006 ) is a Norwegian astronomer .
Larry Grayson ( 31 August 1923 -- 7 January 1995 ) , born William Sulley White , was an English comedian and television presenter who was best known in the 1970s and early ' 80s .
Abdul Rahman Jabarah ( عبدالرحمن جبارة ) was a Canadian killed in a July 2003 firefight with Saudi Arabian officials who believed he was involved in the Riyadh compound bombings by al - Qaeda .
Narasimha I ( Kannada : ಒಂದನೆ ನರಸಿಂಹ ) ( r.1152 - -1173 CE ) was a ruler of the Hoysala Empire .
Pope Innocent XI ( Latin : Innocentius XI ; 16 May 1611 -- 12 August 1689 ) , born Benedetto Odescalchi , was Pope from 21 September 1676 to his death in 1689 .
John Furphy ( 17 June 1842 -- 23 September 1920 ) was a blacksmith , best known for his Furphy Water Carts that were an important part of Australia 's history .
Alfred Charlesworth ( 9 May 1865 -- 4 December 1928 ) was an English cricketer who played for Derbyshire in 1888 and 1898 .
Jacques de l'Ange or the Monogrammist JAD ( fl . 1630 -- 1650 ) was a Flemish painter and draughtsman known for his genre scenes and history paintings executed in a Caravaggesque style .
Sidi Abd As - Salam Al - Asmar ( Arabic : عبد السلام الأسمر‎ , Al - Lasmar ` Abd as - Salām ) was a renowned religious Libyan Muslim saint who lived and died during the 15th century ( 1455 - 1575 CE ) .
Ji Dengkui ( Chinese : 纪登奎 ; 17 March 1923 -- 13 July 1988 ) was a prominent Chinese political figure during the Cultural Revolution .
Roland Ratzenberger ( 4 July 1960 -- 30 April 1994 ) was an Austrian racing driver who raced in sports prototype , Formula Nippon , Formula 3000 and Formula One .
Derek Humble ( March 1930 - 22 February 1971 ) was an English jazz alto saxophonist .
Vojislav Nikčević ( Serbian : Војислав Никчевић ; 18 January 1935 -- 2 July 2007 ) was a Montenegrin linguist .
Daniel of Morley ( c. 1140 -- c. 1210 ) was an English scholastic philosopher and astronomer .
Augustus George Vernon Harcourt FRS ( 24 December 1834 -- 23 August 1919 ) was an English chemist who spent his career at Oxford University .
Charles Kraitsir ( 28 January 1804 in Schmolnitz , Hungary -- 7 May 1860 in Morrisania , New York ) was a Hungarian - American philologist of Polish descent .
Matt Incigneri ( 1 February 1891 -- 24 October 1960)was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Saint Primianus or Primianus of Larino ( Italian : San Primiano or Primiano Martire ) ( d. 15 May 303 or 304 ) is the patron saint of Lesina , Apulia , in Italy .
Sir William Bisset Berry ( 26 July 1839 -- 8 June 1922 ) was a South African politician and the fourth Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the Cape Colony .
Aajonus Vonderplanitz ( born Richard Swigart in 1947 , died 28 August 2013 ) was an American nutritionist and activist , based in Malibu , California , and in Thailand , who developed the Primal Diet .
Edwin Davis French ( 1851 - -1906 ) was a bookplate engraver , who produced at least 330 engravings beginning in 1893 .
David Kraiselburd ( 1912 - -1974 ) was an Argentine journalist , newspaper publisher , and lawyer , best known for his commitment and actions against military regimes and political violence of both right- and left - wing extraction .
Alfred Harker FRS ( 19 February 1859 -- 28 July 1939 ) was an English geologist who specialised in petrology and interpretive petrography .
Dai Xi ( Chinese : 戴熙 ; pinyin : Dài Xī ; Wade -- Giles : Tai Hsi ) ( 1801 -- 1860 ) was a Chinese painter of the 19th century and representative of the academic manner .
Krzysztof Grodzicki ( died 1659 ) was a Polish artillery general , serving the Polish--
Rudolf Hitrec ( born 1903 in Zagreb - died 1970 in Zagreb ) was a Croatian footballer and international manager .
Peter Philipp ( 16 July 1971 -- 6 February 2014 ) was a German writer and comedian .
Saint Godric of Finchale ( or Saint Goderic ) ( c. 1065 -- 21 May 1170 ) was an English hermit , merchant and popular medieval saint , although he was never formally canonised .
Declan Costello ( 1 August 1926 -- 6 June 2011 ) was an Irish jurist and Fine Gael politician , who served as a Teachta Dála ( TD ) for twenty years , as Attorney General for four years and as a High Court judge for another twenty years before his retirement .
The Honourable Justice Geza Francis Kim Santow AO ( 11 March 1941 -- 10 April 2008 ) was an Australian Judge of the Supreme Court of New South Wales Court of Appeal .
Otto Huth ( 1906 - -1998 ) was a German theologian , ethnologist , archeologist and an expert on folklore , who taught at the University of Tübingen .
Hernán Díaz Arrieta ( 1891 - -1984 ) , widely known by his pen name , Alone , was a Chilean literary and film critic and memoirist .
Nebiogastes ( Greek : Νεοβιγάστης or Νεβιγάστιος ; died 407 AD ) was a Roman military commander that supported the usurper Constantine III .
James Bateman ( 18 July 1811 -- 27 November 1897 ) was a British landowner and accomplished horticulturist .
William Arthur Irving Washington ( 11 December 1879 -- 20 October 1927 ) was an English first - class Cricketer , who played forty four matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1900 and 1902 .
Alonso Enríquez ( Guadalcanal , 1354 Guadalupe , 1429 ) was Lord of Medina de Rioseco and Admiral of Castile .
William Henry Wahl ( 14 December 1848 Philadelphia - 23 March 1909 ) was a United States scientific editor and journalist .
Julián Robledo ( 1887 -- 1940 ) was a composer best known for the song `` Three O'Clock in the Morning '' .
John Crewe , 1st Baron Crewe ( 27 September 1742 -- 28 April 1829 ) , of Crewe Hall in Cheshire , was a British politician .
Dagon Khin Khin Lay ( Burmese : ဒဂုံ ခင်ခင်လေး ( dəɡòʊɴ kʰɪ̀ɴ kʰɪ̀ɴ lé ) ; 20 February 1904 -- 23 June 1981 ) was a Burmese novelist , screenwriter , and cinematographer .
June Bragger ( 2 June 1929 in Birmingham -- 27 June 1997 in Solihull , Warwickshire ) played 5 test matches for the England women 's cricket team between 1963 and 1966 .
Louis - Philippe Fiset ( 11 January 1854 -- 4 September 1934 ) was a local physician and politician in the Mauricie area .
Aldwine ( or Aldwyn , Aldwini or Ealdwine ; died 737 ) was a medieval Bishop of Lichfield and Bishop of Leicester .
Bandi Rajan Babu ( 9 February 1938 -- 25 August 2011 ) was an Indian photographer , known for his black and white pictures of tribal people .
Zahir Howaida ( Persian:ظاهرهویدا ) ( also spelled as Zahir Huwaida ; February 28 , 1946 -- 5 March 2012 ) was an Afghan singer .
Sir David Brewster KH PRSE FRS FSA(Scot ) FSSA MICE ( 11 December 1781 -- 10 February 1868 ) was a Scottish physicist , mathematician , astronomer , inventor , writer , historian of science and university principal .
Richard Gwinnett ( died 1717 ) was an English dramatist .
Henri Coutard ( 27 April 1876 -- 16 March 1950 ) was a French pioneer in radiation oncology and is credited with establishing radiotherapy as a clinical discipline .
George M'Gonigle ( 1889 - -1939 ) was Medical Officer of Health for Stockton - on - Tees , UK .
Noël Corbu ( 27 April 1912 -- 20 May 1968 ) is best known as a former restaurateur in the Southern French village of Rennes - le - Château , who from the mid-1950s circulated the story that the 19th - century French priest Bérenger Saunière discovered the treasure of Blanche of Castile .
Samuel Carlton Cooley ( April 15 , 1898 in Milford , New Jersey -- November 1981 in Stockton , New Jersey ) was an American violist and composer .
Ebba Lodden , née Sjuve ( 9 November 1913 -- 14 January 1997 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and politician for the Labour Party .
John Goldicutt ( 1793 -- 3 October 1842 ) was a British architect , the son of a bank cashier , who was better known for his architectural drawings than his completed buildings .
Ben E. May ( 1889 - -1972 ) was a Mobile , Alabama , businessman and philanthropist who helped found the Ben May Institute for Cancer Research at the University of Chicago and established the Southern Research Institute in Birmingham , Alabama .
Soo Ik Lee , MD ( died 1995 ) was a Korean - born American neurologist and a subspecialist in clinical neurophysiology based at the University of Virginia in Charlottesville , Virginia .
Edward John Trelawny ( 13 November 1792 -- 13 August 1881 ) was a biographer , novelist and adventurer who is best known for his friendship with the Romantic poets Percy Bysshe Shelley and Lord Byron .
Carl Gustaf Wolff ( 28 October 1800 - 19 July 1868 ) was a prominent Finnish shipowner and businessman during his time .
James Benjamin Taylor aka Jim B. Taylor ( December 1860 Cape Town -- 25 December 1944 Cape Town ) , was a South African Randlord and the fifth of 8 children of Isaac Rowland Taylor ( 6 November 1826 Holborn -- 22 August 1888 Kimberley ) and Jane Dorothea Hellet ( 7 May 1827 -- 27 November 1876 ) .
Maurice Jones ( alias Meurig Prysor ) ( 21 June 1863 -- 7 December 1957 ) was a priest and university educator .
Nicolas - André Monsiau ( 1754 -- 31 May 1837 ) was a French history painter and a refined draughtsman who turned to book illustration to supplement his income when the French Revolution disrupted patronage .
Alma Smith Jacobs ( 21 November 1916 -- 18 December 1997 ) was the first African American to serve as Montana State Librarian .
Christopher Ness ( 1621 - -1705 ) was an English ejected minister and theological author .
George Carpenter , 1st Earl of Tyrconnell ( 26 August 1723 -- 9 March 1762 ) , known as The Lord Carpenter between 1749 and 1761 , was a British peer and politician .
Yvonne Hubert ( 28 May 1895 -- 8 June 1988 ) was a Belgian - born Canadian pianist and pedagogue .
Thomas Lomar Gray ( 4 February 1850 -- 19 December 1908 ) was a Scottish engineer noted for his pioneering work in seismology .
Yoshio Masuda ( died 2009 ) was a former Japanese naval commander , regarded as the father of modern wave power technology .
Ray Gilhooley ( 15 July 1887 , in New York City , New York -- 18 September 1973 , in New Milford , Connecticut ) was an American racecar driver .
Yolanda Marculescu ( also Yolanda Marculescu - Stern ; 2 April 1923 -- 19 December 1992 ) was a Romanian coloratura soprano and diva of the Romanian National Opera in Bucharest from 1948 to 1968 .
Ian Roy MacLennan DFM , FRAIC , MTPIC , RAF & RCAF ( 4 April 1919 -- 6 November 2013 ) , was a Canadian fighter pilot of the Second World War who later became a successful architect .
Ernő Garami ( 13 December 1876 - 28 May 1935 ) was a Hungarian mechanic who became a social democratic politician and editor , who served as Minister of Justice in 1919 .
Sir Dennis Weatherstone KBE ( 29 November 1930 -- 13 June 2008 ) was the former CEO and Chairman of J. P. Morgan & Co ..
Haji Mir Mohammad Zainuddin ( d. 1850 AD ) was Faujdar during Bhonsle Dynasty at Nagpur .
Isabella d'Este ( 18 May 1474 -- 13 February 1539 ) was Marchesa of Mantua and one of the leading women of the Italian Renaissance as a major cultural and political figure .
John Wykeham Archer ( 1808 - -1864 ) was a British artist , engraver and writer .
Gabriel de la Corte ( 1648 -- 6 August 1694 ) was a Spanish painter with little success who lived in poverty , specializing in the painting of vases , baskets , garlands and signboards , that he had learned to paint without help of any teacher .
Gouyen ( in Mescalero Góyą́ń , `` the one who is wise '' ) ( c. 1857 - 1903 ) , was a 19th - century Apache woman noted for her heroism .
Sigurd Overby ( 1899 - -1979 ) was am American skier .
John Patrick Gillese ( March 7 , 1920 -- 23 October 1999 ) was an Irish - born Canadian author whose prolific career spanned six decades from the early 1940s to the late 1990s .
Đorđe Lobačev ( Serbian Cyrillic : Ђорђе Лобачев ) or Yuriy Lobachev ( Russian : Юрий Лобачев ; 1909 - -2002 ) was a Soviet Russian and Serbian - Yugoslavian comic strip author and illustrator .
Elsie Jane Wilson ( 7 November 1885 -- 16 January 1965 ) was a cinema actress , director , and writer during the early film era .
Aharon Dolgopolsky ( Hebrew : אהרון דולגופולסקי‎ , Russian : Арон Борисович Долгопольский ; 18 November 1930 -- 20 July 2012 ) was a Russian - Israeli linguist and one of the modern founders of comparative Nostratic linguistics .
Brian Keany , RSW , DA ( Edin ) ( 1945 -- February 2007 ) was a Scottish painter and teacher , who was elected as a member of The Royal Scottish Society of Painters in Watercolour .
Maria Korp ( born Maria Matilde ; 14 January 1955 -- 5 August 2005 ) was an Australian woman reported missing for four days and later found , barely alive , in the boot of her car on 13 February 2005 .
Lieutenant - Colonel Sir Cecil Kaye CBE CSI CIE ( 27 May 1868 -- 5 March 1935 ) was an officer in the British Indian Army .
José Antonio de Armas Chitty ( 30 November 1908 -- 6 October 1995 ) was a Venezuelan historian , poet , chronicler , essayist , biographer and researcher .
Maxwell M. Geffen ( born May 28 , 1896 , in Brooklyn , New York , died in March 1980 in New York ) was an American publisher .
Eduardo Propper de Callejón ( 1895 - -1972 ) was a Spanish diplomat who is mainly remembered for having facilitated the escape of thousands of Jews from occupied France during World War II between 1940 and 1944 .
Elizabeth de Burgh ( c. 1284 -- 27 October 1327 ) was the second wife and the only queen consort of King Robert the Bruce .
Prof . Hamida Barmaki ( 4 January 1970 -- 28 January 2011 ) was a renowned Afghan law professor and human rights activist .
Robert Getgood ( 1882 -- 30 November 1964 ) , sometimes known as Bob Getgood , was a politician and trade unionist in Northern Ireland .
Marcelle de Manziarly ( born 1/13 October 1899 , Kharkiv , Ukraine , then in Russian Empire - died 12 May 1989 ) was a French pianist , music educator , conductor and composer .
Theophilus Hastings , 7th Earl of Huntingdon PC ( 10 December 1650 -- 30 May 1701 ) was an English politician .
Clementina Suárez ( 12 May 1902 -- 1991 ) was an early Honduran writer who broke social norms .
Liv Paulsen ( 29 November 1925 -- 3 November 2001 ) was a Norwegian 100 metres sprinter and shot putter .
Joseph Morley Drake ( 1828 - 1886 ) was a doctor and educator .
Bruce Stern ( 25 September 1942 -- 18 July 2007 ) was an American attorney , photographer , and gun collector .
Johann Bernhard Fischer von Erlach ( 20 July 1656 -- 5 April 1723 ) was an Austrian architect , sculptor , and architectural historian whose Baroque architecture profoundly influenced and shaped the tastes of the Habsburg Empire .
Giulio Bartolocci ( 1 April 1613 -- 19 October 1687 ) was an Italian Cistercian Hebrew scholar and author of the four volume Bibliotheca Magna Rabbinica .
Tobias Querfurt , also Tobias Querfurt the Elder , ( 1660 -- 13 September 1734 ) was a German painter , draughtsman , and engraver .
Archduke Joseph Karl of Austria ( German : ( Erzherzog ) Josef Karl ( Ludwig ) von Österreich , Hungarian : Habsburg -- Toscanai József Károly ( Lajos ) főherceg ; Pressburg , 2 March 1833 -- Fiume , 13 June 1905 ) was a member of the Habsburg dynasty .
Daniel Davis Jr. ( 1813 - -1887 ) was an American photographer , daguerreotypist and ambrotypist .
Robert Hayden ( 4 August 1913 -- 25 February 1980 ) was an American poet , essayist , educator .
Baburao Patel ( 1904 - -1982 ) was an Indian publisher and writer , associated with films and politics .
Mufasir - ul - Haq ( 16 August 1944 , Karnal , India -- 27 July 1983 ) was a Pakistani cricketer who played in one Test in 1965 .
Robert McBain ( 9 October 1932 -- 24 April 2004 ) was an English actor , photographer and artist .
Anders Jonas Ångström ( Swedish : ( ˈan.ˈdəʂ ˈjuː.ˈnas ˈɔŋ.ˈstrøm ) ; 13 August 1814 -- 21 June 1874 ) was a Swedish physicist and one of the founders of the science of spectroscopy .
Praise - God Barebone ( c. 1598 --1679 ) , also spelled Barbon , was an English leather - seller , preacher and Fifth Monarchist .
John Frederick Weishampel ( April 4 , 1808 -- November , 1883 ) was a Baltimore , Maryland , minister and author .
Gustav Lærum ( 2 June 1870 , in Fet -- 21 May 1938 ) was a Norwegian satirical illustrator and sculptor .
John Gardiner Calkins Brainard ( 1795 - -1828 ) was an American lawyer , editor and poet .
William Weekes Fowler ( January 1849 - 3 June 1923 ) was an English clergyman and entomologist mainly interested in beetles .
Wallace Walter Atwood ( 1872 -- 1949 ) was an American geographer and geologist .
Michael Murgatroyd ( 1925 -- 2004 ) was an English - born Scottish nationalist political activist .
Catherine Trianon , née Boule , called La Trianon ( 1627 - 6 May 1681 ) , was a French fortune teller and poisoner , one of the accused in the famous Poison Affair .
Milton Drake ( 3 August , 1912 - 13 November , 2006 ) was an American lyricist and performing rights administrator .
Charles Wesley Hambly ( June 3 , 1863 -- 1942 ) was a drover and political figure in Ontario .
Johann Karl Zeune ( 29 October 1736 -- 8 November 1788 ) was a German academic and philologist .
Alexander Pitcairn ( 1750 -- 17 November 1814 ) was an English cricketer who played for Hampshire and the Marylebone Cricket Club from 1791 to 1792 .
Sir Baynham Throckmorton , 3rd Baronet ( 11 December 1629 -- 31 July 1681 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1656 and 1679 .
Joseph Henry Woodger ( 2 May 1894 - 8 March 1981 ) was a British theoretical biologist and philosopher of biology whose attempts to make biological sciences more rigorous and empirical was significantly influential to the philosophy of biology in the twentieth century .
Major Richard Harry Heslop ( 23 January 1907 -- 17 January 1973 ) , DSO was a British agent for the Special Operations Executive during World War II . He worked for the French section of the organisation , and under the codename Xavier , was the organiser of the Marksman circuit .
Marion Harvie Barnard ( 1874 - -1969 ) was a suffragist .
Tadun ( died 207 ) was a leader of the Wuhuan tribe during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Mads Alstrup ( 1808 - 1876 ) was the first Danish portrait photographer with his own studio .
Roy Holt ( 1942 - -2007 ) was a British contemporary artist specialising in painting .
Matei Ghica , a member of the Ghica family , was the Prince of Wallachia between 11 September 1752 and 22 June 1753 , and Prince of Moldavia between 22 June 1753 and 8 February 1756 .
Frank Farrelly ( 1931 -- 10 February 2013 ) was a therapist best known for the 1974 book Provocative Therapy , which advocated radical ( and sometimes humorous ) therapeutic moves intended to jolt the client out of his current mindset .
Dempsey Travis ( 1920 - 2009 ) was a real estate entrepreneur and civil rights activist who , later in life , became a prominent historian and author , writing extensively on African American history , politics , social issues , and music .
Arthur Murray Goodhart ( christened 25 July 1866 -- 1941 ) was a British composer and organist .
Pierre Robert Olivétan ( c.1506 - 1538 ) a Waldensian by faith was the first to translate the Bible into the French language starting from the Hebrew and Greek texts .
William Paton Ker ( usually referred to as W. P. Ker ; 30 August 1855 -- 17 July 1923 ) was a Scottish literary scholar and essayist .
Ken Rattenbury ( 10 September 1920 - -9 April 2001 ) was an English jazz trumpeter , pianist and composer and author born in Spilsby , Lincolnshire to Sidney , a postmaster .
Johan Albert Brommels ( 7 February 1891 , Övermark - 15 June 1962 ) was a Finnish schoolteacher , journalist and politician .
John Slany ( died 1632 ) , merchant , ship builder , born in Shropshire , England , was secretary of the Newfoundland Company and a member of the Merchant Taylor 's Company .
John Douglas Cook ( 1808?--1868 ) was a Scottish journalist , known as the founding editor of the Saturday Review .
Christian III Maurice , Duke of Saxe - Merseburg ( Merseburg , 7 November 1680 -- Merseburg , 14 November 1694 ) , was a duke of Saxe - Merseburg and member of the House of Wettin .
Marcel Capelle , born 11 December 1904 in Paris , died 1993 , was a professional French association footballer who played in defence .
Luka Svetec ( 8 October 1826 -- 28 January 1921 ) was a Slovene politician , lawyer , author and philologist .
Jean Avisse ( 1723 -- 1796 ) produced chairs , sofas , chaises and similar furniture in 18th century France .
Johann Philipp Christian Schulz ( also Schulze ; 24 September 1773 -- 30 January 1827 ) was a German composer and conductor .
Flight Lieutenant Nicholas Gresham Cooke , DFC ( 26 August 1913 -- 31 May 1940 ) , nicknamed Lanky , was a Royal Air Force pilot and Second World War flying ace most notable as an ace in a day .
Kā - kīwistāhāw ( or Kahkewistahaw , meaning `` He Who Flies Around '' ) ( c. 1810 -- 1906 ) was a Canadian Plains Cree chief .
Peruz ( 1866 ; Sivas - c . 1920 ; Istanbul ) also known as Peruz Hanım or Kantocu Peruz , Perviz Hanım was an Ottoman Armenian kanto singer , songwriter .
Sekukuni or Matsebe Sekhukhune , ( 1814 - -1882 ) , the son of King Sekwati , was king of the Bapedi ( or Marota ) of Sekukuniland , in the current Limpopo province of South Africa .
Jakub Cytryn ( 1909 -- 1943 ) was a Jewish painter in the interwar Poland .
Peggy Thorpe - Bates ( 11 August 1914 -- 26 December 1989 ) was an English actress who appeared in the first three series of Rumpole of the Bailey as Rumpole 's fearsome wife Hilda .
Gaspar Henaine Pérez ( 6 January 1926 -- 30 September 2011 ) , more commonly known by his pseudonym Capulina , was a Mexican comedian , actor , singer , film producer , and screenwriter .
Daniel Coker ( 1780 - -1846 ) , born Isaac Wright , was an African American and the first Methodist missionary to the British colony of Sierra Leone .
John Calvin Ferguson ( Chinese : 福開森 ; pinyin : Fú Kāisēn ; 1866 -- 1945 ) was an American scholar of Chinese art , collector and procurer for American art museums , and a Chinese governmental adviser .
Augusto Lamo Castillo ( 25 September 1938 in Badajoz -- 10 September 2002 ) was a Spanish football referee .
Marlen Haushofer née Marie Helene Frauendorfer ( 11 April 1920 -- 21 March 1970 ) was an Austrian author , most famous for her novel The Wall .
Jan Baptist Bonnecroy or Jean Baptiste Bonnecroy ( 1618 -- after 1676 ) was a Flemish painter and engraver known for his large panoramic city views and marine paintings .
István Kovacsóczy de Körtvélyfa ( ? -- October 1634 ) was a Hungarian noble in the Principality of Transylvania , who served as Chancellor of Transylvania from 1622 to 1634 .
Hugh of Saxony or Hugh de Saxony(ca . 850 -- 880 ) was a Frankish prince , a member of the Carolingian dynasty .
Baptist Levinz , sometimes Baptiste or Baptist Levinge , ( died 1693 ) was an Anglican churchman .
George Matthews Harding ( 1882 - -1959 ) was a war artist for the United States Army during World War I.
John Frederic Inglis ( 16 July 1853 -- 27 February 1923 ) was a Scottish amateur sportsman who became a Major in the Duke of Edinburgh 's ( Wiltshire Regiment ) .
Lukas Heller ( 1930 -- 2 November 1988 ) was a German screenwriter born in Kiel .
Benjamin Matlack Everhart ( born near West Chester , Pennsylvania , 24 April 1818 ; died in West Chester , 22 September 1904 ) was a United States mycologist .
Mai Jones ( 6 February 1899 -- 7 May 1960 ) , was a Welsh songwriter , entertainer and radio producer .
William Fleetwood Sheppard ( 20 November 1863 -- 12 October 1936 ) Australian - British civil servant , mathematician and statistician remembered for his work in finite differences , interpolation and statistical theory , known in particular for the eponymous Sheppard 's corrections .
Zhang Da'an ( 張大安 ) ( died 684 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
Negübei was a khan of the Chagatai Khanate ( 1271 - 1272 ? ) .
Evelyn Walkden ( Oct 1893 - 12 September 1970 ) was a British politician and trades unionist .
On 10 January 2002 , Bishop Karas suffered a stroke and fell into a coma ; he died in the early morning of January 17 , the day before his 47th birthday .
Carl Heinrich Biber ( 4 September 1681 -- 19 November 1749 ) was a late Baroque violinist and composer .
Cesare Fracanzano ( 1605 - 1651 ) , a Neapolitan painter who flourished in the 17th century , was a pupil of Spagnoletto .
Johannes Wolleb ( Wollebius ) ( 1589 - -1629 ) was a Swiss Protestant theologian .
Thomas Bartholin ( /bɑːrˈtoʊlɪn , ˈbɑːrtəlɪn/ ; Latinized : Thomas Bartholinus ; 20 October 1616 -- 4 December 1680 ) was a Danish physician , mathematician , and theologian .
James Walker Dawson ( 1870 , India - 26 June 1927 , Edinburgh ) was a Scottish pathologist remembered for his work on multiple sclerosis including the description of the eponymous Dawson 's fingers .
Hyalmar Blixen Lerena ( born 1916/17 , died February 17 , 2007 ) was a Uruguayan poet , novelist and essayist .
John Cheltenham Wake ( 1837 - -1882 ) was an English oil painter who specialised in seascape and marine art .
Maurice Goldman ( 1910 - -1984 ) was an internationally known composer and conductor .
Clément Marchand ( 12 September 1912 -- 22 April 2013 ) was a Canadian author , poet and journalist and publisher .
George Macculloch Miller ( 1832 - -1917 ) , was a lawyer and secretary of Cathedral of St. John the Divine .
Lujo Györy ( 28 May 1930 -- 28 March 2012 ) was a Croatian handball player , referee and official .
Aman Kekilov ( Аман Кекилов ; Keshi village , current Ahal Province , 9 May 1912 -- 13 December 1974 ) was a Soviet Turkmen poet .
Adriaan van der Stel ( -Ceylon , 25 May 1646 ) was opperhoofd of Mauritius from 1640 ? to 1645 .
Obadiah J. Barker , Jr. ( October 31 , 1856 -- July 1908 ) was a Los Angeles business man and the founder and president of the furniture company , Barker Brothers .
John Green Crosse , FRCS , FRS ( 1790 - -1850 ) was a well - known English surgeon of his day , at the old Norfolk and Norwich Hospital .
Ernest Hodkin ( 1890 -- 1967 ) was an English footballer who played for Sunderland and Stoke .
Blessed John Story ( or Storey ) ( 1504 -- 1 June 1571 ) was an English Roman Catholic martyr and Member of Parliament .
Gaylord Powless ( 1946 - -2001 ) was a Mohawk lacrosse player from the Six Nations of the Grand River First Nation Indian reserve near Brantford , Ontario .
Andrew Baird ( 11 June 1866 in Irvine -- 1916 ) was a Scottish footballer , who played for Queen 's Park and Scotland .
Harry Whittier Frees ( 1879 - -1953 ) was an American photographer who created novelty postcards and children 's books based on his photographs of live , posed animals .
Pope Gregory XV ( Latin : Gregorius XV ; 9 January 1554 -- 8 July 1623 ) , born Alessandro Ludovisi , was Pope from 9 February 1621 to his death in 1623 .
Enrique Campos Menéndez ( 1914 - -2007 ) was Marquee of Torreblanca and a Chilean writer .
Rami Mehmed Pasha ( 1645 - -1706 ) was an Ottoman statesman and poet who served as Grand Vizier ( 1703 ) and governor of Cyprus and of Egypt ( 1704 - -06 ) .
Rhoda Delaval Astley ( 1 July 1725 -- 1757 ) was an English aristocrat and artist .
Shakuntala Devi ( 4 November 1929 -- 21 April 2013 ) was an Indian writer and mental calculator , popularly known as the `` human computer '' .
Lou Miami ( 1956 -- August 1995 ) was an American punk musician based in Boston , Massachusetts , United States .
Jacques Christian or Jacob Christiaan Pielat ( sometimes Pielaat ) ( 27 August 1692 , Rotterdam - ca . 3 August 1740 , Loosduinen ) was the 22nd Governor of Ceylon during the Dutch colonial time from 2 December 1732 until 27 January 1734 .
AVM Saeedullah Khan ( 23 July 1926 - 2002 ) was one of the pioneering officers of Pakistan Air Force .
Samuel Eaton ( 1596?--1665 ) , was an English independent divine .
Maria Cumani Quasimodo ( 7 January 1908 - 22 November 1995 ) was an Italian actress and dancer .
Herbert Rose Barraud ( 24 August 1845 - 1896 ) was a noted portrait photographer who had studios in London and Liverpool .
Howard Wilbert Nowell ( May 16 , 1872 - -1940 ) , was instructor in pathology at Boston University , and a pioneering cancer researcher .
James Milner , 9th Seigneur of Sark ( died 1730 ) bought the fief of Sark from John Johnson in 1723 for £ 5,000 , and was Seigneur of Sark until 1730 .
Alfredo Le Pera ( 4 June 1900 -- 24 June 1935 ) was a journalist , dramatist , and lyricist , best known for his brief but fruitful collaboration with the renowned tango singer Carlos Gardel .
Anton Štefánek ( 15 April 1877 -- 29 April 1964 ) was a Slovak politician and sociologist who was involved in the campaign for Czech and Slovak unity and independence from the Austro - Hungarian Empire .
Lottie Gilson ( 1862 -- June 10 , 1912 ) was a popular comedian and vaudeville singer of the 1880s and 1890s .
Maria Fortunata d'Este ( 24 November 1731 -- 21 September 1803 ) was a Modenese princess by birth and a princess of the blood of France by marriage .
Beata Oxenstierna ( 1591 in Reval Castle -- 16 March 1652 ) , was a Swedish noblewoman and courtier .
Nazario Sauro ( 20 September 1880 -- 10 August 1916 ) was an Austrian - born Italian irredentist and sailor .
William Josephus Stafford ( 1781 - 1823 ) , also known as William S. Stafford and Jose Guillermo Estifano , was a sea captain and privateer during the War of 1812 and afterward .
The McKinleys were a Scottish pop duo comprising sisters Sheila ( ca . 1941 -- 16 December 2012 ) and Jeanette McKinley .
Sir Louis Mallet CB PC ( 14 March 1823 -- 16 February 1890 ) was a British civil servant who was an advocate of free trade and served on the Council of India .
James C. Rose ( 1913 - -1991 ) was a prominent landscape architect and author of the twentieth century .
Arnljot Eggen ( 13 August 1923 -- 4 February 2009 ) was a Norwegian poet who also wrote plays and children 's books .
Manuel María Mallarino Ibargüen ( 18 June 1808 -- 6 January 1872 ) was the 8th Vice President of New Granada , and as such served as Acting President from 1855 to 1857 .
Niklaus Stump ( 23 December 1920 -- 30 April 2005 ) was a Swiss cross - country and Nordic combined skier who competed during the 1940s .
Thomas Nelson , 2nd Earl Nelson , born Thomas Bolton ( 7 July 1786 -- 1 November 1835 ) , was the 2nd Earl Nelson .
Luo Zundian ( Chinese : 羅遵殿 ; died March 19 , 1860 ) was a Chinese provincial governor who ended several rebellions , but forced to commit suicide in the Second rout the Army Group Jiangnan in Hangzhou when the Taiping forces conquered the city .
Miguel Gómez Bao ( 1894 -17 September 1961 ) was a Spanish - born Argentine actor of the Golden Age of Argentine cinema .
Leonard Edgcombe ( died 1696 ) was a ship 's captain with the Hudson 's Bay Company who made a number of voyages into Hudson Bay and James Bay on behalf of the company .
John Bowra ( baptised 3 June 1716 at Sevenoaks , Kent ; buried 22 December 1785 at Sevenoaks ) was an English professional cricketer of the mid - Georgian period who made 5 known appearances in first - class cricket .
Leonora Corbett ( 28 June 1908 -- 29 July 1960 ) was an English actress , noted for her charm and elegance in stage roles , and for a number of films made in the 1930s .
Theodore Kremer ( 1871 - -1923 ) was a German born playwright whose works include The Fatal Wedding .
Albert Dumouchel ( 15 April 1916 -- 11 January 1971 ) was a Canadian artist , photographer and printmaker .
Anand Shetty ( c. 1961 -- 21 May 2013 ) was an Indian athlete who specialized in sprints .
Vincenzo Foppa ( c. 1430 -- c. 1515 ) was a Northern - Italian painter , active in a Renaissance style .
Andrieu Contredit d'Arras ( c.1200 - -1248 ) was a trouvère from Arras and active in the Puy d'Arras .
Albert Suho ( before 1390 - after 1449 ) was a German cleric and writer .
Emperor Hiệp Hòa , also known as Nguyễn Phúc Hồng Dật , was the sixth emperor of the Vietnamese Nguyễn Dynasty and reigned for four months ( 30 July 1883 -- 29 November 1883 ) .
Jack Flavell ( 15 May 1929 -- 25 February 2004 ) was an English cricketer who played in four Tests for England from 1961 to 1964 .
Andrea Biglia ( c.1395 -- 1435 ) was an Italian Augustinian humanist , known as a moral philosopher and historian .
Marcus Claudius Fronto ( killed in battle AD 170 ) was a Roman senator and Consul , and a general in the Imperial Roman army during the reigns of emperors Antoninus Pius ( r.138 - 61 ) and Marcus Aurelius ( r. 161 - 80 ) .
Nakdimon Rogel ( 1925 - 8 December 2011 ) was an Israeli journalist , broadcaster and pioneer of Israeli television .
Bhagwan Das ( 12 January 1869 -- 18 September 1958 ) was an Indian Theosophist and public figure .
Muhammad Abu Zahra ( 1898 - -1974 ) was an Egyptian public intellectual , scholar of Islamic law , and author .
James Dafforne ( died 1880 ) was an English journalist , known for his art criticism in The Art Journal .
Brian Kenneth Hobbs ( 1937 - -2004 ) was a medical doctor in Adelaide , South Australia and chair of Community Aid Abroad .
Cornelis Pietersz Bega , or Cornelis Pietersz Begijn ( 1631/1632 -- 27 August 1664 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter and engraver .
Ernricus Pirhing ( born at Sigarthin , near Passau , 1606 ; died between 1678 and 1681 ) was a German Jesuit canon lawyer .
Charles FitzRoy , 2nd Duke of Grafton KG PC FRS ( 25 October 1683 -- 6 May 1757 ) was an Irish and English politician .
Isaiah Emmanuel Morter ( sometimes spelled Isiah ) ( 1860 - 7 April 1924 ) was born in 1860 in the Freetown district of Belize .
Murong Huang ( Chinese : 慕容皝 ; 297 - -348 ) , courtesy name Yuanzhen ( 元真 ) , formally Prince Wenming of ( Former ) Yan ( ( 前)燕文明王 ) was a ruler of the Xianbei state Former Yan and the commonly recognized founder of the state .
George Henry Bachhoffner ( 1810 - -1879 ) , was a British scientist , one of the founders of the London Polytechnic Institution , and a lecturer on scientific subjects .
Abu Shuayb Ayub Ibn Said Erredad al - Sanhaji Assariya ( French transliteration Abou Chouaib ) ( died 1176 - 7 ) is the patron saint of Azemmour , Morocco .
Eladio Acosta Arteaga ( 9 April 1916 -- 30 January 2012 ) was a Colombian Prelate of Roman Catholic Church .
Rev. Dr. John Henry Barrows ( 1847 - -1902 ) was an American clergyman of First Presbyterian Church and Chairman of the 1883 General Committee on the Congress of Religions ( later to be known as the World 's Parliament of Religions ) .
Admiral of the Fleet Sir Cloudesley Shovell ( c. November 1650 -- 22 October or 23 October 1707 ) , was an English naval officer .
Edward John Dunn ( 1 November 1844 -- 20 April 1937 ) was an English - born Australian geologist , winner of the 1905 Murchison Medal .
Heinrich Koenen ( 12 May 1910 -- February 1945 ) was a German engineer , anti - fascist resistance fighter and agent of the Soviet military intelligence service GRU .
Louis Dyer ( 1851 - -1908 ) was an American educator and author born in Chicago in the U.S. state of Illinois .
Air Vice - Marshal Peter Furniss , DFC ( 16 July 1919 -- 11 December 2005 ) was a British solicitor and senior Royal Air Force officer .
Ștefan Gușă or Gușe ( 17 April 1940 -- 28 March 1994 ) was a Romanian general who was the Chief of the General Staff of the Romanian Armed Forces between 1986 and 1989 .
Quauhtlatoa ( or Cuauhtlatoa ) ( 1 Flint ( 1428 ) -- 4 Reed ( 1431)/7 Flint ( 1460)/8 House ( 1461 ) ) was a tlatoani ( king , ruler ) of the Nahua city - state Tlatelolco .
Are nt Greve de Besche ( 4 December 1878 -- 17 September 1945 ) was a Norwegian bacteriologist .
George Beranger ( 27 March 1893 -- 8 March 1973 ) , also known as André Beranger , was an Australian actor and film director of stage and Hollywood .
Karl Adolf Lorenz ( 13 August 1837 -- 3 March 1923 ) was a German conductor , composer , and music pedagogue .
Rebecca Rawson ( May 23 , 1656 , Massachusetts - June 7-June 9 , 1692 , near Port Royal , Jamaica ) was the heroine of the 1849 book Leaves from Margaret Smith 's Journal , in the Province of Massachusetts Bay ( by John G. Whittier ) .
Eduard Clemens Fechner ( 21 August 1799 -- 7 February 1861 ) was a German portrait painter and an etcher .
Qazi Syed Hayatullah ( died c. 1135 AH / 1722 AD ) was a Muslim scholar of Fiqh from Sakras , District Gurgaon ( Haryana , India ) .
Ezra Stoller ( 16 May 1915 -- 29 October 2004 ) was an American architectural photographer .
Konstantinos Mazarakis - Ainian ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Μαζαράκης-Αινιάν , 1869 - -1949 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General .

Dr. Victor George Springett ( 28 September 1916 -- 8 September 1990 ) was a politician in the State of South Australia .
Kailash Radhabai Subbarayan , nee Kudmul ( b. April 22 , 1891-d . 1960 ) was an Indian politician , women 's rights activist and social reformer .
Leo Motzkin ( also Mozkin ; 1867 -- 7 November 1933 ) was a Russian Zionist leader .
Thomas Francis Brennan ( 6 October 1855 -- 20 March 1916 ) was an American Catholic bishop who served as the first Catholic bishop of Dallas from 1891 to 1893 .
Mauri Nyberg - Noroma ( born 31 January 1908 in Viborg , died 23 December 1939 in Muolaa ) was a Finnish gymnast .
Richard Sloley ( 20 August 1891 - -17 October 1946 ) , sometimes known as Dick Stoley , was an English amateur football inside right who played in the Football League for Aston Villa .
Henno Martin ( March 15 , 1910 -- January 7 1998 ) was a German professor of geology who , along with Hermann Korn , lived for two years in the Namib Desert to avoid internment during the Second World War .
George Adamson MBE ( 3 February 1906 -- 20 August 1989 ) , also known as the Baba ya Simba ( `` Father of Lions '' in Swahili ) , was a British wildlife conservationist and author .
Walter Nugent Monck ( 1877 - 1958 ) was an English theatre director and founder of Maddermarket Theatre , Norwich .
Maximilian Joseph Franz of Oer ( 1806 - -1846 ) was a German author , baron , and older brother of the notable artist Theobald von Oer .
Kane O'Hara ( 1711 or 1712 -- 17 June 1782 ) was an Irish composer and playwright .
Philip Rosseter ( 1568 -- 5 May 1623 ) was an English composer and musician , as well as a theatrical manager .
Thamizhavel G. Sarangapani , ( Tamil : தமிழவேள் கோ. சாரங்கபாணி , 19 April 1903 -- 16 March 1974 ) or Kosa as he was also known , a Tamil writer and publisher , was born in Thiruvarur , Tamil Nadu , on 20 April 1903 .
Carl Hoddle ( 8 March 1967 -- 2 March 2008 ) was an English football player and coach .
Jeanne Duval ( French pronunciation : ​(ʒan dyˈval ) ) ( c.1820 -- 1862 ) was a Haitian - born actress and dancer of mixed French and black African ancestry .
Konstantinos Manetas ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Μανέτας , 1879 - -1960 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General and served as Chief of the Hellenic Army General Staff in 1931 .
Erich Wenk ( 12 August 1923 -- 30 March 2012 ) was a German bass - baritone singer in opera and especially in concert .
Jean Clérée ( 1450 - -1507 ) was the Master of the Order of Preachers in 1507 .
George Wolfe Plank ( 1883 - -1965 ) was an American artist illustrator , chiefly remembered for his long - term association with Vogue Magazine , which resulted in years of covers in an Art Deco style related to that of Helen Dryden and influenced , by among others , Edmund Dulac .
Count Lasher was the stage - name of Terence Parkins ( c.1921 -- 1977 ) , a Jamaican singer and songwriter .
Paul Parmalee ( 1926 - 2006 ) was an early worker in the field of zooarchaeology .
Ngô Đình Cẩn ( 1911 -- 9 May 1964 ) was a younger brother and confidant of South Vietnam 's first president , Ngô Đình Diệm , and an important member of the Diệm government .
The Rev. Samuel Lodge ( 11 February 1829 -- 5 September 1897 ) was the author of Scrivelsby , the Home of the Champions He was a headmaster of Horncastle Grammar School , Lincolnshire , rector for 30 years of Scrivelsby in Lincolnshire , and a Canon of Lincoln Cathedral .
James Milnes Gaskell ( 19 October 1810 -- 5 February 1873 ) was a British Conservative politician .
Jane Deans ( née McIlraith , 21 April 1823 -- 19 January 1911 ) was a New Zealand pioneer and community leader .
William G. Sebold ( Wilhelm Georg Debrowski ; 10 March 1899 in Mülheim , Germany -- 16 February 1970 in Walnut Creek , California ) was a United States citizen when he visited Germany and was coerced into becoming a spy .
Theodore Bruce ( 5 April 1847 -- 2 July 1911 ) was an auctioneer , politician and Mayor of Adelaide 1904 - 1907 .
Shayah Charnam ( d. 1929 ) was a Jewish communist activist in Poland .
Elizabeth Hanbury ( 9 June 1793 -- 31 October 1901 ) was a British philanthropist who worked with Elizabeth Fry .
Oluf Gjerset ( 1 June 1848 -- 29 May 1941 ) was a Norwegian - born , American politician from Minnesota .
Sir Nicholas Malby ( 1530?--1584 ) was an English soldier active in Ireland , Lord President of Connaught from 1579 to 1581 .
Godfrid Haraldsson ( c. 820 -- c. 856 ) was the son of the Danish king Harald Klak .
George Blackman ( 1897 -- March 2003 ) , was born in Barbados and served as a Private in the 4th British West Indies Regiment during the First World War .
Georg Hochgesang ( 3 November 1897 -- 12 June 1988 ) was a German football forward , who played for 1 .
Przemysław of Racibórz ( Polish : Przemysław raciborski ) ( between 21 October 1258 and 12 June 1268 -- 7 May 1306 ) was a Duke of Racibórz since 1282 until his death ( until 1290 with his brother as co - ruler ) .
Anthony Rous ( 1605 -- 1 May 1677 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1653 and 1660 .
Edward Cromwell , 3rd Baron Cromwell , Kt ( c. 1560 -- 27 April 1607 ) was an English peer .
James Cardwell Gardner ( 29 June 1864 -- 25 March 1935 ) , also known by his nickname Jumps Gardner , was an English doctor and amateur rower who won the Diamond Challenge Sculls at Henley Royal Regatta and the Wingfield Sculls and rowed for Cambridge in the Boat Race in 1888 , 1889 and 1890 .
Charles Bruce , 5th Earl of Elgin and 9th Earl of Kincardine ( 6 July 1732 -- 14 May 1771 ) was the son of William Bruce , 8th Earl of Kincardine .
Wang Chucun ( 王處存 ) ( 831 - -895 ) was a general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who controlled Yiwu Circuit ( 義武 , headquartered in modern Baoding , Hebei ) in late Tang .
Emil Diesen ( 14 April 1880 -- 24 June 1942 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and editor .
Michael John O'Brien ( 19 September 1851 -- 26 October 1940 ) was a railway builder , industrialist and philanthropist .
Robert Kloster ( 8 March 1905 -- 7 February 1979 ) was a Norwegian museum director and art historian .
Otto Carlmar ( 14 August 1902 -- 20 May 1987 ) was a Norwegian film producer , writer and actor , most active during the 1950s .
Fazzio ( Fatius , Fazius , Facius ) of Verona ( 1190 - -1272 ) was an Italian saint .
Bernard Tilakaratna , SLOS ( 1927 - -2004 ) was a senior diplomat and bureaucrat of the Sri Lankan government .
Randolph Fields ( 29 December 1952 , Santa Monica California -- 24 February 1997 , Jersey , Channel Islands ) was an Anglo - American lawyer who founded British Atlantic Airways which later became Virgin Atlantic Airways .
Mohammad Biriya and the original name Mohammad Baghezadeh ( Azerbaijani : Məhəmməd Biriya , Persian : محمد بي‌ريا‎‎ ; born 1914 in Tabriz -- death 1985 in Tabriz ) was an Iranian Azerbaijani poet and politician .
John Hay , 4th Marquess of Tweeddale PC ( 1695 -- 9 December 1762 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Mohan Upreti ( Hindi : मोहन उप्रेती ) ( 1928 - -1997 ) was an Indian theatre director , playwright and a music composer , considered one of the pioneers in Indian theatre music .

Ingenuin Molitor ( Habach , 1610 - -1669 ) was a German - born Franciscan priest and composer .
