Marx W. Wartofsky ( 1928 - -1997 ) was a philosopher , specialising in historical epistemology .
Sir Henry Wentworth of Nettlestead , Suffolk , KB ( born c.1448 , died between 17 August 1499 and 27 February 1501 ) , de jure 4th Baron Despenser , was the grandfather of Henry VIII 's third wife , Jane Seymour , and the great - grandfather of Jane 's son , Edward VI .
Edmond de Stoutz ( 18 December 1920 -- 28 January 1997 ) was a Swiss conductor from Zurich .
Ee - mat - la , also known as King Philip , ( died 1839 ) was a Seminole chief during the Second Seminole War .
Alf Schwarz ( 22 May 1935 -- 3 August 2015 ) was a Canadian sociologist noted for his research in Sub - Saharan Africa .
Johann Schwarzer ( 30 August 1880 -- 10 October 1914 ) was an Austrian photographer and pioneer producer of adult films through his Saturn - Film company .
Morton Bartlett ( 1909 in Boston -- 1992 ) was an American freelance photographer and graphic designer who , from 1936 to 1963 , devoted much of his spare time to creating and photographing a series of intricately carved lifelike plaster dolls .
Christoffer Hjort ( 1561 - -1616 ) was a Norwegian clergyman and crypto - Catholic .
Dai Woodham , MBE , BEM ( 5 September 1919 - 12 September 1994 ) , born David Lloyd Victor Woodham , is remembered by many steam railway enthusiasts as the man who saved over 200 former British Railways steam locomotives from the scrap heap .
Martyn Fonnereau ( 19 March 1741 -- 18 May 1817 ) was the second son of Zachary Philip Fonnereau , a British merchant and banker of Huguenot extraction .
Liam Forde was an alias used by Séamas Ó Maoiléoin ( aka James Malone ) ( 1891 - 1958 ) of Tyrrellspass , County Westmeath , Ireland when working as a spy for Michael Collins .
Georges Prosper Remi (; 22 May 1907 -- 3 March 1983 ) , known by the pen name Hergé ( ) , was a Belgian cartoonist .
John Northcote ( 1570 - 1632 ) of Uton and Hayne , Newton St Cyres , near Crediton , Devon , was a member of the Devonshire gentry , lord of the manor of Newton St Cyres , who is chiefly known to history for his artistically acclaimed effigy and monument in Newton St Cyres Church .
Alan Arthur ( 12 November 1905 -- 9 August 1979 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played thirty games for Essendon in 1928 and 1930 in the Victorian Football League ( now the AFL ) .
Jeffery Hart Bent , occasionally known as Geoffrey Hart Bent ( 1781 -- 29 June 1852 ) was the first judge in the colony of New South Wales , Australia .
Ven Hong Choon died on 25 December 1990 , after which a relic stupa and a memorial hall was built at the Phor Kark See Monastery commemorating him .
William Stewart , 2nd Viscount Mountjoy ( 1675 - 10 January 1728 ) , was an Anglo - Irish peer .
Wolfgang von Graben , also Wolfgang de Groben ( de Gröben ) ( 1465 in Kornberg castle , Styria -- 11 December 1521 ) , was a member of the Austrian nobility .
Talib Chakwali ( 1900 - 1988 ) was an Urdu ghazal and nazm writer .
Francis Colegrove ( c. 1667 -- c. 1759 ) was an English colonial immigrant , born most likely in Oxfordshire or London , England , although others have suggested Glamorgan , Wales , who settled in Warwick , Rhode Island , in about 1688 .
Thomas Brerewood ( c.1670 - 22 December 1746 ) , was a ' Gentleman Entrepreneur & Fraudster ' .
Víctor Marchesini ( 1930 - -1999 ) , born in Río Negro Province , was an Argentine lawyer and politician .
John Francklyn ( c. 1564 -- 1645 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1644 .
Max Abraham ( German : ( ˈaːbʀaham ) ; 26 March 1875 -- 16 November 1922 ) was a German physicist .
Nicolaes Woutersz van der Meer ( 1575 -- 1666 ) , was a Dutch brewer , magistrate and mayor of Haarlem , best known today for his portrait with its pendant of his wife Cornelia Claesdr Voogt , both painted by Frans Hals in 1631 .
Otis M. Smith ( 1922 - -1994 ) was the first African American justice on the Michigan Supreme Court and the General Counsel for General Motors .
Alfred Renard ( 21 April 1895 - 20 June 1988 ) was an eminent Belgian aviation pioneer .
Saint Gobain ( died 670 ) , also known as Goban , was an Irish Benedictine monk and spiritual student of Saint Fursey at Burgh Castle , Norfolk , England .
John Seymour , 4th Duke of Somerset ( before 1646 -- 29 April 1675 ) was an English peer and MP .
John Alexander Gresse ( 1741 - -1794 ) , was an English painter and drawing - master .
William West Neve ( 7 June 1852 -- 26 December 1942 ) was a minor English architect in the Arts and Crafts style .
Archibald Menzies ( /ˈmɪŋɪs/ MING - iss ; 15 March 1754 -- 15 February 1842 ) was a Scottish surgeon , botanist and naturalist .
Joseph Leeson , 2nd Earl of Milltown ( 1730 -- 27 November 1801 ) , styled Viscount Russborough between 1763 and 1783 , was an Irish peer .
Martin J. Levitt ( 14 October 1944 -- 21 November 2004 ) was a supervisory trainer , union buster and a union organizer on and off over a 20-year period before 1987 when he reportedly changed direction .
Hamazasp Srvandztyan ( Armenian : Համազասպ Սրվանձտյան ; 1873 -- 18 February 1921 ) , commonly known as Hamazasp , was an Armenian fedayee military commander and member of the Armenian Revolutionary Federation .
Colonel John Macleod of Colbecks ( died 1823 ) was a British soldier , during the Napoleonic Wars .
Darius Goff ( 10 May 1809 -- 14 April 1891 ) was one of the foremost textile manufacturers in the United States and a leading citizen of Pawtucket , Rhode Island .
Philipp Krementz ( 1 December 1819 -- 6 May 1899 ) was a German Catholic bishop , created Cardinal in 1893 .
Dr. Pritam Saini ( 1927 - -2003 ) was a Punjabi journalist , literary critic and history scholar .
Knut Strøm ( 25 January 1923 -- 10 September 2007 ) was a Norwegian resistance fighter and Lieutenant colonel in the Norwegian army .
Baselios Solomon was the Maphrian of the East of the Syriac Orthodox Church , from 1509 until his death in 1518 .
William Thomas Collings ( 4 September 1823 -- 7 March 1882 ) was a clergyman of the Church of England who served as Seigneur of Sark from 1853 to 1882 .
Wojciech Długoraj ( c. 1557 - after 1619 ) , also called Wiecesław Długoraj , Adalbert Długoraj and Gostinensis , was a Polish Renaissance composer and lutenist .
James Allen Harker FLS ( 31 July 1847 -- 19 December 1894 ) was an English entomologist , professor of natural history at the Royal Agricultural College in Cirencester , Gloucestershire from 1881 until his death .
William Baylor Hartland ( 1836 - -1912 ) was a plantsman from Ireland .
Bernard Joy ( 29 October 1911 -- 18 July 1984 ) was an English footballer and journalist .
Fridtjof Frank Gundersen ( 29 October 1934 -- 11 November 2011 ) was a Norwegian professor of jurisprudence and politician .
Eugen Ciucă ( Romanian : ( e.uˈd͡ʒen t͡ʃjukə ) ; 27 February 1913 -- 26 September 2005 ) was a contemporary Romanian - American artist known for his monumental sculptures , vivid paintings and drawings of delicate feminine figures .
Conall Laeg Breg mac Áedo Sláine ( died 612 ) was a King of Brega from the Síl nÁedo Sláine branch of the southern Ui Neill .
Emory McClintock ( 1840 - -1916 ) , born John Emory McClintock was an American actuary , born in Carlisle , Pennsylvania .
Lysander ( /laɪˈsændər/ or /ˈlaɪˌsændər/ ; died 395 BCE , Greek : Λύσανδρος , Lýsandros ) was a Spartan admiral who commanded the Spartan fleet in the Hellespont which defeated the Athenians at Aegospotami in 405 BCE .
William Freeman ( c. 1558 - -13 August 1595 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest during the Reformation .
Sir Henry Unton ( or Umpton ) ( c. 1557 -- 23 March 1596 ) was an Elizabethan English diplomat .
Walter Valdi ( stage name of Walter Pinnetti ; 20 August 1930 -- 13 October 2003 ) was an Italian singer , songwriter , author and actor of several songs and theatrical pieces in Milanese Dialect .
Brita Sophia De la Gardie ( 1713 - -1797 ) was a Swedish noble and amateur actress .
Estelle May Hurll ( 1863 - -1924 ) , a student of aesthetics , wrote a series of popular aesthetic analyses of art in the early twentieth century .
Quentin Lawrence ( 1920 in Gravesend -- 1979 in Halifax , Yorkshire ) was an English film and television director .
Jacob Yoder , pioneer , born in Reading , Pennsylvania , 11 August 1758 : died in Spencer County , Kentucky , 7 April 1832 .
Gad Tedeschi ( Hebrew : גד טדסקי ; Italian : Guido Uberto Tedeschi ) ( born 1907 ; died 1992 ) was an Israeli jurist .
Cattamanchi Ramalinga Reddy OM ( 10 December 1880 -- 24 February 1951 ) , also popularly known as Sir C. R. Reddy , was an educationist and political thinker , essayist and economist , poet and literary critic .
Ferdinand Canu ( 1863 - 1932 ) was a French paleontologist and author .
Sabita Devi ( 1914 - -1965 ) was a Hindi film actress in Indian cinema .
P.Bhaskaranunni ( 17 Dec 1926 -- 8 April 1994 ) was a historian and Malayalam literary critic .
Walter Belasco ( 1864 , Vancouver , Canada -- 21 June 1939 , San Francisco , California ) was a Canadian silent film actor .
Chet Gardner , Born `` Chester Leroy Gardner '' ( 16 March 1898 in Grant City , Missouri -- 3 September 1938 in Flemington , New Jersey ) was an American racecar driver , named by promoters as `` The Grand Old Man of Auto Racing . ''
John Krushenick ( March 18 , 1927 -- June 19 , 1998 ) painter and co - founder of the Brata Gallery in New York City .
David Caro ( ca . 1782 , Fordon , Grand Duchy of Posen--25 December 1839 , Posen ) was a Prussian pedagogue .
Leonard Steinberg , Baron Steinberg ( 1 August 1936 -- 2 November 2009 ) was a British life peer and multi - millionaire businessman .
Main Poc died in 1816 , furthering the trend to leaders who were comfortable in both the Potawatomi villages and the American trading companies .
Upendra Kumar ( 1941 -- 24 January 2002 ) ( Kannada : ಉಪೇಂದ್ರ ಕುಮಾರ್ ) was an Indian music director who predominantly worked in Kannada and Oriya films .
Nicholas Sturgeon ( ca.1380s - 1454 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1442 to 1454 , a composer and a compiler of the Old Hall Manuscript .
Jean - Baptiste Baudry ( bapt 3 July 1684 -- 20 November 1755 ) was born at Trois - Rivières and was the son of Guillaume Baudry , a gunsmith and goldsmith .
Simon Deignan ( 1922 -- November 2006 ) was a former Gaelic football player for Cavan , and a referee .
Peregrine Branwhite ( 1745 - 1795 ? ) , was an English poet .
Cosmo Grant Niven Edwards ( c. 1896 - 22 July 1964 ) was a soldier and British civil servant of the Indian political service who served as resident for the Madras States .
Dionys van Dongen ( 1748 Dordrecht--1819 Rotterdam ) was a Dutch painter .
Nicholas Comper ( 29 April 1897 -- 17 June 1939 ) was an English aviator and aircraft designer , whose most notable success was the 1930s Comper Swift monoplane racer .
Johann Carl Friedrich Dauthe ( 26 September 1746 -- 13 July 1816 ) was a German architect and etcher who specialised in the Neo - Classical style .
Lope Íñiguez ( c. 1050 -- 1093 ) succeeded his father Íñigo López to become the second Lord of Biscay in 1076 .
Heinrich August Hahn ( 19 June 1821 , Königsberg - 1 December 1861 ) was a German theologian and the eldest son of the theologian August Hahn .
Edward Heneage , 1st Baron Heneage PC , JP , DL ( 29 March 1840 -- 10 August 1922 ) was a British Liberal and Liberal Unionist politician .
Jeremy Hindley ( 1 January 1944 -- 7 January 2013 ) was an English horse trainer who trained around 700 winners in a 17-year career .
Thomas Fletcher Oakes ( July 15 , 1843 in Boston -- 1919 in Seattle ) was president of Northern Pacific Railway from 1888 to 1893 .
Frits Goodings ( 10 October 1963 - 7 June 1989 , Paramaribo ) was a Dutch - Surinamese footballer .
Jack Dolan ( 14 June 1906 -- 5 March 2001 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir William Reginald Halliday ( 26 September 1886 -- 25 November 1966 ) was a historian and archaeologist who served as Principal of King 's College London from 1928 to 1952 .
Christian Henrik Nicolai Mejdell ( 21 April 1822 -- 1899 ) was a Norwegian mining engineer .
Endel Laas ( 29 August 1915 in Tartu -- 1 November 2009 ) was an Estonian forest scientist and professor .
Sir John Watson Gibson OBE ( 1885 - -1947 ) was an English civil engineer , key in developing the water supply infrastructure in the former British Empire , and instrumental in the design of Mulberry Harbour used in the Normandy landings .
John Orlando Parry ( 3 January 1810 -- 20 February 1879 ) was an English actor , pianist , artist , comedian and singer .
John Monson ( c.1628 -- 14 October 1674 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1660 and 1674 .
Christer Zetterberg ( 2 November 1941 -- 5 April 2012 ) was a Swedish businessman and Chairman of investment bank Carnegie .
Dudley Ryder , 6th Earl of Harrowby ( 11 October 1892 -- 7 May 1987 ) , known as Viscount Sandon from 1900 to 1956 , was a British peer and Conservative Member of Parliament .
Flight Lieutenant Wallace McIntosh DFC and Bar , DFM ( 27 March 1920 -- 4 June 2007 ) flew 55 bombing missions with the RAF during the Second World War as an air gunner in Lancaster bombers .
Thomas McAfee ( November 28 , 1866 -- May 1947 ) was an Irish - born Presbyterian minister and political figure in Saskatchewan .
The Reverend Thomas Seaton ( baptised 2 October 1684 , Stamford , Lincolnshire , died 18 August 1741 at Ravenstone , Buckinghamshire ) , was a Church of England clergyman and religious writer .
Luelen Bernart ( Pohnpei 1866 - 1946 ) was the first Micronesian to write a book and Pohnpei 's first historian .
Yogini Joglekar ( 6 Aug 1925 -- 1 Nov 2005 ) was a famous Marathi writer , poet and also a renowned classical singer .
Giovanni Aurelio Augurello ( Joannes Aurelius Augurellus ) ( 1441 - -1524 ) was an Italian humanist scholar , poet and alchemist .
Meir Eisenstaedter ( Meir ben Judah Leib Eisenstädter , 1780 - 1852 ) was a nineteenth - century rabbi , Talmudist , and paytan ( liturgic poet ) .
Jan Wellens de Cock ( c. 1480 -- 1527 ) was a Flemish painter and draftsman of the Northern Renaissance .
Victoire Jean - Baptiste ( 1861 - -1923 ) , known as `` La Belle Victoire '' , was a Haitian politician de facto , mistress to president Florvil Hyppolite and highly influential during his reign .
Alice Cordelia Morse ( June 1 , 1863 - -July 15 , 1961 ) was a designer of book covers .
Helge Ellingsen Waagaard ( 27 January 1781 -- 25 March 1817 ) was a Norwegian farmer and non - commissioned military officer .
John James Wright ( 20 February 1821 -- 22 October 1904 ) was an Australian flour miller , local government councillor , local government head , Member of Lower House , Orangeman and store / shopkeeper .
Abram Hill , also known as Ab Hill , ( 20 January 1910 -- 13 October 1986 ) was an American playwright ; author of On Strivers Row , Walk Hard , Talk Loud and several other plays ; and a principal figure in the development of black theatre from Atlanta , Georgia .
Roger Niger ( died 1241 ) was a thirteenth - century cleric who became Bishop of London .
George Cranstoun , Lord Corehouse ( died 1850 ) was a Scottish advocate , judge and satirist .
William I Sanudo ( or Guglielmo ; died ca . 1323 ) was the fourth Duke of the Archipelago from 1303 to his death .
Otto Furrer ( 19 October 1903 -- 26 July 1951 ) was a Swiss alpine skier and cross - country skier and world champion .
Ann Griffiths ( née Thomas ) ( April 1776 -- August 1805 ) was a Welsh poet and writer of Methodist Christian hymns .
Arne Meidell ( 17 November 1894 -- 8 August 1963 ) was a Norwegian jurist and businessperson .
Juan Coronel ( born 1569 , in Spain ; died 1651 , at Mérida , Mexico ) was a Spanish Franciscan missionary .
Ralph Amner ( died 1664 ) , a relation of John Amner , was admitted a lay clerk of Ely Cathedral in 1604 , and retained the post until 1609 , when he was succeeded by Michael Este .
Colin Mackenzie , 1st Earl of Seaforth ( 1596/7 - 1633 ) , was a Highland clan chief and Scottish nobleman , possessed of vast estates and wealth .
Vladimir Košak ( 25 July 1908 -- 18 June 1947 ) was a Croatian economist , lawyer , politician and diplomat .
Johannes Rosinus ( Johann Roszfeld ) ( c. 1550 -- 1626 ) was the German author of a work on Roman antiquities called Antiquitatum romanarum corpus absolutissimum , which first appeared at Basel in 1585 .
Mario Esposito ( 7 September 1887 -- 19 February 1975 ) was an Irish and Italian scholar who specialised in Hiberno - Latin studies .
Albert Whiggs Easmon ( 1865 -- 21 May 1923 ) was a Sierra Leonean doctor and the half - brother of Dr John Farrell Easmon .
Louis Antoine François Baillon ( 20 January 1778 -- 3 December 1855 ) was a French naturalist and collector .
Dionicio Rodriguez ( 1891 - -1955 ) was a Mexican - born artist and architect whose work can be seen in Alabama , Arkansas , Illinois , Maryland , Michigan , New Mexico , Tennessee , and Texas , as well as Washington , D.C. and Mexico City .
Albert I of Käfernburg ( German : Albrecht I. von Käfernburg ) ( died 15 October 1232 ) was the eighteenth Archbishop of Magdeburg .
Christian Thams ( 9 September 1867 -- 22 May 1948 ) was a Norwegian architect , industrialist , businessman and diplomat .
Piero della Francesca ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈpjɛːro della franˈtʃeska ) listen ; c. 1415 -- 12 October 1492 ) was an Italian painter of the Early Renaissance .
Joseph Relph ( 3 December 1712 -- 26 June 1743 ) was a Cumberland poet ( his first name is given as Josiah in later editions of the Dictionary of National Biography ) .
Albert Ballard ( 2 August 1888 -- 7 January 1969 ) was a leading figure in the British Co - operative Party .
Giacomo Franceschini ( 1672 - -1745 ) ( also called Jacopo Franceschini ) was an Italian painter .
Lieutenant - Colonel Allister Miller DSO OBE ( 1892 - -1951 ) was a South African aviation pioneer , who contributed significantly to both military and civil aviation in his country during the first half of the 20th century .
Vincenzo Fabrizi ( 1764 -- c. 1812 ) was an Italian composer of opera buffa .
Nicol Galanderian ( Armenian : Նիկոլ Գասպարի Գալանդերյան ( also Nikol ) , September 7 , 1881 - March 2 , 1944 ) was a noted composer of Armenian music and is especially known for vocal , choral and children 's works whose primary source of inspiration is folk music and urban folksong .
Alexander Livingstone , 1st Earl of Linlithgow ( died 1621 ) was a Scottish nobleman , courtier , and politician .
Isaac Preston Cory ( 1802 - -1842 ) was an antiquarian who compiled ancient fragments and published them in a compendium called Cory 's Ancient Fragments ( 1826 , revised 1832 ) .
René Zavaleta Mercado born in Oruro ( 1935 ) , died in Mexico City ( 1984 ) , was a Bolivian politician , sociologist and philosopher .
Granny Alina ( died 1969 ) was the foster grandmother of Gabriel Louis Duval , who claimed in his 2004 book A Princess in the Family that she might have been Grand Duchess Anastasia Nikolaevna of Russia .
Jacques Le Bossu ( Paris , 1546 -- Rome , 1626 ) was a French Benedictine theologian and Doctor of the Sorbonne .
John Loudon McAdam ( born John Lowdon McAdam , 23 September 1756 -- 26 November 1836 ) was a Scottish engineer and road - builder .
John Ross Woodring ( J. Ross Woodring ) ( 1882 - -1946 ) , a newspaperman , was born in Macy , Indiana , on December 23 , 1882 .
Giovanni Domenico Campiglia ( 1692 - -1768 ) was an Italian painter and engraver from Florence , active under the patronage of the House of Medici .
Ran Zhi ( Chinese : 冉智 ; died c. 354 ) was the crown prince of the short - lived Chinese state Ran Wei .
Caleb Wild Hammill ( 1863 - 1921 ) was one of the founders of the stockbrokerage and banking investment firm of Shearson , Hammill & Co. , founded in 1902 by Mr. Hammill & Edward Shearson .
Tom Caldwell ( 30 June 1921 -- November 2002 ) was a politician , art dealer and interior designer in Northern Ireland .
Dr Lo Wing - lok , JP ( Chinese : 勞永樂 ; 13 September 1954 -- 9 May 2015 ) was a Hong Kong doctor and politician .
Aristide Leonori ( 28 July 1856 -- 30 July 1928 ) was an Italian architect and engineer .
Theophilus Redwood ( 9 April 1806 -- 5 March 1892 ) was a Welsh pharmacist who was one of the founding members of the Royal Pharmaceutical Society of Great Britain .
Wang Kunlun ( 1902 - -1985 ) , birth name Wang Ruyu , was a Chinese politician who held high - profile positions , at different times , in both the Nationalist and Communist parties .
Juan Bravo Murillo ( 24 June 1803 -- 11 February 1873 ) was a Spanish politician , jurist and economist .
Frederick T. Melges ( 2 December 1935 -- 29 July 1988 ) was an American Psychiatrist and Professor of Psychiatry at Stanford University School of Medicine , notable for his interest in time and for his pioneering work on the role of distortions of time in various psychiatric disorders .
Stafford Somerfield ( 9 January 1911 - -14 January 1995 ) was a British newspaper editor .
Arnold Beitzel ( 27 May 1897 -- 6 November 1982 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
General Sir Thomas Monteath Douglas KCB ADC ( 1787 -- October 1868 ) was an officer of the Bengal Army of the East India Company .
Yves Ramette ( 6 February 1921 -- 2 June 2012 ) was a French post - romantic composer and organist .
Sir Thomas Harte Franks ( 1808 - -1862 ) , was a British Army general who fought in the Second Anglo - Sikh War .
Heinrich Wangnereck ( July 1595 - 11 November 1664 ) was a Catholic theologian , preacher , author .
Hon . Joseph Docker ( 1802 -- 9 December 1884 ) , was an Australian politician , member of the New South Wales Legislative Council .
Sir Charles Lucas ( 1613 -- 28 August 1648 ) was an English soldier , a Royalist commander in the English Civil War .
Sir Samuel Romilly ( 1 March 1757 -- 2 November 1818 ) , was a British legal reformer .
Peter John Anderson , LLB , MA , FSA , JP , ( 1853 -- 12 May 1926 ) was the Librarian of the University of Aberdeen since 1894 and a noted philatelist who signed the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1921 .
Charles - François d'Iberville , marquis de La Bonde ( 1653 - 1723 ) was a French aristocrat and diplomat .
Ismail Ahmed Cachalia ( 1908 - 2003 ) , popularly known as Moulvi , was a South African political activist and a leader of Transvaal Indian Congress and the African National Congress .
Donald Malcolm ( 1930 -- 2013 ) was a Scottish author of science fiction and fact who was active as a writer from the mid-1950s until the mid-1970s .
Ross Baillie ( 26 September 1977 -- 18 June 1999 ) was a Scottish track and field athlete , older brother of Commonwealth Silver medal winner Chris Baillie .
Guillermo Deisler ( 15 June 1940 - -21 October 1995 ) was a stage designer , visual poet and mail artist .
William Farren ( 13 May 1786 -- 24 September 1861 ) , English actor , was born the son of an actor ( born 1725 ) of the same name , who played leading roles from 1784 to 1795 at Theatre Royal , Covent Garden .
Li Zitong ( died AD 622 ) was an agrarian leader who claimed the title of emperor in the aftermaths of the death of Emperor Yang of Sui at the hands of the general Yuwen Huaji in 618 .
Prince Dimitri Alexandrovich Obolensky ( 19 March ( old style ) 1882 -- 27 April 1964 ) was a Russian nobleman , landowner and marshal of the nobility who after the October Revolution and the Russian Civil War became a night watchman and a taxi driver in Paris .
József Madarász de Kisfalud ( 27 August 1814 -- 31 January 1915 ) was a Hungarian lawyer and politician , who served as Speaker of the House of Representatives between 1898 and 1899 .
Heinrich Gustav Mühlenbeck , name also given as Henri Gustave Muehlenbeck ( 2 June 1798 , Sainte - Marie - aux - Mines -- 21 November 1845 , Mulhouse ) was an Alsatian physician and botanical collector known for his work with bryophytes .
George Alfred Barnard ( 23 September 1915 -- 9 August 2002 ) was a British statistician known particularly for his work on the foundations of statistics and on quality control .
Mary Latter ( 1725 -- 28 March 1777 ) was an English poet , essayist and playwright of the 18th century .
Dong Biwu ( 5 March 1886 -- 2 April 1975 ) was a Chinese communist political leader during the regime of Mao Zedong .
Peter Zirschky died by accident around 2004 .
Arild Haga ( 8 April 1913 -- 22 February 1985 ) was a Norwegian revue writer .
Johann Georg Zobel von Giebelstadt ( 1543 - -1580 ) was the Prince - Bishop of Bamberg from 1577 to 1580 .
Lieutenant - Colonel Lord Edward Cavendish ( 28 January 1838 -- 18 May 1891 ) was a 19th - century British politician .
Sir Henry Howarth Bashford FRCP ( 13 January 1880 -- 15 August 1961 ) was a distinguished English physician , becoming Honorary Physician to King George VI .
Pierre - Émile Gounelle ( Paris , 9 June 1850 -- 2 October 1914 , Paris ) was a French entomologist and naturalist .
George Joseph Smith ( 11 January 1872 -- 13 August 1915 ) was an English serial killer and bigamist .
Kimweri Mputa Magogo ( 1914 - 20 September 2000 ) was a traditional leader of the Shambaa people of the Usambara Mountains in Tanzania .
Gustav Weindorfer ( 23 February 1874 -- 5 May 1932 ) was an Austrian - born Australian amateur botanist , lodge - keeper and promoter of the Cradle Mountains National Park .
Sebastianus ( died 413 ) , a brother of Jovinus , was an aristocrat of southern Gaul .
Ts'ao Yung - ho ( Chinese : 曹永和 ; pinyin : Cáo Yǒnghé ; Wade -- Giles : Ts'ao2 Yung3-ho2 ; 1920 -- 12 September 2014 ) was a Taiwanese historian known for his work on the early history of Taiwan .
Lloyd Reckord ( 26 May 1929 -- 8 July 2015 ) was a Jamaican actor , film maker , and stage director who lived in England for some years .
The shooting of Denzel Dowell , an African - American resident of North Richmond , California , occurred on April 1 , 1967 .
Gerard van Honthorst ( Gerrit van Honthorst ) ( 4 November 1592 -- 27 April 1656 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Muhammad Afzaal Ahmad Hussain Gilani ( Urdu : سیّد محمد افضال احمد حسين گیلانی ) ( also known as Sakhiy - e - Kamil , Mahboob - e - Khaas ) ( 1926 - -1998 CE ) was a Pakistani Sufi mystic .
Nicholas Upton ( 1400?--1457 ) , was an English cleric , precentor of Salisbury , and writer on heraldry and the art of war .
Sir John Furley , CH ( 19 March 1836 in Ashford , Kent -- 27 September 1919 in Oxford ) was an English humanitarian who worked to improve medical care both in wartime and at home .
Sir Thomas Robinson , 1st Baronet ( 1703 - -1777 ) was an English politician , architect and collector .
Dragutin Brahm ( 26 August 1909 , Zagreb -- 27 June 1938 , Starigrad ) was a Croatian mountain climber .
Marcel Lehoux ( 3 April 1888 -- 19 July 1936 ) was a French racing driver and businessman .
Ross Hill ( died 29 September 2007 ) was an English BMX cyclist who won British and European titles .
Joshua Allen , 2nd Viscount Allen LLD ( 17 September 1685 -- 5 December 1742 ) was an Irish peer and politician .
Edward J. Kuntze ( b. in Pomerania , Prussia , in 1826 ; d. in New York City , 10 April 1870 ) was a sculptor .
On March 19 , 1988 , John Otis Brew died from congestive heart failure in Cambridge , Massachusetts .
Adolphe Emile Marval ( ca.1845 -- 11 July 1935 ) was a French - born educator and art dealer in Adelaide , South Australia .
Al - Mansur al - Hasan ( 1199 - -1271 ) was an imam of the Zaidi state of Yemen who ruled in 1262 - 1271 .
Dominique Roquebert ( Bayonne 1744-Battle of Tamatave 1811 ) was a French navy officer .
William Ross , 14th Lord Ross of Halkhead ( c.1720 - 19 August 1754 ) , was a Scottish nobleman .
Lu Su ( 172 - -217 ) , courtesy name Zijing , was a politician , diplomat and military general serving under the warlord Sun Quan in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Battista Guarino ( Latin : Baptista Guarinus ; 1434 - -1513 ) was the youngest son of Guarino da Verona .
Friedrich Diedrich ( 5 October 1935 -- 7 October 2015 ) was a German Roman Catholic theologian and Old Testament scholar .
Gabriel Fragnière ( 4 March 1934 -- 9 September 2015 ) was a Swiss university professor , philosopher and scientific researcher .
Charles Arthur Curran ( 1913 - -1978 ) was a Jesuit priest and psychologist who is best known as the creator of Community Language Learning ( CLL ) , a method in education and specifically in Second Language Teaching .
Dhanraj Bhagat ( 1917 - 1988 ) was an Indian sculptor , considered by many as one of the major sculptors of the Indian subcontinent .
Frank Oates ( 1840 - -1875 ) was a British naturalist , explorer and uncle to Antarctic explorer Lawrence Oates .
Nakagawa Kenzō ( Japanese : 中川健藏 ) ( July 16 , 1875 -- June 26 , 1944 ) was a Japanese bureaucrat and political figure .
Saint Ælfgifu of Shaftesbury , also known as Saint Elgiva ( died 944 ) was the first wife of Edmund I ( r. 939 - -946 ) , by whom she bore two future kings , Eadwig ( r. 955 - -959 ) and Edgar ( r. 959 - -975 ) .
Zoran Prljinčević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Зоран Прљинчевић ; 27 January 1932 -- 13 June 2013 ) was a former Serbian footballer and football coach .
Alan Maxwell Boisragon ( 1860 - 1922 ) was a British army officer , and author , and was Captain Superintendent of the Shanghai Municipal Police from 1901 - 1906 .
Michael Christiansen ( 1926 or 1927 -- 15 June 1984 ) was a British newspaper editor .
Pasquale del Pezzo , Duke of Caianello and Marquis of Campodisola ( 2 May 1859 -- 20 June 1936 ) , was a Neapolitan mathematician .
William Logsdail ( 25 May 1859 -- 3 September 1944 ) was a prolific English landscape , portrait , and genre painter .
John Gerard Anderson ( 1836 - -1911 ) , M.A. , J.P. , was a Scottish - born educationalist and public servant in colonial Queensland .
James Lysaght Finegan or Finigan ( died 8 September 1900 ) was an Irish barrister , soldier , merchant and politician .
Roberto Curcio ( 3 August 1912 -- 1993 ) was an Italian modern pentathlete .
Hal Braham ( 1911 - 1994 ) was an American writer primarily known for his work in crime fiction and western fiction .
Diepold III , Margrave of Vohburg ( c. 1079 -- 1146 ) , also known as Diepold von Vohburg and Diepold III von Giengen , was a Bavarian noble in the 12th century .
Melito of Sardis ( Greek : Μελίτων Σάρδεων Melíton Sárdeon ) ( died c. 180 ) was the bishop of Sardis near Smyrna in western Anatolia , and a great authority in early Christianity .
Hedwig von Restorff ( December 14 , 1906 , Berlin -- 1962 ) is best known for her discovery of the von Restorff effect or isolation effect .
Günther Strupp ( March 6 , 1912 -- 1996 ) was a German artist , illustrator , and art director .
Rakesh Deewana ( c. 1969 -- 27 April 2014 ) was an Indian character actor from Hathras , Uttar Pradesh .
Dafydd Llywelyn ( 10 January 1939 in South Wales -- 25 March 2013 in München ) was a Welsh composer , pianist , conductor and teacher .
Robert Millhouse ( 1788 - -1839 ) was an English Spenserian poet , born in Nottingham , England .
Gabrielle Duchêne ( 26 February 1870 -- 3 August 1954 ) was a French feminist and pacifist who was active in the French section of the Women 's International League for Peace and Freedom ( WILPF ) .
Andrianampoinimerina ( Malagasy pronunciation : ( anˈɖʐianˌmpuʲnˈmerʲnə̥ ) ) ( 1745 - -1810 ) ruled the Kingdom of Imerina from 1787 until his death .
Roulland Le Roux ( fl . 1508 - 1527 ) was a French gothic architect responsible for the Flamboyant west facade and the Tour De Beurre of Rouen Cathedral , and the Bureau Des Finances in Rouen .
Perry Bullard ( full name , Winston Perry Bullard ) , ( 1942 - -1998 ) , was a Democratic politician and lawyer in Ann Arbor , Michigan .
Ida Bagus Made Poleng ( 1915 - -1999 ) was a traditional Balinese painter .
Ali Fethi Okyar ( 29 April 1880 -- 7 May 1943 ) was a Turkish diplomat and politician who also served as a military officer and diplomat during the last decade of the Ottoman Empire .
Benjamin Carrington FRSE FLS MRCS ( 1827 -- 1893 ) was a leading British botanist and taxonomist in the late 19th century .
John Goodyer ( 1592 - -1664 ) was a 17th - century botanist who lived in Hampshire , England .
Gheorghe Adamescu ( July 23 , 1869 - -March 4 , 1942 ) was a Romanian literary historian and bibliographer .
Franz Hoppenstätt ( died 1657 or 1658 ) was a German - Estonian wood carver .
Nero Hawley ( 1742 - -1817 ) , born into slavery in North Stratford , now Trumbull , Connecticut , enlisted in place of his owner , Daniel Hawley , in the Continental Army on April 20 , 1777 during the American Revolution and earned his freedom .
Hugo Griebert ( 1867 - 1924 ) was a stamp dealer and philatelist who was a specialist in the stamps of Spain and who was entered on the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1921 .
Qiao Rui ( died 197 ) was an official serving under the warlord Yuan Shu during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Cathal Carragh Ua Conchobair was King of Connacht from 1189 to 1202 .
Elizabeth Malleson ( née Whitehead ; 1828 - 1916 ) was an English educationalist , suffragist and activist for women 's education and rural nursing .
Bernie Elsey Snr ( 1906 -- 25 August 1986 ) was a property developer and entrepreneur , associated with early developments on the Gold Coast , Queensland , Australia .
Vera von Schalburg ( 23 November 1907 - 1993 ) was a Soviet , German and British agent and sister of Christian Frederik von Schalburg .
Ambrose Serle ( 1742 - -1812 ) was an English official , diarist and writer of Christian prose and hymns .
Herbert William Garratt ( 8 June 1864 -- 25 September 1913 ) was an English mechanical engineer and the inventor of the Garratt system of articulated locomotives .
George Samuel Fereday Smith ( 7 May 1812 -- 26 May 1891 ) was an English industrialist and canal manager who from 1837 to 1887 was the Deputy Superintendent of the Bridgewater Trustees and their successors , whose major source of income came from the Bridgewater Canal .
Benjamin Frater ( 1979 - -2007 ) , also known as `` The Catholic Yak '' , was an Australian poet .
Thaddeus Lynch ( 1901 -- 25 October 1966 ) was an Irish Fine Gael politician and auctioneer .
William Lindsay , 18th Earl of Crawford and 2nd Earl of Lindsay ( died 1698 ) was a Scottish noble and politician .
Virgil Jordan ( 1892 - -1965 ) was an economist and author .
Dr. Richard Orton ( 1940 - -2013 ) was a composer , performer and music educator .
Diane Cilento ( 5 October 1933 -- 6 October 2011 ) was an Australian theatre and film actress and author .
Barbara Aleksi - Meskhishvili ( 1 February 1898 , Tbilisi -- 25 December 1972 , ibid ) was a Georgian stage actress .
Ajay Kumar Singh was an Indian Police Service officer who was killed on 4 October 2000 by suspected Maoists .
Hugh Bellot ( 1542 - -1596 ) was bishop of Bangor and then bishop of Chester .
Heinz Ebert ( Saxony , Germany , October 13 , 1907 , -- 1983 , Rio Claro , São Paulo ) was a German - Brazilian geologist , naturalist , and educator .
Yoo Byung - eun ( Hangul : 유병언 ; hanja : 兪炳彦 ; RR : Yu Byeong - eon ; 11 February 1941 -- 2014 ) was a South Korean religious leader , businessman , and inventor , who as a photographer was known under the art name Ahae .
Jindřich Polák ( 5 May 1925 -- 22 August 2003 ) was a Czech film and television director .
Eliseo Reyes Rodríguez ( 1940 - -1967 ) was a Cuban guerrillero .
Joseph Nutting ( 1660 - -1722 ) was an English engraver , working in London .
George Earle Buckle ( 10 June 1854 -- 13 March 1935 ) was an English editor and biographer .
Arthur Lovekin ( 12 November 1859 -- 10 December 1931 ) was a West Australian journalist , newspaper editor and owner , and politician .
Sebastian D'Souza ( 1906 - -1996 ) was a successful Goan music arranger in the Bollywood music industry , considered to be the master of fusing Indian classical music with European classical music concepts of harmony , cadence and obbligato .
Corneliu Moldovanu ( pen name of Corneliu Vasiliu ; 15 August 1883 -- 2 September 1952 ) was a Romanian poet , prose writer and playwright .
Oruç Reis ( Turkish : Oruç Reis ; Arabic : عروج بربروس‎ ; Spanish : Arrudye ; c. 1474 - -1518 ) was an Ottoman bey ( governor ) of Algiers and beylerbey ( chief governor ) of the West Mediterranean , and the elder brother of Hayreddin Barbarossa .
Horia Creangă ( 20 July 1892 -- 1 August 1943 ) was a Romanian architect important in the modernist movement .
Saint Pambo ( also known as Pemwah and Bemwah ) ( d. ca . 375 ) is an Egyptian Desert Father of the fourth century .
Saint Credan of Evesham ( died 19 August 780 ) is a saint in the calendar of the Roman Catholic Church and of the Orthodox Church .
Rowland Berkeley ( about 1548 - 11 June 1611 ) of Worcester and Spetchley was an English clothier and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1593 and 1611 .
Assadollah Mobashery ( 1909 - -1990 ) was Persian judge , politician , journalist , poet and translator of Goethe , Corbin and Jaspers from French into Persian .
Hemalatha Lavanam ( 26 February 1932 --19 March 2008 ) was an Indian social reformer , writer , and atheist who protested against untouchability and the caste system .
Henry Pratt Fairchild ( 1880 - -1956 ) was a distinguished American sociologist .
Neeta Sen ( 1935 -- 1 April 2006 ) was an Indian classical singer and music composer .
Matteo di Giovanni ( c. 1430 -- 1495 ) was an Italian Renaissance artist from the Sienese School .
Margaret Elizabeth Sangster ( February 22 , 1838 -- 1912 ) was an American poet , author , and editor .
Charles Vereker , 2nd Viscount Gort PC ( Ire ) ( 1768 -- 11 November 1842 ) , known as Charles Vereker until 1817 , was a British soldier and politician .
John Butler , 2nd Marquess of Ormonde , KP ( 24 August 1808 -- 25 September 1854 ) was an Irish politician and peer .
Edward Lowth Badeley ( 1803/1804 -- 29 March 1868 ) was an English ecclesiastical lawyer , a member of the Oxford Movement , who was involved in some of the most notorious cases of the 19th century
Wim Steijn ( 28 January 1914 , Assendelft -- 23 August 1980 , Bentveld ) , was a Dutch painter .
Jules Meese ( 3 September 1896 -- 1 December 1968 ) was a French lightweight weightlifter .
Gift Tandare ( died 2007 ) was a member of the Zimbabwe political party Movement for Democratic Change .
Juan de Bermúdez ( /bɜrˈmjuːdɛz/ ; Spanish pronunciation : ( berˈmuðeθ ) ; d. 1570 ) was a Spanish navigator of the 16th century .
Henryk Sławik ( 16 July 1894 -- 23 August 1944 ) was a Polish politician in the interwar period , social worker , activist , and diplomat , who during World War II helped save over 30,000 Polish refugees , including 5,000 Polish Jews in Budapest , Hungary by giving them false Polish passports with Catholic designation .
Karl Samuel Leberecht Hermann ( 20 January 1765 -- 1 September 1846 ) was a German chemist who independently discovered cadmium in 1817 .
Kristian Gerhard Jebsen ( 27 May 1927 -- 19 February 2004 ) was a Norwegian ship - owner .
Constantine Phipps , 1st Baron Mulgrave ( 22 August 1722 ( baptised ) -- 13 September 1775 ) was an Irish peer .
Bertram Luard - Selby ( 12 February 1853 -- 26 December 1918 ) was an English composer and cathedral organist .
Olimpia Aldobrandini ( 20 April 1623 -- 18 December 1681 ) was a member of the Aldobrandini family of Rome , and the sole heiress to the family fortune .
Joseph Wilcocks ( 19 December 1673 -- 28 February 1756 ) was an English churchman , bishop of Gloucester , and bishop of Rochester and dean of Westminster .
Ayin Hillel ( Hebrew : ע . הלל‎ ) was the pen name of Hillel Omer ( 4 August 1926 - 30 June 1990 , Hebrew : הלל עומר‎ ) , an Israeli poet and children 's author .
Gerbrand van den Eeckhout ( 19 August 1621 -- 29 September 1674 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter and a favourite student of Rembrandt .
Sarah Bradlee Fulton ( December 14 , 1740 , Dorchester - 1835 , Medford ) was an active participant of the Revolutionary War on the American side .
Joe Tasker ( 12 May 1948 -- 17 May 1982 ) was one of the most talented British climbers during the late 1970s and early 1980s .
Though some of his followers believed he was immortal , Haidakhan Babaji died on 14 February 1984 , of what appeared to be a heart failure .
Slavko Pavletić ( 1917 -- 1945 ) was a Croatian football midfielder who tenured within Croatia during his spanned career .
James Myles Hogge ( 19 April 1873 - 27 October 1928 ) was a British social researcher and Liberal politician .
Roy Cazaly ( 13 January 1893 -- 10 October 1963 ) was an Australian rules football player famous for his high marks and ruck work , which gave rise to the phrase `` Up There Cazaly '' .
Otakar Hromádko ( 30 August 1909 in Kněž , district Čáslav , Czechoslovakia -- 14 April 1983 in Yverdon - les - Bains , Switzerland ) was a Czechoslovak journalist and army officer .
Makina Kameya ( died February 1988 ) was an Angola - born Zimbabwean sculptor .
Ma Xianda ( 1932 -- 17 June 2013 ) was a Chinese martial artist .
Sokollu Mehmed Pasha ( Ottoman Turkish : سوکلو محمد پاشا‎ ; Serbo - Croatian : Mehmed - paša Sokolović , Cyrillic : Мехмед-паша Соколовић , pronounced ( měxmet pâʃa sokǒːloʋit͡ɕ ) ; 1506 -- 11 October 1579 ) was an Ottoman statesman .
George Bowdler Buckton ( 24 May 1818 , London - 25 September 1905 , Haslemere , Surrey ) was an English entomologist who specialised in aphids .
Wilhelm Heinrich Waagen ( 23 June 1841 -- 24 March 1900 ) was a geologist and paleontologist .
Charles H. Ruth ( 1889 - -1949 ) was considered the founding father of the Army Map Service .
Brigadier General John Patrick McGlinn CMG , CBE ( 11 April 1869 -- 7 July 1946 ) was a senior officer of the Australian Army who served in World War I.
August Albo ( 11 September 1893 Suurupi , Harju County -- 13 December 1963 New York City , USA ) was an Estonian artist who studied at the Russian Royal Academy of Art but lived most of his life in New York City .
Charmian Clift ( 30 August 1923 -- 8 July 1969 ) was an Australian writer and essayist during the mid 20th century .
Berta Bojetu , also Berta Bojetu Boeta , ( 7 February 1946 -- 16 March 1997 ) was a Slovene writer , poet and actress .
Earth No More is an upcoming first - person shooter video game produced by Radar Group ( formerly by 3D Realms ) .
Virtual Pool 3 , often referred to as VP3 , is a 3D , first - person sports simulation video game , developed and released for the PC and PlayStation by Celeris .
Wizball is a computer game written by Jon Hare and Chris Yates ( who together formed the company Sensible Software ) and released in 1987 originally for the Commodore 64 and later in the year for the ZX Spectrum and Amstrad CPC .
Laser Squad Nemesis ( LSN ) is a 2002 multiplayer turn - based tactics video game developed by Codo Technologies for the PC .
Opera Mini requests web pages through Opera Software 's servers , which process and compress them before sending them to the mobile phone , speeding up transfer by two to three times and dramatically reducing the amount of data transferred , chargeable on many mobile phone data plans .
Hot Wheels Velocity X ( also known as Hot Wheels Velocity X : Maximum Justice in the PlayStation 2 version ) is a racing video game released in 2002 by Beyond Games .
The Darkness II is a first - person shooter video game with light role - playing elements developed by Digital Extremes and published by 2 K Games .
DocBook began in 1991 in discussion groups on Usenet and eventually became a joint project of HAL Computer Systems and O'Reilly & Associates and eventually spawned its own maintenance organization ( the Davenport Group ) before moving in 1998 to the SGML Open consortium , which subsequently became OASIS .
Bomberman Blitz is a DSiWare game developed by Hudson Soft .
Kirby 's Dream Course ( Kirby Bowl ( カービィボウル Kābī Bouru ) in Japan ) is a 1994 golf video game developed by HAL Laboratory and published by Nintendo for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System video game console .
Escape from Rungistan is an interactive fiction computer game written by Bob Blauschild for the Apple II and released by Sirius Software in 1982 .
Puyo Puyo ! ! 20th Anniversary ( ぷよぷよ ! ! Puyopuyo 20th anniversary ) is a Puyo Puyo game created by Sega and Sonic Team , released for the Nintendo DS on July 14 , 2011 and for the Wii , Nintendo 3DS , and PlayStation Portable on December 15 , 2011 .
Alley Master is a Tenpin bowling arcade game released by Cinematronics in 1986 .
Mad Dog McCree is the first live - action laserdisc video game released by American Laser Games .
HAMMER is a high - availability 64-bit file system developed by Matthew Dillon for DragonFly BSD using B+trees .
Big Money ! is a computer puzzle game created by PopCap Games .
Armageddon Riders is a vehicular combat video game produced by Targem Games .
Tori - Emaki ( Japanese for `` bird picture scroll '' ) is an interactive emakimono developed by SCE London Studio in association with Playlogic Entertainment for the PlayStation 3 platform , which utilizes the PlayStation Eye camera peripheral .
Al Emmo and the Lost Dutchman 's Mine is an adventure game created by Himalaya Studios for the PC .
NTFS ( New Technology File System ) is a proprietary file system developed by Microsoft .
Transarctica ( or Arctic Baron ) is a 1993 computer game made by the French company Silmarils for the Amiga and ported to the PC , Atari ST , Macintosh and Atari Falcon .
Heavyweight Champ is a series of boxing video games released by Sega .
Portal 2 is a 2011 first - person puzzle - platform video game developed and published by Valve Corporation .
Blue Toad Murder Files ( full title , Blue Toad Murder Files : The Mysteries of Little Riddle ) is a murder mystery puzzle video game developed and published by the British video game developer Relentless Software .
Adobe Acrobat is a family of application software and Web services developed by Adobe Systems to view , create , manipulate , print and manage files in Portable Document Format ( PDF ) .
Parakey is a Web - based computer user interface proposed by Firefox contributors Blake Ross and Joe Hewitt .
Assassin 's Creed III is a 2012 action - adventure video game developed by Ubisoft Montreal and published by Ubisoft for PlayStation 3 , Xbox 360 , Wii U , and Microsoft Windows .
Sherlock Holmes Versus Jack the Ripper is an adventure game for Microsoft Windows and Xbox 360 , developed by Frogwares .
' Splosion Man is a 2.5D action platform video game developed by Twisted Pixel Games for the Xbox 360 's Xbox Live Arcade digital download service .
Dungeon Keeper is a strategy video game developed by Bullfrog Productions and released by Electronic Arts in July 1997 for the PC .
The Legend of Mir 3 was a sprite based isometric 3-D massively multiplayer online role - playing game , developed by WeMade Entertainment .
Near Orbit Vanguard Alliance 3 ( also called N.O.V.A. 3 ) is Gameloft 's third installment of the N.O.V.A. series for iOS , BlackBerry 10 and Android devices , with planned releases for the BlackBerry PlayBook and Windows Phone 8 devices .
China Warrior , known in Japan as The Kung Fu ( THE 功夫 ( ザ・クンフー ) ) , is a horizontal beat'em up video game created in 1987 by Hudson Soft for the TurboGrafx-16 .
Munch Man is a video game written by Jim Dramis for the Texas Instruments TI-99/4A home computer and published as a cartridge by Texas Instruments in 1982 .
Communist Mutants from Space is a fixed shooter video game created in 1982 by Starpath ( formerly known as Arcadia ) for the Atari 2600 home video game console and the Starpath Supercharger cassette accessory .
DJMax Technika 2 ( Korean : 디제이맥스 테크니카 2 ) is a music arcade game published and developed by Pentavision in South Korea , and is a sequel to the earlier DJMax Technika arcade game .
BESYS ( Bell Operating System ) was an early computing environment originally implemented as a batch processing operating system in 1957 at Bell Labs for the IBM 704 computer .
Kinectimals was developed by Frontier Developments and was a launch title for Kinect .
Aces of the Galaxy is a downloadable rail shooter , developed by Artech Digital Entertainment and published by Sierra Entertainment for the Xbox Live Arcade .
Alpine Racer 2 is a 3D Alpine skiing arcade game released by Namco in 1996 .
Original authors of Gallium3D were Keith Whitwell and Brian Paul at Tungsten Graphics ( acquired by VMware ) .
Mendel Palace , originally released in Japan as Quinty ( Japanese : クインティ Hepburn : Kuinti ) , is a 1990 action / puzzle arcade game developed by Game Freak .
Namco Driver 's Eyes is a 3D first - person Formula One simulator racing video game released on the Namco System 21 arcade hardware in 1990 .
Primeval Hunt is a shooting arcade game which is developed and published by Sega and runs on their Sega Lindbergh hardware .
Driift Mania ( formerly titled Driift ) is a WiiWare racing game by Konami .
Dance Maniax is a game from the Bemani series of rhythm games , published by Konami , with songs mostly from the Dancemania series of music , and shares many songs with Dance Dance Revolution .
Fighter & Attacker , originally titled F / A ( エフ/エイ Efu / Ei ) in Japan , is a vertical scrolling shooter arcade game , which was released by Namco in 1992 .
Robot Rascals is a scavenger hunt video game by Ozark Softscape and published by Electronic Arts .
Trine 2 is a side - scrolling action platform and puzzle video game developed by Frozenbyte .
Project Gotham Racing ( PGR ) is a racing game , the first in its series , developed by Bizarre Creations and published by Microsoft for the Xbox gaming console .
Blitz Brigade is a multiplayer first - person shooter video game developed and published by Gameloft released on 9 May 2013 for iOS , Android and Windows .
Power Golf is a golf video game released by Hudson Soft for the TurboGrafx-16 in 1989 .
San Francisco Rush 2049 is a 1999 racing video game developed by Atari Games and published by Midway Games for the Arcade , Nintendo 64 , Game Boy Color , and Sega Dreamcast .
Dark Void is a video game developed by Airtight Games using the Unreal Engine 3 and published by Capcom for the PlayStation 3 , Xbox 360 and Microsoft Windows .
Code of the Samurai , known in Japan as Shinsengumi Gunraw Den ( 新選組群狼伝 Shinsengumi Gunrou Den ) , is a hack and slash game for the PlayStation 2 by Red Entertainment .
Gregory Schopen is Professor of Buddhist Studies at University of California , Los Angeles .
Paul E. Johnson ( born August 15 , 1942 in Los Angeles ) is an American historian and professor emeritus at University of South Carolina .
Mark N. Katz ( born November 11 , 1954 ) is a professor of government and politics at George Mason University in Fairfax , Virginia , United States .
Denis Pelli is a Professor of Psychology and Neural Science at New York University studying object recognition and reading .
Tariq Modood , MBE , FAcSS ( born 1952 ) is a British Pakistani Professor of Sociology , Politics and Public Policy at the University of Bristol ( 1997 - - ) .
Lawrence L. Larmore , PhD , is an American mathematician and theoretical computer scientist , currently tenuring as the professor of computer science at the University of Nevada , Las Vegas ( UNLV ) .
Rolando Hinojosa ( born 1929 ) is a novelist , essayist , poet and the Ellen Clayton Garwood professor in the English Department at the University of Texas at Austin .
Sandra Jovchelovitch , from Porto Alegre , Brazil , is a social psychologist , currently Professor of Social Psychology and Director of the MSc program in Social and Cultural Psychology at the Institute of Social Psychology at the London School of Economics ( LSE ) , of which she serves as head since August 2007 .
Ralph Hyde ( 25 March 1939 -- 5 June 2015 ) was a curator of graphic arts at the Guildhall Library in London , a pre - eminent historian and writer on the subject of Panoramic painting .
Dr. Alexander Smits ( born December 25 , 1948 ) is the Eugene Higgins Professor of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering at Princeton University .
Javier Soltero is a Puerto Rican entrepreneur and current Corporate Vice President of Outlook at Microsoft .
Patrick Vaughan ( born 1965 ) is an American historian and scholar teaching at the MA program in Transatlantic Studies , Jagiellonian University in Kraków , Poland .
Lieutenant General Tadesse Werede Tesfay is Head of Mission and Force Commander of the United Nations Interim Security Force for Abyei ( UNISFA ) .
Lawrence Ponoroff is the Samuel M. Fegtly Chair in Commercial Law and former dean of the James E. Rogers College of Law at the University of Arizona .
Ivar Grande ( 28 April 1911 -- 11 December 1944 ) was a police officer and Gestapo agent in Trondheim , Norway during World War II . He was second - in - command of the group Sonderabteilung Lola , led by Henry Rinnan .
Dr. Thomas McGlashan ( born 1942 ) is an American professor of psychiatry at Yale University , well known for his academic contributions to the study of schizophrenia and other mental illnesses .
Tilman Nagel ( born 19 April 1942 , in Cottbus ) is a German Orientalist and Professor Emeritus at the University of Göttingen .
Hagen Schulze ( 31 July 1943 -- 4 September 2014 ) was a German historian who held a position at the Free University of Berlin .
Aled Edwards ( born June 1 , 1962 ) is the director and CEO of the Structural Genomics Consortium and holds the Banbury Chair of Medical Research at the University of Toronto , Canada and is Visiting Professor of Chemical Biology at the University of Oxford , U.K.
Walter Rudin ( May 2 , 1921 -- May 20 , 2010 ) was an Austrian - American mathematician and professor of Mathematics at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison .
Humphrey Hawksley is a journalist who has been a foreign correspondent for the BBC since the early 1980s .
Charles Engel ( born 1956 ) is an American economist and currently the Hester professor in the economics department at the University of Wisconsin - Madison .
Andrew H. Hedges ( born 1966 ) is a co - editor of the Joseph Smith Papers , and from 1995 until 2009 was an associate professor of Church History and Doctrine at Brigham Young University ( BYU ) .
Michael J. Belton ( born 1934 ) is President of Belton Space Exploration Initiatives and Emeritus Astronomer at the Kitt Peak National Observatory in Arizona .
( Helen ) Fay Dowker ( /ˈdaʊkər/ ; born 1965 in Manchester , Lancashire ) is a British Professor of Theoretical Physics at Imperial College London .
Ken Howery is a co - founder and partner at Founders Fund , a San Francisco - based venture capital firm with over $ 2 billion under management .
Dina Appeldoorn attended the Royal Conservatory of The Hague , where she studied composition under F.E.A. Koeberg and later with Johan Wagenaar .
Joe Logan ( born January 28 , 1974 ) is the head coach of the Loyola University Maryland women 's basketball team , an NCAA Division I program that competes in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference ( MAAC ) .
James Landale ( born 1969 ) is a BBC journalist who is the current Deputy Political Editor of BBC News .
Jonathan Glickman ( born May 18 , 1969 ) is an American film producer and the President of Metro - Goldwyn - Mayer Pictures Film Division .
Maria Limanskaya ( also mistakenly referred to as Anna Pavlova ) was a female soldier of the Red Army for three years during World War II . She became known as the Russian woman who directed traffic at the Brandenburg Gate in 1945 after the Battle of Berlin .
Alan Keith - Lucas ( 1910 - -1995 ) , known during the early part of his life as Alan Lucas , was a social worker and professor at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill who worked primarily in the field of residential childcare .
Vik Singh previously worked at Google and Microsoft , both in research and products , helping ship Google Custom Search and Microsoft Windows XPSP2 Wireless Networking .
Ernst Joachim Wolfgang Stroebe ( born 5 May 1941 ) is a German social psychologist and Emeritus Professor of Social Psychology at the Utrecht University and the University of Groningen , particularly known for his works `` Introduction to social psychology '' and `` Social psychology and health , '' and on brainstorming .
Ingrid D. Rowland ( b. August 19 , 1953 ) is a professor at the University of Notre Dame School of Architecture .
Robin Truth Goodman is a Professor of Literature at Florida State University .
Joseph Sweetman Ames ( July 3 , 1864 -- June 24 , 1943 ) was a physicist , professor at Johns Hopkins University , provost of the university from 1926 until 1929 , and university president from 1929 until 1935 .
Bridget Kendall MBE ( born 27 April 1956 ) is an English journalist who is the BBC 's Diplomatic correspondent working for the corporation 's radio and television networks .
Hoda Elsadda is Chair in the Study of the Contemporary Arab World at the University of Manchester .
Liz Balmaseda ( born January 17 , 1959 ) is a Pulitzer Prize - winning journalist , who writes for The Palm Beach Post .
Alejandro Strachan is a Professor of Materials Engineering at Purdue University and the Deputy Director of NNSA 's Center for the Prediction of Reliability , Integrity and Survivability of Microsystems .
Olimpia Salas Martínez ( b. 1958 ) is a professor and researcher at the Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education , State of Mexico .
François Noudelmann is currently a professor at the European Graduate School in Saas - Fee ( Switzerland ) , the University of Paris VIII ( Université de Vincennes à Saint - Denis ) , Johns Hopkins University in Baltimore , and New York University .
Herbert Mohring ( 1928 -- June 4 , 2012 ) was a transportation economist who taught at the University of Minnesota from 1961 - -1994 .
Major Barclay Harding Warburton I ( April 1 , 1866 -- December 5 , 1954 ) was the publisher of the Philadelphia Evening Telegraph .
Mahmoud Hessabi ( Persian : سید محمود حسابی‎‎ , February 23 , 1903 , Tehran -- September 3 , 1992 , Geneva ) was an Iranian scientist , researcher and professor of University of Tehran .
Philippe Desan is Howard L. Willett Professor of French and History of Culture at the University of Chicago .
Susan Fromberg Schaeffer ( March 25 , 1940 -- August 26 , 2011 ) was a noted novelist and poet who was a Professor of English at Brooklyn College for over thirty years .
Frank Ruskey is a combinatorialist and computer scientist , and professor at the University of Victoria .
William F. Edwards ( April 26 , 1906 - 13 August 1989 ) was a prominent businessman and educator who held the Driggs Chair of Finance at Brigham Young University ( BYU ) among many other notable positions .
Kirsty Lang ( born 1962 ) is a British journalist and broadcaster who works for BBC Radio and Television .
In 2015 Paula Vogel 's literary archive was obtained by the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library at Yale University , and she became the first female playwright included in the library 's Yale Collection of American Literature .
Rinaldo Walcott is a Black Canadian academic and writer , employed as an associate professor at OISE / University of Toronto in the Department of Sociology and Equity Studies in Education .
David A. Weitz ( born October 3 , 1951 ) is a Canadian / American physicist and Mallinckrodt Professor of Physics & Applied Physics and professor of Systems Biology at Harvard University .
Yuen - Ron Shen ( 沈元壤 ) is a professor emeritus of physics at the University of California , Berkeley , known for his work on non - linear optics .
Kent W. Colton ( born November 21 , 1943 ) is a Senior Scholar at the Joint Center for Housing Studies , Harvard University .
Rochel Gelman ( born January 23 , 1942 ) is a psychology professor at Rutgers University , New Brunswick , NJ , and Co - Director of the Center for Cognitive Science .
Harry Bolton Seed ( August 19 , 1922 -- April 23 , 1989 ) was an educator , scholar , former Professor at the University of California , Berkeley .
Arthur Scott Walters is an American neurologist , a professor of neurology at the Vanderbilt University School of Medicine in Nashville , Tennessee , USA .
Perry A. Frey ( born 1935 ) is professor emeritus of biochemistry at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison .
William Lyman Underwood ( 1864 -- January 24 , 1929 ) was an American photographer who was also involved in the research of time - temperature canning research at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) during 1895 - 96 .
William Horbury ( b. 1942 ) is Professor of Jewish and Early Christian Studies and a Fellow of Corpus Christi College at Cambridge University .
Tom W. Mayer is a writer and retired professor of the English Department at the University of New Mexico , Albuquerque , where he held the position of Professional Writer during his tenure there in the 1980s and 1990s .
Kweku Adoboli ( born 21 May 1980 ) is a Ghanaian ex - trader known for his role in the 2011 UBS rogue trader scandal .
Nabi Saleh is an Iranian Australian businessman and commodities trader , known for his role in purchasing Gloria Jean 's Coffees and taking it world wide .
Katherine Weare ( born 1950 ) is a Professor of Education at the University of Southampton , England .
Bernd Sturmfels ( born March 28 , 1962 in Kassel , West Germany ) is Professor of Mathematics and Computer Science at the University of California , Berkeley .
Menna Richards OBE was the Controller of BBC Cymru Wales from February 2000 to February 2011 .
Lieutenant General Purna Chandra Thapa is an officer in the Nepalese Army and served as the Head of Mission and Force Commander of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force from 19 January 2015 until 7 February 2016 .
Gerrit Glas ( born 31 August 1954 , Bennekom ) studied Medicine at the University of Amsterdam and Philosophy at the Vrije Universiteit .
Dorothee Kern , ( born 1966 ) is a professor of Biochemistry at Brandeis University and former player for the East German national basketball team .
Carl Van Ness is the Curator of Manuscripts & Archives Department in the University of Florida Libraries ' Special & Area Studies Collections , and was appointed the University Historian for the University of Florida in 2006 .
Carol Myers - Scotton ( born 1934 ) was a Distinguished Professor Emerita in the Linguistics Program and Department of English at the University of South Carolina until 2003 and is now an adjunct professor in the Department of Linguistics and Languages at Michigan State University , and also a visiting scholar at the MSU African Studies Center .
Sow - Hsin Chen ( simplified Chinese : 陈守信 ; traditional Chinese : 陳守信 ; pinyin : Chén shǒuxìn ; born in Chia - yi , Taiwan ) , is an American physicist and Professor Emeritus at Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) .
Lawrence Amos McLouth , A.B. , LL.D. ( 1863 - -1927 ) was an American Germanic scholar , born at Ontonagon , Michigan He graduated from the University of Michigan in 1887 , as a member of the Zeta Psi fraternity .
Matthias Kuhle ( 20 April 1948 -- 25 April 2015 ) was a German geographer and professor at the University of Göttingen .
Lawrence M. Principe is the Drew Professor of the Humanities at Johns Hopkins University in the Department of History of Science and Technology and the Department of Chemistry .
Joseph M. Hellerstein ( born 7 June 1968 ) is professor of Computer Science at the University of California , Berkeley , where he works on database systems and computer networks .
Paul Beaudry ( born 1960 ) is Professor and Canada Research Chair in the UBC Department of Economics at the University of British Columbia .
Daniel Guggenheim ( July 9 , 1856 -- September 28 , 1930 ) was an American mining magnate and philanthropist , and a son of Meyer Guggenheim .
Matteo I Visconti ( Invorio , 15 August 1250 - Crescenzago , 24 June 1322 ) was the son of Teobaldo Visconti ( nephew of the Archbishop of Milan , Ottone Visconti ) and Anastasia Pirovano .
Ali ibn Buya ( Persian : علی بن بویه‎‎ ) , known by his laqab ( honorific epithet ) Imad al - Dawla ( c. 891/2 -- December 949 ) , was the founder of the Buyid dynasty in Iran ( in Shiraz , 934 - -949 ) .
Tokai Teio ( Japanese : トウカイテイオー , April 20 , 1988 - August 30 , 2013 ) was a Japanese thoroughbred racehorse , sired by Symboli Rudolf , a son of Partholon , out of Tokai Natural , a daughter of Nice Dancer .
Sir George Downing , 2nd Baronet , of East Hatley ( died June 1711 ) was the son and heir of Sir George Downing , 1st Baronet .
Lady Katherine Percy ( May 18 , 1423 -- c. 1475 ) was the daughter of Henry Percy , 2nd Earl of Northumberland and Lady Eleanor Neville .
Shealtiel ( Hebrew : שְׁאַלְתִּיאֵל‎ , Shə’altî’ēl ) or Greek - derived variant Salathiel ( Greek : Σαλαθιηλ , Salăthiēl ) was the son of Jeconiah , king of Judah .
Nikephoros Xiphias was born probably some time around or before 980 , and was most likely the son of Alexios Xiphias , who served as the Catepan of Italy in 1006 - -08 .
Agonglo took over from his father King Kpengla in 1789 and inherited many of the economic problems that developed during Kpengla 's reign .
Mahmoud Mirza ( 9 October 1905 -- 2 July 1988 ) Iranian prince of Qajar Dynasty , was the son of Mohammad Ali Shah Qajar .
Philip Herbert , 5th Earl of Pembroke , 2nd Earl of Montgomery ( 1621 -- 11 December 1669 ) , was the son of Philip Herbert , 4th Earl of Pembroke , and Susan de Vere .
Some scholars have linked the Nine Mothers of Heimdallr with the Nine Daughters of Ægir ( whose parentage and names combined imply waves ) , an identification that would mean that Heimdallr was thus born from the waves of the sea .
Henry Marc Brunel ( 27 June 1842 -- 7 October 1903 ) was the second son of the celebrated English engineer Isambard Kingdom Brunel , and followed his father 's footsteps in becoming a civil engineer .
Leonidas Palaskas was born in Ioannina in 1819 , the son of the chieftain Christos Palaskas .
James Hay , 15th Earl of Erroll ( 20 April 1726 -- 3 July 1778 ) was the son of William Boyd , 4th Earl of Kilmarnock .
Henry Vaux ( c. 1559 - 19 November 1587 ) was an English recusant , priest smuggler , and poet during the reign of Elizabeth I. He was born the eldest child of William Vaux , 3rd Baron Vaux of Harrowden , and his first wife , Elizabeth Beaumont , daughter of John Beaumont of Grace Dieu , Leicester .
Doon Arbus ( born April 3 , 1945 ) , a daughter of actor Allan Arbus and photographer Diane Arbus , is a writer and journalist .
Roland Mack grew up as a son of the entrepreneur Franz Mack , in Waldkirch .
Mary Anna Custis Lee was the only surviving child of George Washington Parke Custis , George Washington 's step - grandson and adopted son and founder of Arlington House , and Mary Lee Fitzhugh Custis , daughter of William Fitzhugh and Ann Bolling Randolph Fitzhugh .
Xiong Zhi succeeded his father Xiong Kang , but later abdicated due to illness .
Lewis Washington was the son of George Corbin Washington , the grandson of William Augustine Washington , and a great - grandson of Augustine Washington , half - brother of George Washington .
The most widely accepted version is recounted in Ovid 's Metamorphoses , where Adonis is the son of Myrrha and her father Cinyras .
Publius Cornelius Scipio Africanus ( 236 - -183 BC ) , also known as Scipio the African , Scipio Africanus - Major , Scipio Africanus the Elder , and Scipio the Great , is renowned as one of the greatest generals , not only of ancient Rome , but of all time .
Raja Zarith Sofiah was born in Batu Gajah Hospital , Batu Gajah , on 14 August 1959 as the third child and second daughter of Sultan Idris Shah II of Perak and Raja Mazwin Raja Arif Shah .
Mao Anqing ( Chinese : 毛岸青 ; pinyin : Máo Ànqīng ) ( 23 November 1923 - 23 March 2007 ) was the last known surviving son of Mao Zedong .
Philip Frederick of the Palatinate ( Prince Palatine John Philip Frederick , 16 September 1627 -- 16 December 1650 ) , was the seventh son of Frederick V , Elector Palatine ( of the House of Wittelsbach ) , the `` Winter King '' of Bohemia , by his consort , the English princess Elizabeth Stuart .
Endeïs was either the daughter of Chiron and the nymph Chariclo ; the daughter of Pandion of Athens ; or the daughter of the Megarian warlord Sciron .
Nguyễn Phúc Cảnh ( 1780 - -1801 ) , also known as Prince Cảnh , was the eldest son of the Vietnamese Prince Nguyễn Phúc Ánh , the future Emperor Gia Long .
Brian Henson ( born November 3 , 1963 ) is an American puppeteer , director , producer , and the chairman of The Jim Henson Company .
Jeanne Modigliani ( 29 November 1918 -- 27 July 1984 ) was the biographer of her father , artist Amedeo Modigliani , writing the 1958 book Modigliani , man and myth , later translated into English from the Italian by Esther Rowland Clifford .
Louis Lully ( Paris , 4 August 1664 -- 1 April 1734 ) was a French musician and the eldest son of Jean - Baptiste Lully .

Prince Albert Victor , Duke of Clarence and Avondale ( Albert Victor Christian Edward ; 8 January 1864 -- 14 January 1892 ) , was the eldest son of Albert Edward , Prince of Wales ( later King Edward VII ) , and the grandson of the reigning British monarch , Queen Victoria .

Axayacatl was a son of the princess Atotoztli II and her cousin , prince Tezozomoc .
Attalus III ( Greek : Ἄτταλος Γ΄ ) Philometor Euergetes ( c. 170 BC -- 133 BC ) was the last Attalid king of Pergamon , ruling from 138 BC to 133 BC . He was the son of Eumenes II and wife Stratonice of Pergamon and the nephew of Attalus II , whom he succeeded .
Elizabeth Ferrers ( c. 1250 -- c. 1300 ) was a daughter of William de Ferrers , 5th Earl of Derby , and his second wife Margaret de Quincy ( born 1218 ) .
Joseph Ignaz Philipp von Hessen - Darmstadt was born in Brussels on January 22 , 1699 , the son of Philip of Hesse - Darmstadt and his wife Princess Marie Therese von Croÿ ( 1673 - -1714 ) , daughter of Ferdinand François Joseph von Croÿ , 3rd Duke of Havré .
Prince Pedro Luiz of Orléans - Braganza ( 12 January 1983 -- 1 June 2009 ) was the son of Prince Antônio of Orléans - Braganza , and was third in the line of succession to the former Brazilian throne , abolished in 1889 .
Louise Hollandine of the Palatinate ( 18 April 1622 -- 11 February 1709 ) was a daughter of Frederick V , Elector Palatine and King of Bohemia , and Elizabeth Stuart .
Yuan Huangtou ( Chinese : zh:元黄头 ) was the son of emperor Yuan Lang of Eastern Wei .
