In Greek mythology , Atreus ( /ˈeɪtriəs/ ; Greek : Ἀτρεύς ) was a king of Mycenae in the Peloponnese , the son of Pelops and Hippodamia , and the father of Agamemnon and Menelaus .
Abdullah Khadr was born in 1981 in Ottawa , Canada as the second child and first son to Ahmed Khadr and his wife Maha el - Samnah , while his father was still in graduate school in computer science .
Matthew , Count of Boulogne , also known as Matthew of Alsace ( c. 1137 - -1173 ) was the second son of Thierry , Count of Flanders and Sibylla of Anjou .
Judith of Habsburg ( 13 March 1271 -- 21 May 1297 ) was the youngest daughter of Rudolph I of Germany and his wife Gertrude of Hohenburg .
Princess Maria Maximilianovna of Leuchtenberg , also known as Princess Maria Romanovskya , Maria , Princess Romanovskaja , or Marie Maximiliane ( 16 October 1841 - 16 February 1914 ) was the eldest daughter of Maximilian de Beauharnais , 3rd Duke of Leuchtenberg and his wife Grand Duchess Maria Nikolaevna of Russia .
Rohese of Monmouth ( Rohese de Monemue in Anglo - Norman ; born about 1135/1140 ; died in or near 1180 ) was the daughter of Baderon fitzWilliam , lord of Monmouth , and of his wife Rohese de Clare .
Herman I , Count of Henneberg ( 1224 -- 18 December 1290 ) was the son of Count Poppo VII of Henneberg and his wife , Jutta of Thuringia ( born : 1184 ; died : 6 August 1235 in Schleusingen ) , the eldest daughter of Landgrave Herman I of Thuringia .
John VII Palaiologos was the son of Emperor Andronikos IV Palaiologos and Keratsa of Bulgaria , a daughter of Emperor Ivan Alexander of Bulgaria and Theodora of Wallachia .
Duchess Anna of Prussia and Jülich - Cleves - Berg ( 3 July 1576 -- 30 August 1625 ) was the daughter of Albert Frederick , Duke of Prussia , and Marie Eleonore of Cleves .
Prince Aloys of Liechtenstein ( Aloys Gonzaga Maria Adolf ; 17 June 1869 in Hollenegg -- 16 March 1955 in Vaduz ) was the son of Prince Alfred of Liechtenstein ( 1842 - -1907 ) and Princess Henriette of Liechtenstein ( 1843 - -1931 ) , daughter of Alois II of Liechtenstein .
Doña Leonor Cortés Moctezuma ( born c. 1528 ) was the out of wedlock daughter of Hernán Cortés , conquistador of Mexico , and Doña Isabel Moctezuma the eldest daughter of the Aztec Emperor Moctezuma II . She was acknowledged by her father and married Juan de Tolosa , one of the discoverers of the silver mines in Zacatecas .
Gen. Duke 's dam was Wistful , a daughter of Sun Again by Sun Teddy .
In mathematics ( specifically in measure theory ) , a Radon measure , named after Johann Radon , is a measure on the σ-algebra of Borel sets of a Hausdorff topological space X that is locally finite and inner regular .
Borel sets are named after Émile Borel .
La Plata was renamed Eva Perón City ( Ciudad Eva Perón ) between 1952 and 1955 .
Emmer - Erfscheidenveen is a hamlet in the Netherlands and it is part of the Emmen municipality in Drenthe .
Köpmantorget ( Swedish : `` Merchant 's Square '' ) is a small public square in Gamla stan , the old town in central Stockholm , Sweden , located between the street Köpmangatan and to slopes collectively named Köpmanbrinken , both of which lead down to the street Österlånggatan .
In physics and fluid mechanics , a Blasius boundary layer ( named after Paul Richard Heinrich Blasius ) describes the steady two - dimensional laminar boundary layer that forms on a semi - infinite plate which is held parallel to a constant unidirectional flow .
The Kilimanjaro Region borrowed its name from the tallest mountain in Africa , Mount Kilimanjaro .
OCR - A is a font that arose in the early days of computer optical character recognition when there was a need for a font that could be recognized not only by the computers of that day , but also by humans .
The Kirov Islands or Sergey Kirov Islands ( Russian : Oстрова Кирова , Ostrova Kirova or Aрхипелаг Сергея Кирова , Archipelag Sergeya Kirova ) , also known as Kerova Islands , is an archipelago of small islands covered with tundra vegetation .
Pyrénées - Orientales ( French pronunciation : ​(pi.ʁe.ne.ɔ.ʁjɑ̃.tal ) ; Catalan : Pirineus Orientals ; Occitan : Pirenèus Orientals ; `` Eastern Pyrenees '' ) is a department of southern France adjacent to the northern Spanish frontier and the Mediterranean Sea .
143 Adria is a fairly large main - belt asteroid that was discovered by Austrian astronomer J. Palisa on February 23 , 1875 , at Pula , and named after the Adriatic Sea , on the coast of which the discovery was made .
The Martin Luther University of Halle - Wittenberg ( German : Martin - Luther - Universität Halle - Wittenberg ) , also referred to as MLU , is a public , research - oriented university in the cities of Halle and Wittenberg within Saxony - Anhalt , Germany .
The Jastrow illusion is an optical illusion discovered by the American psychologist Joseph Jastrow in 1889 .
The Toarcian takes its name from the city of Thouars , just south of Saumur in the Loire Valley of France .
McCormick Foundation is a Chicago - based nonprofit charitable trust established in 1955 , following the death of `` Colonel '' Robert R. McCormick of the McCormick family .
The Lewinsky scandal was an American political sex scandal emerging in 1998 , from a sexual relationship between 49-year - old President Bill Clinton and a 22-year - old White House employee , Monica Lewinsky .
Blum Blum Shub ( B.B.S. ) is a pseudorandom number generator proposed in 1986 by Lenore Blum , Manuel Blum and Michael Shub that is derived from Michael O. Rabin 's oblivious transfer mapping .
Space launch vehicle Volna ( `` wave '' in Russian ) , is a converted Submarine - launched ballistic missile used for launching satellites into orbit .
162 Laurentia is a large and dark main - belt asteroid that was discovered by the French brothers Paul Henry and Prosper Henry on April 21 , 1876 , and named after A. Laurent , an amateur astronomer who discovered asteroid 51 Nemausa .
Kopp 's law can refer to either of two relationships discovered by the German chemist Hermann Franz Moritz Kopp ( 1817 - -1892 ) .
Edenite is named for the locality of Edenville , Orange County , New York , where it was first described .
In mathematics , Giambelli 's formula , named after Giovanni Giambelli , expresses Schubert classes in terms of special Schubert classes , or Schur functions in terms of complete symmetric functions .
And the name Santa María Rupes are named after the Santa Maria , the ship of Christopher Columbus because all rupes are named after the ships of famous explorers on Mercury .
Tetrahedrite gets its name from the distinctive tetrahedron shaped cubic crystals .
In mathematics , Weber 's theorem , named after Heinrich Martin Weber , is a result on algebraic curves .
The Dalton Minimum was a period of low sunspot count , representing low solar activity , named after the English meteorologist John Dalton , lasting from about 1790 to 1830 or 1796 to 1820 , corresponding to the period solar cycle 4 to solar cycle 7 .
Suburban Girl is a 2007 comedy film starring Sarah Michelle Gellar , Alec Baldwin and Maggie Grace , which was filmed in New York City .
The Bedford Diaries explores the excitement and intensity of New York City college life through the eyes of six students with different backgrounds , experiences and ages , who are brought together in a provocative sexuality seminar .
Le calife de Bagdad ( The Caliph of Baghdad ) is an opéra comique in one act by the French composer François - Adrien Boieldieu with a libretto by Claude de Saint - Just ( Godard d'Aucourt ) .
I Am Mary Dunne ( 1968 ) is a novel by Northern Irish - Canadian writer Brian Moore about one day in the life of a beautiful and well - to - do 31-year - old Canadian woman living in New York City with her third husband , a successful playwright .
Walk Into Paradise ( also known as Walk Into Hell ) is a 1956 French - Australian international co - production adventure film directed by Lee Robinson and Marcello Pagliero shot on location in the highlands of Papua New Guinea .
Mother of George is a 2013 Nigerian drama film directed by Andrew Dosunmu and tells the story of a newly married Nigerian couple in Brooklyn who own and manage a small restaurant while struggling with fertility issues .
McTeague is a dentist of limited intellect from a poor miner 's family , who has opened a dentist shop on Polk Street in San Francisco .
Urban Ghost Story is a 1998 British horror film set in a high - rise housing estate in Glasgow .
The White Family is a novel by English author Maggie Gee , published in 2002 in London by Saqi Books .
Crisis in the Kremlin is a 1991 strategy video game with managerial aspects in which the player acts as General Secretary of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union from 1985 to 2017 .
Detropia is a 2012 documentary film , directed by Heidi Ewing and Rachel Grady , about the city of Detroit , Michigan .
Lost in the Barrens is an adventure story that takes place in northern Manitoba and southwestern North West Territories in 1935 .
God of Gamblers II ( Chinese : 賭俠 ; Cantonese Yale : Dou Hap ; literally : `` Knight of Gambling '' ) is a 1990 Hong Kong action comedy film written and directed by Wong Jing .
The Liver Birds is a British sitcom , set in Liverpool , North West England , which aired on BBC1 from April 1969 to January 1979 , and again in 1996 .
The Colour of Magic ( also known as The Color of Magic ) is a 1983 comic fantasy novel by Terry Pratchett , and is the first book of the Discworld series .
The L.A. Quartet is a sequence of four crime fiction novels by James Ellroy set in the late 1940s through the late 1950s in Los Angeles .
The Sweeney is a 1970s British television police drama focusing on two members of the Flying Squad , a branch of the Metropolitan Police specialising in tackling armed robbery and violent crime in London .
Kokowääh is set in Berlin and Potsdam , Brandenburg , Germany .
Wizard of the Pigeons is a 1985 urban fantasy novel set in Seattle , Washington by Megan Lindholm , issued as a paperback original by Ace Books and reprinted in hardcover by Hypatia Press in 1994 .
Set in California , Spencer 's Pilots was created and produced by Larry Rosen .
The Blood of Others ( French : Le Sang des autres ) is a novel by the French existentialist Simone de Beauvoir first published in 1945 and depicting the lives of several characters in Paris leading up to and during the Second World War .
Only When I Dance tells the story of two teenagers , Irlan and Isabela , who pursue their dreams of becoming professional ballet dancers as a way to escape the violent slums of Rio de Janeiro .
Memoirs of an Invisible Man is a 1992 film directed by John Carpenter and released by Warner Bros. , with many scenes taking place in and around San Francisco .
The New Adventures of Heidi is a 1978 made for television musical using the Heidi character ; updating the character to the present time and shifting the action for Switzerland to New York City .

There , they take part in a reenactment of the events of `` The Final Problem '' organised by The Sherlock Holmes Society of London .
Whispers Under Ground is the third novel in the Rivers of London series by English author Ben Aaronovitch , published 2012 by Gollancz .
Lewis Black 's Root of All Evil is an American television series that premiered on March 12 , 2008 , on Comedy Central and was hosted by comedian Lewis Black .
Kavanagh QC is a British television series made by Central Television for ITV between 1995 and 2001 .
Curb Your Enthusiasm is an American comedy television series produced and broadcast by HBO , which premiered on October 15 , 2000 .
Alma Gêmea ( English : Soul Mate ) is a Brazilian telenovela that produced and broadcast by Rede Globo in 2005 and 2006 .
Brew Masters is a television series that was run weekly on Discovery Channel starting on Sunday , November 21 , 2010 .
The Thirteenth Year is a 1999 fantasy comedy - drama Disney Channel Original Movie .
Tidewater Tramp was a Canadian children 's adventure television series which aired on CBC Television from 1959 to 1961 .
Shorr is an Indian television drama series that airs on Sahara One , based on the story of a mute ( speech - impaired ) girl named Kanku .
Sunrise Weather was an early morning weekend program that aired on The Weather Channel from September 2008 to November 2013 .
Video on Trial is a Canadian comedy television program that airs on Canadian television network MuchMusic .
Design on a Dime is a decorating television series on HGTV .
`` The Sound of Jazz '' is a 1957 edition of the CBS television series Seven Lively Arts , and was one of the first major programs featuring jazz to air on American network television .
Web Junk 20 is an American television program in which VH1 and iFilm collaborate to highlight the twenty funniest and most interesting clips collected from the Internet that week .
The Red Buttons Show premiered on the CBS television network in 1952 , and ran for two years on that network , then moved to NBC for the final 1954 - 55 season .
16 and Pregnant is an American reality television series that debuted June 11 , 2009 , on MTV .
Caught on Camera with Nick Cannon is an American documentary reality television show on NBC .
Yancy Derringer is an American Western series that ran on CBS from 1958 to 1959 , with Jock Mahoney ( 1919 - -1989 ) in the title role .
Mobil 1 The Grid is a motorsport magazine show , which airs on Channel 4 in the UK on Saturday mornings ( the first six episodes were shown on Friday nights ) and is repeated during the following week on Motors TV .
Joey Faye 's Frolics is an American comedy / variety show that aired on CBS Wednesday night from 9:30 to 10:00 pm Eastern time for two weeks from April 5 , 1950 to April 12 , 1950 .
The Organist Entertains is a long - running music programme broadcast on BBC Radio 2 presented by Nigel Ogden .

Kiki 's American Adventure is an adult reality series which aired on Playboy TV in 2010 .
The Channel Four Daily ( or Channel 4 Daily ) was a breakfast television news magazine which was produced by Independent Television News , in collaboration with other independent production companies for Channel 4 .
The Proud Family is an American animated television sitcom that ran on the Disney Channel , from September 21 , 2001 to August 19 , 2005 .
Crime Syndicated was an American anthology series that aired on CBS from September 18 , 1951 to June 23 , 1953 .
The George Burns Show is a short - lived comedy television program that aired on NBC for one season ( 1958 - -59 ) , and was essentially a continuation of The George Burns and Gracie Allen Show .
Our Fellow Americans is a Canadian documentary television miniseries which aired on CBC Television in 1976 .
Świat według Kiepskich ( The World According to the Kiepskis , `` kiepski '' being a term roughly translating to the English term poor or crappy ) is a popular Polish television sitcom , produced by Polsat since 1999 .

A Man Called Sloane is an American secret agent adventure television series that aired on NBC during the 1979 - 1980 television season .

The Polly Bergen Show was a half - hour 18-episode comedy / variety show , starring then 27-year - old Polly Bergen , which aired on NBC in the 1957 - -1958 television season .
Zonosemata is a genus of tephritid or fruit flies in the family Tephritidae , comprising six species from North America and one from South America .
Typhonodorum is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Araceae .
The Cape zoanthid , Isozoanthus capensis , is a species of zoanthid in the family Parazoanthidae .
Darwinellidae is a family of sponges of the order Dendroceratida .
The Tasmanian devil ( Sarcophilus harrisii ) is a carnivorous marsupial of the family Dasyuridae , now found in the wild only on the Australian island state of Tasmania .
Allagelena is a genus of araneomorph spiders , in the family Agelenidae .
The Oriental beetle ( Anomala orientalis , not to be confused with the Japanese beetle ) is a beetle about 0.7 - 1.1 cm ( 0.3 - 0.4 inches ) long , with mottled , metallic brown- and black - colored elytra and a similarly - colored thorax and head during the adult stage .
Clonopsis is a stick insect genus in the family Bacillidae .
The Klaas 's cuckoo ( Chrysococcyx klaas ) is a species of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family .
Lear 's macaw ( Anodorhynchus leari ) , also known as the indigo macaw , is a large all - blue Brazilian parrot , a member of a large group of neotropical parrots known as macaws .
The Pugnose shiner ( Notropis anogenus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Kronokotherium is an extinct herbivorous marine mammal of the genus Desmostylia of the family Desmostylidae .
The Namaquab barb ( Barbus hospes ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Waccamaw killifish ( Fundulus waccamensis ) is a species of fish in the Fundulidae family .
The Calamoideae are a subfamily of the family Arecaceae containing 21 genera and about 620 species which are distributed worldwide .
The Sevan trout ( Salmo ischchan ) is an endemic fish species of Lake Sevan in Armenia , known as ishkhan ( իշխան , pronounced ( iʃˈχɑn ) ) in Armenian .
The Dalmatian wall lizard ( Podarcis melisellensis ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
Maurica is a genus of moths in the Arctiidae family from North - Western Africa .
The Murrayonida are an order of sea sponges in the sublass Calcinea .
Milyeringa is a genus of blind cave - fish in the family Eleotridae from the Cape Range and Barrow Island , northwestern Australia .

The Heermann 's gull ( Larus heermanni ) is a gull resident in the United States , Mexico and extreme southwestern British Columbia , nearly all nesting on Isla Rasa in the Gulf of California .
Heteranthera is a genus of aquatic plants in the water hyacinth family , Pontederiaceae , known generally as mud plantains .
The African piculet ( Sasia africana ) , sometimes placed in the monotypic genus Verreauxia , is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Pomatoschistus norvegicus , the Norway goby , is a species of goby native to the eastern Atlantic from Lofoten to the western English Channel and has also been recorded from the Mediterranean Sea .
Water treaders , the superfamily Mesovelioidea , are insects in the order Hemiptera , the true bugs .
The Yunnan red - backed vole ( Eothenomys miletus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Andinotrechus naranjoi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Andinotrechus .
Schwartz 's catfish ( Corydoras schwartzi ) is a tropical freshwater fish belonging to the Corydoradinae sub - family of the Callichthyidae family .
Orthophytum ( Greek `` ortho '' = straight and `` phytum '' = plant ) is a genus of the botanical family Bromeliaceae , subfamily Bromelioideae .
The African goshawk ( Accipiter tachiro ) is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
Betula minor , the dwarf white birch , is a species of birch which can be found in Eastern Canada and in such US states as Maine , New Hampshire , and New York .
Trombicula is a genus of harvest mites ( also known as red bugs , scrub - itch mites , berry bugs , or in their larval stage , as chiggers or chigoe ) in the Trombiculidae family .
The Low 's squirrel ( Sundasciurus lowii ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Socotra cormorant ( Phalacrocorax nigrogularis ) is a threatened species of cormorant that is endemic to the Persian Gulf and the south - east coast of the Arabian Peninsula .
Tritoniopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae , first described as a genus in 1926 .
Tulbaghieae is a tribe of plants belonging to the subfamily Allioideae of the Amaryllis family ( Amaryllidaceae ) .
Malabica tatai is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Malabica .

Oligosoma belongs to the Eugongylus group of genera in the subfamily Lygosominae ; the genus Bassiana appears to be fairly closely related .

Lemaireia is a genus of moths from the Saturniidae family , commonly known as Moon moths .

Chorizema is a genus of the legume family Fabaceae .
The European conger ( Conger conger ) is a species of conger of the family Congridae .
Curcuma is a genus of about 100 accepted species in the family Zingiberaceae that contains such species as turmeric and Siam Tulip .
Uropetala is a small genus of very large dragonflies in the family Petaluridae .
Cryptomma multistriatum is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cryptomma .
Gillaroo ( Salmo stomachicus ; historically included in Salmo trutta ) is a variety of trout which eats primarily snails and is only proven to inhabit Lough Melvin in Ireland .
The Congo moor chat or Congo moor - chat ( Myrmecocichla tholloni ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .

The Satéré marmoset ( Mico saterei ) is a marmoset species endemic to Brazil .

Torneutes pallidipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Torneutes .

The Brazilian merganser ( Mergus octosetaceus ) is a duck in the typical merganser genus .
Propimelodus is a genus of South American catfish of the family Pimelodidae .
Callilepis is easily distinguished from other Gnaphosidae by the single translucent lamina on the cheliceral retromargin , the short , angular endites and the flattened , transverse posterior median eyes .
Under the Dahlgren system , Dioscoreales was placed in the superorder Lilianae in subclass Liliidae ( monocotyledons ) of class Magnoliopsida ( angiosperms ) and comprised the eight families Dioscoreaceae , Petermanniaceae , Ripogonaceae , Smilacaceae , Stemonaceae , Taccaceae , Trichopodaceae and Trilliaceae .

The Marquesan ground dove ( Gallicolumba rubescens ) is a bird species in the family Columbidae .

Atlantic stargazer ( Uranoscopus scaber ) is a marine , subtropical fish of family Uranoscopidae .
The Cuban gar ( Atractosteus tristoechus ) is a fish in the Lepisosteidae family .

Triopha is a genus of colorful sea slugs , nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the family Polyceridae .
Fernandina 's flicker ( Colaptes fernandinae ) is a species of bird in the woodpecker family .
Oligochlora is an extinct genus of sweat bee in the Halictidae subfamily Halictinae .
Chrysoritis , commonly called Opals or Coppers , is a genus of butterflies in the Lycaenidae family found mainly in southern Africa and particularly South Africa .
Anatropites is a genus in the ceratitid family Tropitidae with spines instead of nodes on the umbilical shoulder , at least in early whorls .
The Choco toucan ( Ramphastos brevis ) is a large , mainly black bird found in humid lowland and foothill forests on the Pacific slope of Colombia and Ecuador .
Acanthopidae is a family of mantises consisting of 13 genera in the order Mantodea .
Hastingsia is a small genus of flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Agavoideae , known generally as rushlilies .
The Trappeaceae are a family of truffle - like fungi in the order Hysterangiales .
Common seadragon or weedy seadragon ( Phyllopteryx taeniolatus ) is a marine fish related to the seahorse .
The Middle American burrowing snake ( Adelphicos quadrivirgatus ) is a species of dipsadine colubrid snake , endemic to Mexico and Central America .
The Cuban trogon or tocororo ( Priotelus temnurus ) is a species of bird in the Trogonidae family .
Calyptrosciadium polycladum is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , the only member of the genus Calyptrosciadium .
The Balkan mole ( Talpa stankovici ) is a species of mammal in the family Talpidae .
Panjange is a genus of leaf - dwelling spiders in the family Pholcidae , widely distributed in the islands of Southeast Asia from Borneo and the Philippines to northern Australia .
As Baptornis was quite peculiar among the Hesperornithes , the family Baptornithidae has been established for it .
Ptilagrostis is a genus of grasses in the family Poaceae .
The Asian narrow - headed softshell turtle ( Chitra chitra ) is a large species of softshell turtle in the Trionychidae family .
Pyrrhocoris is a genus of true bugs in the family Pyrrhocoridae , the cotton stainers .
Banchinae are a subfamily of the parasitic wasp family Ichneumonidae with about 1,500 species ; the genera Glypta and Lissonota are very large .
Auriculella is a genus of air - breathing tropical land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
The Bloody Bay poison frog ( Mannophryne olmonae ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Actenonyx bembidioides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Actenonyx .
Nakhoda is a genus of mites in the family Laelapidae .
Dactylobatus is a small genus of skate in the family Rajidae .
The Cape long - billed lark ( Certhilauda curvirostris ) , also known as the Cape lark is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Junnanotrechus microps is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Junnanotrechus .
The Japanese skylark ( Alauda japonica or Alauda arvensis japonica ) is usually considered a subspecies of Eurasian skylark .
Sand bubbler crabs ( or sand - bubblers ) are crabs of the genera Scopimera and Dotilla in the family Dotillidae .
Neofelis diardi diardi ( Wilting et al . , 2007 ) is a subspecies of the Sunda clouded leopard ( Neofelis diardi ) native to the Batu and Sumatran islands of Indonesia .
Weale 's running frog , Weale 's frog , or rattling frog ( Semnodactylus wealii ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Hysteropterum is a genus of ' planthoppers ' described by Amyot & Serville in 1843 , belonging to the family Issidae , subfamily Issinae .
Sarcandra is a genus of the family Chloranthaceae , containing a single accepted species , and two proposed species .
Ceramaster is a genus of cushion stars in the family Goniasteridae .
The Cape Melville shade skink , Saproscincus saltus , is a species of lizard from the Cape York Peninsula of Queensland , Australia , described in 2013 .
The Kikambala nothobranch ( Nothobranchius interruptus ) is a species of fish in the Aplocheilidae family .
The Ascension frigatebird ( Fregata aquila ) is a seabird of the frigatebird family Fregatidae which breeds on the tiny Boatswain Bird Island just off Ascension Island in the tropical Atlantic Ocean .
The Brown River tree frog ( Litoria vocivincens ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Metahehoa granulata is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Megabalanus is a genus of barnacles in the family Balanidae .
The Madagascan stonechat or Madagascar stonechat ( Saxicola sibilla ) is a species of stonechat , endemic to Madagascar .
Archiacanthocephala is a class within the phylum of Acanthocephala .
Alchemilla is a genus of herbaceous perennial plants in the family Rosaceae , with the common name `` lady 's mantle '' applied generically as well as specifically to Alchemilla mollis .
Tetraphysa is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1906 .
The Amazon climbing salamander or Amazon mushroomtongue salamander ( Bolitoglossa palmata ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Brongersma 's toad or crapaud de Brongersma ( Bufo brongersmai ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Stempfferia marginata , the Scalloped Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Peruvian anchoveta ( Engraulis ringens ) is a species of fish of the anchovy family , Engraulidae .
Crateva is a genus of flowering plants in the caper family , Capparaceae .
The Anderson 's shrew mole ( Uropsilus andersoni ) is a species of mammal in the family Talpidae .
The Lampyrinae are a large subfamily of fireflies ( Lampyridae ) .
Fowlerina , one kind of `` sea angel '' , is a genus of small sea slugs , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Clionidae .
Pseudopolycesta tigrina is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Pseudopolycesta .
The Rio Luisito tree frog , Hyloscirtus piceigularis , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Colombia .
Ghatixalus is a genus of frogs in the family Rhacophoridae , subfamily Rhacophorinae .
Eupodium is a genus of ferns in the family Marattiaceae native to the Neotropics .
Prototocyon was named by Pohle ( 1928 ) and was assigned to Canidae by Carroll ( 1988 ) .
Aletia is a genus of Owlet moths of the Noctuidae family .
The Andean squirrel ( Sciurus pucheranii ) is a tree squirrel endemic to Colombia where it inhabits montane rain forest and cloud forests of the Cordillera Occidental and Cordillera Central ranges of the Colombian Andes , at elevations between 2,000 and 3,300 metres ( 6,600 and 10,800 ft ) .
The Argentine bolo mouse ( Necromys benefactus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Tasman starling ( Aplonis fusca ) was described in 1836 by John Gould as a species which occurred on both Norfolk Island and Lord Howe Island .
The taxonomy is complex . The `` Cerylonid Series '' is a cluster of highly derived Cucujoidea families comprising Alexiidae , Bothrideridae , Cerylonidae , Coccinellidae , Corylophidae , Discolomatidae , Endomychidae , and Latridiidae .
Zonites is a genus of mostly small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Zonitidae .
Endive ( /ˈɛndaɪv/ or /ˈɑːndiv/ ; Cichorium endivia ) is a leaf vegetable belonging to the genus Cichorium , which includes several similar bitter leafed vegetables .
Lepipolys was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Sympistis .
Wound tumor virus is an invertebrate and plant virus found in the United States of America belonging to the genus Phytoreovirus and the family Reoviridae .
The Ancash tapaculo ( Scytalopus affinis ) is a species of bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
Colpodichius platyderoides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Colpodichius .
Based on genetic and morphological analysis , the Cupressus genus is found in the Cupressoideae subfamily .
Neuquenraptor was assigned by Novas and Pol to the Dromaeosauridae in a polytomy with several dromaeosaurid taxa .
Frances 's sparrowhawk ( Accipiter francesiae ) is a small hawk .
Leucopternis is a Neotropical genus of birds of prey in the Accipitridae family .
Buffon 's river garfish ( Zenarchopterus buffonis ) is a species of fish in the Hemiramphidae family .
Agoristenidaeare a neotropical harvestman family of the Suborder Laniatores , in the superfamily Gonyleptoidea .
The Sonoyta pupfish or Quitobaquito pupfish ( Cyprinodon eremus ) is one of the most distinct species in its genus .
Persoonia is a genus of 98 species of shrubs and small trees in the tribe Persoonioideae in the large and diverse plant family Proteaceae .
The Nordmann 's greenshank or spotted greenshank ( Tringa guttifer ) is a wader in the large family Scolopacidae , the typical waders .
Paraoncidium is a genus of air - breathing sea slugs , a shell - less marine pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Onchidiidae .
Savigny 's agama ( Trapelus savignii ) is a species of lizard in the Agamidae family .
Tolypeutinae is a subfamily of armadillo in the family Dasypodidae .
The Rossel Island melomys ( Melomys arcium ) is a species of rodent from the family Muridae .

Tripodichthys is a genus in the tripod fish family ( Triacanthidae ) native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Schumacheria is a small genus of plants in family Dilleniaceae .
Myoga , myoga ginger or Japanese ginger ( myōga ( 茗荷 ) ) is the species Zingiber mioga in the Zingiberaceae family .
Lechea ( pinweed ) is a genus in the Cistaceae family .
Scaphosepalum ( from Greek `` boatlike sepals '' ) is a genus of plants belonging to the family Orchidaceae .
Anelytropsis papillosus is a species of legless lizard in the family Dibamidae , and the only species in the genus Anelytropsis .
Sphenarium is a grasshoppers genus in the family Pyrgomorphidae indigenous to Mexico .
The Chilean myotis ( Myotis chiloensis ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Electrapate martynovi is a fossil species of beetle in the family Schizopodidae , the only species in the genus Electrapate .
Umbopilio paradoxus is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Macrocypraea is a genus of large sea snails , cowries , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Lactifluus hygrophoroides ( formerly Lactarius hygrophoroides ) is a member of the milk - cap genus Lactifluus in the order Russulales .
The Harpactorinae are a large subfamily of the Reduviidae ( assassin bugs ) .
Ovulidae , common names the ovulids , cowry allies or false cowries , is a family of small to large predatory or parasitic sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Cypraeoidea , the cowries and the cowry allies .
Alzoniella is a genus of minute freshwater spring snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Morelet 's crocodile ( Crocodylus moreletii ) , also known as the Mexican crocodile , is a modest sized crocodilian found only in fresh waters of the Atlantic regions of Mexico , Belize and Guatemala .
Champion 's leaf - tailed gecko , Phyllurus championae , is a gecko first found in the Cameron Creek / Black Mountain area near Koumala , Queensland , Australia .
Dimorphoceratidae is one of two families included in the Dimorphocerataceae , a superfamily of ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the Goniatitida that lived during the Late Paleozoic .
Tapoides is a monotypic plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae .
The Mongolian hamster ( Allocricetulus curtatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Syconycteris is a genus of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The Goan day gecko , Cnemaspis goaensis , is a species of gecko found in Goa , India .
Felis margarita meinertzhageni was proposed as a subspecies of the sand cat by Reginald Innes Pocock in 1938 .
Recently Hebe stricta has been reclassified and the botanical name has changed to Veronica stricta .
Dicranoderes annulatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Dicranoderes .
Kyptoceratini is an extinct tribe of the subfamily Synthetoceratinae , deer - like mammals within the family Protoceratidae belonging to the order Artiodactyla , endemic to North America during the Miocene through Pliocene , living 23.03 - -3.6 Ma , existing for approximately 19.43 million years .
Codazziceras is an early Upper Cretaceous ammonite from the upper Cretaceous of Columbia ( S.A ) , distinguished from Lyelliceras ( Lyelliceratidae ) from which it is based and added to the Euomphaloceratinae ( Acanthoceratidae ) .
Wolffsohn 's leaf - eared mouse ( Phyllotis wolffsohni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The African chameleon or Sahel chameleon ( Chamaeleo africanus ) is a species of chameleon native to the Sahel and Nile Valley , although it has been introduced to Greece .
The Sri Lanka drongo ( Dicrurus lophorinus ) is a species of bird in the Dicruridae family .
The Trinidad dog - like bat ( Peropteryx trinitatis ) is a species of bat from the family Emballonuridae .
Originally assigned by Huene to the Allosauridae , Indosaurus is today considered a member of the Abelisauridae .
Llistrofus is an extinct genus of microsaur within the family Hapsidopareiontidae .
Harriotta is a genus of cartilaginous fish in the Rhinochimaeridae family .
Massonia is a genus of bulbous perennials in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae ( also treated as the family Hyacinthaceae ) .
Zenobiella subrufescens is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Dendrocollybia is a fungal genus in the family Tricholomataceae of the order Agaricales .
Acromantinae is a subfamily of the mantis family Hymenopodidae which contains one tribe , Acromantini , and 18 genera .
Phyllocaulis is a genus of land slugs , shell - less terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Veronicellidae , the leatherleaf slugs .
The Macedonian crested newt ( Triturus macedonicus ) is a newt species of the crested newt species complex in genus Triturus , found in the Western Balkan peninsula ( Bosnia - Hercegovina , Albania , Macedonia , north - western Greece and south - western Bulgaria ) .
The Mauritius olive white - eye ( Zosterops chloronothos often mistakenly spelled Zosterops chloronothus ) is a very rare passerine from the family of white - eyes ( Zosteropidae ) .
Tylosema species are in the Leguminosae family , the third largest family of flowering plants ( Doyle and Luckow , 2003 ) , in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae , in the tribe Cercideae .
Laemodonta is a genus of small air - breathing , saltmarsh snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Ellobiidae .
Phyllodesmium is a genus of predatory sea slugs , aeolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Facelinidae .
The Abyssocottidae are a family of fishes in the superfamily Cottoidea , the sculpins .
Callophyllis is a red algae genus in the family Kallymeniaceae .
The Schouteden 's swift ( Schoutedenapus schoutedeni ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Polygireulima is a genus of very small parasitic sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the Eulimidae family .
The Angolan free - tailed bat ( Mops condylurus ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Mammomonogamus is a genus of parasitic nematode of the family Syngamidae that parasitises the respiratory tracts of cattle , sheep , goats , deer , cats , orangutans , and elephants .
The subfamily Phaoniinae is within the Diptera family Muscidae .
The Chapultepec splitfin ( Girardinichthys viviparus ) , known locally as mexcalpique , is a species of fish in the Goodeidae family endemic to Mexico .
Sowell 's short - tailed bat ( Carollia sowelli ) is a common bat species in the family Phyllostomidae .
The Turner 's eremomela ( Eremomela turneri ) is a species of bird formerly placed in the `` Old World warbler '' assemblage , but now placed in the family Cisticolidae .
Blanford 's toad ( Amietophrynus blanfordii ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Aplousobranchia is an order of sea squirts in the class Ascidiacea .
The Pacific bluefin tuna ( Thunnus orientalis ) is a predatory species of tuna found widely in the northern Pacific Ocean , but it is migratory and also recorded as a visitor to the south Pacific .
The Mauritius grey white - eye ( Zosterops mauritianus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Scrobicularia is a genus of bivalve mollusc belonging to the family Semelidae .
The Halfmoon triggerfish , Sufflamen chrysopterum , is a triggerfish of the tropical Indo - West Pacific area .
Giesbertia rugosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Giesbertia .
Horned gophers are extinct rodents from the genus Ceratogaulus , a member of the extinct fossorial rodent family Mylagaulidae .
The Arctic flounder ( Liopsetta glacialis ) is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
The Chatham pigeon , Chatham Island pigeon , or parea ( from Moriori ) ( Hemiphaga chathamensis ) is a bird endemic to the Chatham Islands in New Zealand .
Tiger beetles were traditionally classified as the family Cicindelidae but most authorities now treat them as the subfamily Cicindelinae of the Carabidae ( ground beetles ) .
The Borneo roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros doriae ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Sisal ( /ˈsaɪsəl/ , Spanish : ( siˈsal ) ) , with the botanical name Agave sisalana , is a species of Agave native to southern Mexico but widely cultivated and naturalized in many other countries .
Carnoidea are a superfamily of Acalyptratae flies .
The Lake Rukwa minnow ( Raiamas moorii ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Glinus is a genus of tropical and subtropical plants in the family Molluginaceae .
Brassolini is a tribe usually placed in the brush - footed butterfly subfamily Morphinae , which is often included in the Satyrinae as a tribe Morphini .
Lunovula is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pediculariidae , one of the families of cowry allies .
Androstachys johnsonii , the Lebombo ironwood , is a tree species and the sole member of the genus Androstachys in the Picrodendraceae .
Oechalius ohausi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Oechalius .
The Tucumán amazon ( Amazona tucumana ) , also known as the alder amazon , is a species of parrot in the Psittacidae family .
European lyctus beetle ( Lyctus linearis ) is a species of beetle in the family Bostrichidae .
The Pondoland cannibal snail , scientific name Natalina beyrichi , is a species of medium - sized predatory air - breathing land snail , a carnivorous terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Synteratus ovalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Synteratus .
The Mexican mouse opossum ( Marmosa mexicana ) is a species of Central American opossum in the family Didelphidae .
The Cabanis 's spinetail ( Synallaxis cabanisi ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Lioberus is a genus of mussels in the family Mytilidae .

The South Island giant moa ( Dinornis robustus ) is a member of the moa family .
The Daly Waters frog ( Litoria maculosa formerly Cyclorana maculosa ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .

Megaceros is a genus of hornworts in the family Dendrocerotaceae .
The Columbia spotted frog ( Rana luteiventris ) is a North American species of frog .
Apleurotropis is a genus of hymenopteran insects of the family Eulophidae that is mostly found in Japan .

Grass skippers or banded skippers are butterflies of the subfamily Hesperiinae , part of the skipper family , Hesperiidae .

The Magellanic oystercatcher ( Haematopus leucopodus ) is a species of wader in the family Haematopodidae .
The Turkish hamster ( Mesocricetus brandti ) , also referred to as Brandt 's hamster , Azerbaijani hamster , or avurtlak , is a species of hamster native to Turkey , Armenia and other surrounding nations .
The Amistad gambusia ( Gambusia amistadensis ) was a small fish known only to occur in Goodenough Spring , Val Verde County , Texas , a tributary of the Rio Grande .
The Damara tern ( Sternula balaenarum ) is a species of tern in the family Sternidae .

Macropodinae is a subfamily of marsupials in the family Macropodidae , which includes the kangaroos , wallabies , and related species .

The African giant shrew ( Crocidura olivieri ) is a species of shrew .
Anolis , or anoles , is a genus of iguanian ( anole ) lizards belonging to the family Dactyloidae .
Rough - haired golden moles ( Chrysospalax villosus ) are an ancient group of mammals that live mostly below ground .

Taeniura is a genus of stingrays in the family Dasyatidae , commonly known as ribbontail stingrays .
Adoxaceae is a small family of flowering plants in the order Dipsacales , now comprising five genera and about 150 - 200 species .
Duncker 's pipehorse ( Solegnathus dunckeri ) is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family .
Betula chinensis ( Chinese : 坚桦 ; pinyin : jian hua ) is a species of birch that can be found in China and Korea on the elevation of 700 - -3,000 metres ( 2,300 - -9,800 ft ) .
Named by Lawrence Lambe in 1913 , Styracosaurus is a member of the Centrosaurinae .
The Andean hairy armadillo ( Chaetophractus nationi ) is an armadillo present in Bolivia , in the region of the Puna , the departments of Oruro , La Paz , and Cochabamba ( Gardner , 1993 ) .
The Alaskan tundra wolf ( Canis lupus tundrarum ) , also known as the barren - ground wolf , is a possible subspecies of gray wolf native to the barren grounds of the Arctic Coast region from near Point Barrow eastward toward Hudson Bay and probably northwards to the Arctic Archipelago .
Nototriton , commonly referred to as Moss Salamanders is a genus in the salamander family Plethodontidae , which is characterized by their absence of lungs ; they instead achieve respiration through their skin and the tissues lining their mouth .
Melibe is a genus of sea slugs , nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Tethydidae .
Andasta is a genus of ray spider ( family Theridiosomatidae ) .
Spermodea is a genus of minute , European , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs , or micromolluscs , in the family Valloniidae .
The Juglandaceae are a family , known as the walnut family , of trees , or sometimes shrubs , in the order Fagales .
The African wild ass or African wild donkey ( Equus africanus ) is a wild member of the horse family , Equidae .
Amoaba plumosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Amoaba .
The Fintail serpent eel ( Neenchelys buitendijki , also known commonly as the Spotted worm - eel in India ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Zagrosia is a monotypic genus of bulbous flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae ( also treated as the family Hyacinthaceae ) .
Neita is a butterfly genus from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Chasmosaurus was in 1915 by Lambe within the Ceratopsia assigned to the Chasmosaurinae .
Baer 's pochard ( Aythya baeri ) is a diving duck found in eastern Asia .
Bellamyclus lampetiformis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Bellamyclus .
The Abyssinian roller ( Coracias abyssinicus ) is a member of the roller family of birds which breeds across tropical Africa in a belt south of the Sahara , known as the Sahel .
Micracosmeryx is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species Micracosmeryx chaochauensis , which is known from southern China and northern Vietnam .
The North Island robin ( Petroica longipes ) is a species of Australasian robin endemic to the North Island of New Zealand .
The Pangani suckermouth ( Chiloglanis deckenii ) is a species of upside - down catfish native to Kenya and Tanzania .
Theryola touzalini is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Theryola .
The Tahiti monarch or Tahiti flycatcher ( Pomarea nigra ) is a rare species of bird in the monarch flycatcher family .
Varroa is a genus of parasitic mites associated with honey bees , placed in its own family , Varroidae .
Xiphogymnites is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus from the Triassic included in the family Gymnitidae .
Halophila is a genus of seagrasses in the family Hydrocharitaceae , the tape - grasses .
Cephalocroton is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1841 .
The King of Saxony bird - of - paradise ( Pteridophora alberti ) is a bird in the bird - of - paradise family ( Paradisaeidae ) .
Teuthowenia is a genus of glass squid in the subfamily Taoniinae .
The Namdapha flying squirrel ( Biswamoyopterus biswasi ) is an arboreal , nocturnal flying squirrel endemic to India .
The Tuva silver vole ( Alticola tuvinicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Murray crayfish , Euastacus armatus , is a species of freshwater crayfish endemic to Australia that belongs to the family Parastacidae .
The Azelinini are a tribe of geometer moths in the subfamily Ennominae , with many species in the Southern Hemisphere , particularly in South America .
Argyrocytisus battandieri , the pineapple broom , is a species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Pactolinus is a genus of the Histeridae family of Beetles
Anagaudryceras is an extinct genus of ammonite from the later Cretaceous belonging to the Ammonoidea family Gaudryceratidae .
Kuterintja is an extinct genus of marsupial of the family Ilariidae .
The Parasitiformes are an order of Acari ( treated as a suborder and superorder in outdated classifications ) .
Punalikevirus is a genus of viruses in the order Caudovirales , in the family Myoviridae .
Enneapterygius paucifasciatus , known commonly as the New Caledonian striped triplefin or the Reticulate triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Finned worm eel ( Echelus uropterus , also known as the Finned snake eel in Australia ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
The Asiatic short - tailed shrew ( Blarinella quadraticauda ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Dissopsalis is a genus of extinct predatory mammals of the family Hyaenodontidae .
The genus Asystasia belongs to the family Acanthaceae and comprises approximately 70 species found in the tropics , including the weedy species Asystasia gangetica .
Malcolmia is a genus of flowering plants from the family Brassicaceae .
The Seychelles palm frog ( Sechellophryne pipilodryas ) is a species of frog that is endemic to Silhouette Island in the Seychelles .
Parapionycha lizeri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Parapionycha .
Scops owls are typical owls ( family Strigidae ) mostly belonging to the genus Otus .
Phebalium is a genus of shrubs in the family Rutaceae , endemic to Australia .
The Esmeraldas woodstar , colibrí de Berlepsch , colibrí de esmeraldas , or estrellita Esmeraldeña ( Chaetocercus berlepschi ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Nikolay Kamenskiy ( born October 17 , 1931 in Moscow ) is a Soviet former ski jumper who competed in the late 1950s and early 1960s .
Hryhoriy Surkis ( Ukrainian : Григорій Суркіс ; born September 4 , 1949 in Odessa ) is a Ukrainian businessman and politician , one of five vice - presidents of UEFA since 24 May 2013 .
Abrie Fourie ( born 1969 in Pretoria ) is a South African born artist .
Pauline Hoarau ( born in 1994 , Réunion ) is a French model .
Chatarina Larsson ( born Ingrid Chatarina Larsson ) , a Swedish actress born on 2 April 1947 in Stockholm .
Although frequently associated with Detroit , Kevin Saunderson spent the early years of his life in Brooklyn , New York , before moving to Belleville , Michigan , a rural town some 30 miles from Detroit .
Petra Nareks ( born 27 September 1982 ) is a Slovene judoka from the city of Celje .
Vladimir Grig ( Russian : Владимир Григ ; born March 21 , 1962 , Krasnodar , USSR ) is the pen name of Russian , St. Petersburg - based artist and musician Vladimir Grigoracshenko .

Sarah Boyack ( born 16 May 1961 in Glasgow ) is a Scottish Labour MSP for the Lothian region and formerly constituency MSP for Edinburgh Central in the Scottish Parliament .

Baroness Bethsabée de Rothschild ( assumed the name Batsheva after moving to Israel in 1951 ) , b. September 23 , 1914 in London , d. April 20 , 1999 in Tel Aviv , Israel , was a philanthropist , a patron of dance , and member of the Rothschild banking family .
Moshe Marzouk ( Hebrew : משה מרזוק‎ ; or Musa Lieto Marzuk , Arabic : موسى ليتو مرزوق‎ ; born 20 December 1926 -- 31 January 1955 ) was an Egyptian Karaite Jew , hanged in 1955 for his involvement in a series of terrorist bombings in Cairo codenamed Operation Suzannah .
Leopold Dukes ( Hungarian : Dux Lipót ; 17 January 1810 , Pozsony -- 3 August 1891 , Vienna ) was a Hungarian critic of Jewish literature .
Albert Vigoleis Thelen ( 28 September 1903 in Süchteln , Lower Rhine region , Germany - 9 April 1989 in Dülken , Germany ) was a German author and translator ( from Portuguese ) .
Taddeo Gaddi ( c. 1290 , Florence -- 1366 , Florence ) was a medieval Italian painter and architect .
Pierce Brodkorb ( September 29 , 1908 in Chicago , Illinois -- July 18 , 1992 in Gainesville , Florida ) , also stated as William Pierce Brodkorb , was an American ornithologist and paleontologist .
Kálmán Konrád ( 23 May 1896 in Bácspalánka -- 10 May 1980 in Stockholm , Sweden ) , an inside right , was one of the best football players in the Kingdom of Hungary in the 1910s , and played on the Hungarian National team with his brother , Jenő Konrád .
Benjamin Herschel Babbage ( 6 August 1815 -- 22 October 1878 ) was an English engineer , scientist , explorer and politician , best known for his work in the colony of South Australia .
Ludwig Hopf ( 23 October 1884 in Nürnberg , Germany -- 23 December 1939 in Dublin , Ireland ) was a German - Jewish theoretical physicist who made contributions to mathematics , special relativity , hydrodynamics , and aerodynamics .
Lucos Cozza ( born in Rome , Italy , on 11 April 1921 -- 27 June 2011 ) was a Roman archaeologist .
Wilhelm Ehm ( August 30 , 1918 in Pula , Austro Hungarian Empire -- August 9 , 2009 in Rostock , Germany ) a World War II Wehrmacht veteran and East German Admiral who was Deputy Minister of National Defense of the German Democratic Republic and head of the People 's Navy ( Volksmarine ) .
Luigi Veronesi ( 28 May 1908 in Milan -- 25 February 1998 in Milan ) was an Italian photographer , painter , scenographer and film director .
Carlos Wyld Ospina ( b. Antigua Guatemala , June 19 , 1891 -- Quetzaltenango , June 19 , 1956 ) was a Guatemalan novelist , essayist and poet .
Mohamed Rahmat died on 1 January 2010 in Kuala Lumpur , aged of 71 .
On Brighton 's West Pier , The Great Omani was known for jumping though open flames into a bed of glass .
Baron Ferenc Ottinger ( Sopron , 1792 -- Vienna , 8 April 1869 ) was a Lieutenant General to Franz Josef I of Austria , a Cavalry General and one of the leading generals in the Hungarian Revolution of 1848 .
Born in Byala Slatina to a mother teacher and a father lawyer , Blaga Dimitrova was raised in Veliko Tarnovo and then moved to Sofia .
Ciarán Bourke was born in Dublin on 18 February 1935 , but lived most of his life in Tibradden , County Dublin .
Sigmund Feist ( Mainz , 12 June 1865 - Copenhagen , 23 March 1943 ) was a German Jewish pedagogue and historical linguist .
Christian Joseph Berres Edler von Perez ( 18 March 1796 , Göding - 24 December 1844 , Vienna ) was an Austrian anatomist .
Syd Barrett was born as Roger Keith Barrett in the English city of Cambridge to a middle - class family living at 60 Glisson Road .
Ercole Carzino ( born October 9 , 1901 in Sampierdarena ; died in 1980 ) was a retired Italian professional football player .
Karl Otto Ludwig von Arnim ( August 1 , 1779 in Berlin -- February 9 , 1861 in Berlin ) was a German travel writer .
Juan David Ochoa Vásquez ( c. 1949 -- 25 July 2013 ) was a Colombian drug trafficker and one of the founders of the Medellín Cartel , a major drug trafficking cartel based in the city of Medellín .
Tadeusz Michejda ( 26 September 1879 in Nawsie - 18 May 1956 in Warsaw ) was a Polish physician and politician from the region of Cieszyn Silesia .
Max Fränkel ( Landsberg an der Warthe , 11 March 1846 - Berlin , 10 June 1903 ) was a German classical scholar , philologist , epigrapher and librarian .
Franz Riedel survived the war and died on the 17 May 2001 in Straubing , Germany .
Heinrich Gomperz ( January 18 , 1873 in Vienna , Austria - Hungary -- December 27 , 1942 in Los Angeles , California ) was an Austrian philosopher .
Maarten Maartens , pen name of Jozua Marius Willem van der Poorten Schwartz ( 15 August 1858 in Amsterdam -- 3 August 1915 in Doorn ) , was a Dutch writer , who wrote in English .
Auguste Fickert ( born 25 May 1855 , Vienna - died 9 June 1910 , Maria Enzersdorf , Austria ) was a pioneering Austrian feminist and social reformer .
Glyn Owen died of cancer aged 76 , on 10 September 2004 , in Gwynedd , Wales .
Johann Georg Rosenhain ( 10 June 1816 in Königsberg -- 14 March 1887 Berlin ) was a German mathematician who introduced theta characteristics .
Adrianus Petit Coclico ( Flanders , 1499 -- Copenhagen , after September 1562 ) was a Netherlandish composer of the Renaissance .
Horst Dohlus ( born Plauen 30 May 1925 : died Berlin 28 April 2007 ) was a high ranking SED party functionary in the German Democratic Republic and a member of the country 's National Legislative Assembly ( Volkskammer ) .
William Willard Ashe died on March 18 , 1932 in Washington , D.C. He is buried in Oakwood Cemetery in Raleigh , North Carolina .
Lorimer Johnston ( November 2 , 1858 in Maysville , Kentucky -- February 20 , 1941 in Hollywood , California ) was an American silent film actor and director .
Wilhelm Hanle ( 13 January 1901 -- 29 April 1993 , Gießen ) was a German experimental physicist .

Giacinto Gimignani ( 1606 -- December 9 , 1681 ) was an Italian painter , active mainly in Rome , during the Baroque period .
Gérard Saint ( Renouard , 11 July 1935 -- Le Mans , 16 March 1960 ) was a French professional road bicycle racer .

Stemmops is a genus of small theridiid spiders that mostly occur in America , from the USA to Brazil .
Philodromus bosmansi is a spider species found in Sardinia and Algeria .

Gyrostigma is a genus of botfly which parasitize rhinoceroses .

The Anthaspidellidae are an extinct family of sponges whose dendroclone spicules form ladder - like trabs .
It contains the single species Hestiarcha pyrrhopa , which is found in Australia , where it has been recorded from South Australia .
Larryleachia is a genus of stapeliad succulent flowering plants in the family Asclepiadaceae .
Alvinocarididae is a family of shrimp , originally described by M. L. Christoffersen in 1986 from samples collected by DSV Alvin , from which they derive their name .
Oryzomys is a genus of semiaquatic rodents in the tribe Oryzomyini living in southern North America and far northern South America .
Grindelia oaxacana is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Allium juldusicola is a rare species of wild onion apparently endemic to western part of Xinjiang Province in China .
Elephantopus carolinianus , common names Carolina elephantsfoot or leafy elephant 's foot , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Athrotaxis cupressoides is a species of Athrotaxis , endemic to Tasmania in Australia , where it grows at 700 - -1,300 m altitude .
Cyathea horridula is a species of tree fern native to western New Guinea , where it grows in montane forest at an altitude of approximately 1700 m. It is a rare plant known only from the type locality .
Phyllogonostreptus nigrolabiatus is a common species of millipede found in India .
The Mexican long - tailed shrew ( Sorex oreopolus ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Kurtziella perryae is a species of very small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mangeliidae .
Bulimulus chemitzioides s a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the subfamily Bulimulinae .
Hibiscus lasiocarpos ( also , H. lasiocarpus ) is a species of hibiscus known by the common name hairy - fruited hibiscus .
Orthotylus mariagratiae is a species of bug from the Miridae family that is endemic to Crete .
Prosartes smithii is a North American species of flowering plants known by the common name largeflower fairybells .
Paracristenes fergussoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paracristenes .
Garrya veatchii is a species of flowering shrub known by the common names canyon silktassel and Veatch silktassel .
Diplodonta semiaspera , or the pimpled diplodon , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Ungulinidae .
Abronia turbinata is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common name transmontane sand - verbena .
Orcuttia californica is a rare species of grass known by the common name California Orcutt grass .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Rhipidiomyces acriti .
Dinophysis acuminata is a marine plankton species belonging to the phylum Dinoflagellate that is found in coastal waters of the north Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Amata humeralis is a species of moth of the family Arctiidae It is found in Australia . , where it has been recorded from Western Australia , the Northern Territory , Queensland and New South Wales .
Chaenocephalus aceratus , the blackfin icefish , is a species of crocodile icefish known from around Bouvet Island and the northern Antarctic Peninsula where it occurs at depths of 5 to 770 metres ( 16 to 2,526 ft ) .
Hydrophis bituberculatus , commonly known as Peters ' Sea Snake , is a species of venomous elapid .
Rhopalosomatidae is a family of Hymenoptera containing about 68 extant species in four genera that are found worldwide .
Streptomyces gulbargensis is an alkalitolerant and thermotolerant bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Gulbarga in the Karnataka in India .
Tanipone is a Malagasy genus of ants in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Viguierella is a genus of Madagascan plants in the grass family .
Arta brevivalvalis is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae that is endemic to Arizona .
Atopocottus tribranchius is a species of sculpin native to the Sea of Japan where it is only known from the waters off of Niigata Prefecture .
Gorgonocephalus is a genus of marine basket stars in the class Ophiuroidea .
Acaena juvenca is a species of perennial plant found in scrubland and forest margins up to an altitude of 1200 m on the eastern side of both North and South Islands , New Zealand .
Tumiditarsus cicatricornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Tumiditarsus .
Litoria humboldtorum is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Papua Province of Indonesia , and found on Yapen Island ( its type locality ) as well as on foothills of the Foja Mountains in the mainland New Guinea .
Micropechis ikaheka , commonly known as the New Guinea small - eyed snake or Ikaheka snake , is a highly venomous elapid , the only species in the genus Micropechis .
Acanthophis is a genus of elapid snakes .
Kosmoceras is a moderately evolute ammonite genus from the upper Callovian ( Middle Jurassic ) of Europe with a simple apterure and irregular ribbing interrupted by an irregular row of lateral tubercles .
Hoplorana is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Hoplorana Hoplorana attenuata Fairmaire , 1898 Hoplorana fuscovestita Breuning , 1970 Hoplorana mussardi Breuning , 1957 Hoplorana parterufa Breuning , 1980 Hoplorana quadricristata Fairmaire , 1896 Hoplorana vadoni Breuning , 1957 subgenus Parhoplorana Hoplorana nigroscutata Fairmaire , 1905
Callionymus tethys is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific waters around New Caledonia .
Melianthus comosus ( honey flower ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Melianthaceae .
Paraenicodes annulifer is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraenicodes .
The Myxobolidae are a family of myxosporean parasites which typically infect freshwater fishes , and includes the economically significant species , Myxobolus cerebralis .
Zelkova sicula is a species of Zelkova in the family Ulmaceae , endemic to Sicily .
Panicum decompositum , known by the common names native millet , Australian millet , papa grass , and umbrella grass , is a species of grass native to the inland of Australia .
Causus resimus is a venomous viper species found in isolated populations distributed across tropical Africa .
Ischnura genei , the island bluetail damselfly , is a species of damselfly that replaces the blue - tailed damselfly on some Mediterranean islands ( e.g. , Corsica and Sardinia , where the two species are not known to coexist ) - it is found on four islands .
Oligonychus sacchari , the sugarcane mite , yellow mite or sugarcane yellow mite , is a species of mite .
Nebria cordicollis heeri is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Switzerland .
Aloe falcata is a species of aloe .
Ocypode brevicornis is a species of ghost crabs native to the Indian Ocean , from the Gulf of Oman to the Nicobar Islands .
Cosmetalepas concatenata , common name the pitted keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Aiolocaria hexaspilota is a beetle species from the lady beetle family ( Coccinellidae ) ; adults can be as large as 13 mm long .
Diplotomodon ( meaning `` double cutting tooth '' ) is a dubious genus of reptile , possibly a theropod dinosaur , from New Jersey .
Baccharis klattii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family that is endemic to Ecuador .
Torulaspora delbrueckii is a ubiquitous yeast species with both wild and anthropic habitats .
Dimorphotheca is a genus of plants in the sunflower family , native to Africa and Australia .
Astroboa is a genus of basket stars in the class Ophiuroidea .
Conus striatus , common name the striated cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Aspidura guentheri , commonly known as Günther 's rough - sided snake or කුඩා මැඩිල්ලා ( kuda medilla ) in Sinhala , is a species of colubrid snake endemic to Sri Lanka .
Ctenium elegans is an annual grass species in the genus Ctenium from African savanna areas .
Ptilotus is a genus of mostly perennial herbs or shrubs in the family Amaranthaceae .
Careproctus pallidus is a species of snailfish found around Tierra del Fuego in the far south of South America .
Larra anathema is a species of parasitoid wasps belonging to the family Crabronidae .
Libanopristis is an extinct genus of sawfish belonging to the family Sclerorhynchidae .
Mikadotrochus beyrichii , common name Beyrich 's slit shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Paladilhia hungarica is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Bubas bubalus is a species of beetle of the subfamily Scarabaeinae within the family Scarabaeidae .
Remya mauiensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Maui remya .
' Hemipterochilus ' is a palearctic genus of potter wasps .
Vitis tsoii is a species of wild grape in the Vitaceae family .
Bothrops lojanus , or the Lojan lancehead , is a species of venomous pit viper in the Viperidae family .
Hydrophis klossi , commonly known as Kloss 's sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Poa sieberiana , commonly known as grey tussock - grass and snow grass , is a species of tussock grass that is endemic to Australia .
Gasterophilus is a genus of parasitic flies in the family Oestridae which includes the horse botfly .
Cleomella brevipes is a species of flowering plant in the cleome family known by the common name shortstalk stinkweed .
Tabanus cordiger also known as the plain - eyed grey horsefly is a species of biting horse - fly .
Gigaspermaceae are a family of mosses in subclass Funariidae .
Draba densifolia is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known as the denseleaf draba .
Mesoraphidiidae is an extinct family of snakeflies in the suborder Raphidiomorpha .
Ciulfina klassi is a species of praying mantis in the genus Ciulfina in the order Mantodea .
Chartergellus is a genus of eusocial wasps of Epiponini with ten described species .
The Perote ground squirrel ( Xerospermosphilus perotensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Tuber macrosporum , commonly known as the smooth black truffle , is a species of edible truffle in the family Tuberaceae .
Alternanthera caracasana is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common names khakiweed , washerwoman and mat chaff flower .
Vandeleuria is a small genus of rodent from Asia with only three species .
Thalassius albocinctus , commonly called the fishing spider , is a species of spider found in tropical Asia from India to the Philippines .
Aristolochia longa ( Long Aristolochia , Sarrasine ) is a species of pipevine .
Penicillium flavigenum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces penitrem A , penicillin and roquefortine C.
Reymondia minor is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Paludomidae .
Batyrosaurus is an extinct genus of herbivorous basal hadrosauroid dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous Bostobinskaya Formation ( Santonian to Campanian stage ) of central Kazakhstan .
Osphronemus laticlavius , common name Giant red tail gourami , is a species of gourami belonging to the family Osphronemidae .

Phonodus is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile .
Arisaema jacquemontii is a species of flowering plant from Araceae family that can be found growing on rocky slopes and in the forests on the elevation of 2,400 - -4,000 metres ( 7,900 - -13,100 ft ) in ' Afghanistan , East Asia and Himalayas .
Crocidium multicaule is a species of plants in the daisy family known by the common name spring gold .
Calliophis bibroni , commonly known as Bibron 's coral snake , is a species of venomous elapid snake , which is native to India .
Prothalotia flindersi , common name the Flinders top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Escobaria missouriensis , the Missouri foxtail cactus and formerly Coryphantha missouriensis , is a species of low - growing North American cacti .
Granatellus is a genus of bird previously placed in the family Parulidae , although biochemical evidence suggests it belongs in Cardinalidae , a move followed by the American Ornithologists ' Union in 2009 .
Bulla quoyii , or the brown bubble snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Bullidae , the bubble snails .
Euposauridae was a family of lizards from the Jurassic of Europe .
Eucalyptus muelleriana , commonly known as Yellow Stringybark , is a species of Eucalyptus which is native to New South Wales and Victoria in Australia .

The Horned Dendrobium ( Dendrobium ceraula ) is a species of orchid endemic to the island of Luzon in the Philippines .
Dicerandra cornutissima is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name longspurred mint , longspurred balm , and Robin 's mint .
Oxystelma is a genus of flowering plants of the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1810 .
This genus was named and described in 2008 by its discoverer Rico Stecher ; the type species is Raeticodactylus filisurensis .
Aioliops is a genus of dartfishes native to the central western Pacific Ocean .

Epichirostenotes is a genus of oviraptorosaurian dinosaur from the late Cretaceous .
Neorhodomela larix , commonly known as black pine , is a species of red algae native to coastal areas of the North Pacific , from Mexico to the Bering Sea to Japan .
The genus name Bonitasaura refers to the fossil quarry 's name , `` La Bonita '' , while the name of the type species , B. salgadoi , pays homage to Leonardo Salgado , a renowned Argentine palaeontologist .

Cornus suecica ( dwarf cornel or bunchberry ) is a species of flowering plant in the dogwood family Cornaceae , native to cool temperate and subarctic regions of Europe and Asia , and also locally in extreme northeastern and northwestern North America .
Lonicera fragrantissima is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common names winter honeysuckle , fragrant honeysuckle , January jasmine , Chinese honeysuckle , kiss - me - at - the - gate , and sweet breath of spring .
Drosera filiformis , commonly known as the Thread - leaved sundew , is a small , insectivorous , rosette forming species of perennial herb .
Doryrhamphus janssi , commonly known as the Janss ' pipefish , is a species of pipefish belonging to the family Syngnathidae .
Grevillea neurophylla , commonly known as Granite Grevillea , is a shrub species in the family Proteaceae .
Hibiscus dasycalyx is a species of hibiscus known by the common name Neches River rosemallow .
Arctosaurus ( meaning `` arctic lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of reptile originally classified as a small reptile of unknown affinities , but was often classified as a sauropodomorph dinosaur in the years to follow .
Mammillaria dioica , also called the strawberry cactus , California fishhook cactus , strawberry pincusion or fishhook cactus , is a cactus species of the genus Mammillaria .
Pleuronectes is a genus of righteye flounders found in the northern oceans .
Chaenopsis schmitti , the Yellow - mouth pikeblenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern central Pacific ocean .

Diala semistriata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Dialidae .
Trifolium howellii is a species of clover known by the common names canyon clover and Howell 's clover .
Lupinus adsurgens is a species of lupine known by the common name Drew 's silky lupine .

Chama macerophylla , or the leafy jewel box clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae .
The Cosmosoma cardinale is described as a day - flying moth , meaning that unlike most species of moth it is active during the day and sleeps at night .
Calliomorpha cyanoptera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Calliomorpha .

Dialidae , common name dialids , is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Cambarus pecki ( formerly Procambarus pecki ) , sometimes called the phantom cave crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Abbasites is an extinct ammonite genus from the early Middle Jurassic included in the ammonitid family Erycitidae .
Ceroxys fraudulosa is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Ceroxys of the family Ulidiidae .
Fragaria orientalis is a diploid species of wild strawberry native to E. Asia - Eastern Siberia .
The Thiotrichaceae are a family of Proteobacteria , including Thiomargarita namibiensis , the largest known bacterium .
Triphasia is a small genus of three species in the family Rutaceae , related to Citrus .
Ruppia megacarpa is a submerged herb species in the genus Ruppia found in shallow brackish waters .

Sand stargazers are blennioids ; perciform marine fish of the family Dactyloscopidae .
Wardia is a monotypic genus of mosses in the subclass Dicranidae ; it contains only the species Wardia hygrometrica , `` an aquatic moss endemic to the Western Cape province of South Africa . ''
Scotophilus is a genus of vespertilionid bats commonly called yellow bats .
