Chinchilla rats or chinchillones are members of the family Abrocomidae .
Melica radula is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Chinese provinces such as Jilin , Lea and Shanxi in grassy mountain slopes and forests that are full with Larch species on the elevation of 300 - -1,200 metres ( 980 - -3,940 ft ) .
Ernstichthys is a genus of banjo catfishes that occurs in the Amazon and Orinoco basins .
Omicroides is a monotypic Indomalayan genus of potter wasps .
The Russulales are an order of the Agaricomycetes , ( which include the agaric genera Russula and Lactarius and their polyporoid and corticioid relatives ) .
Plesiocystiscinae is a subfamily of minute sea predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the infraorder Neogastropoda .
The Stygnopsidae are a small family of harvestmen , with almost all species found in Mexico .
Pierreclanis is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Pierreclanis admatha , which is known from Guinea , Ivory Coast , Cameroon , the Central African Republic , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , the Republic of the Congo , Gabon and Ghana .
Carabus sylvestris is a species of either black or brown - coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Czech Republic , Hungary , Italy , Liechtenstein , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Ukraine , and the Netherlands .
Leptobarbus melanopterus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Leptobarbus from the Kapuas River basin in Borneo .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single polypore species Bridgeoporus nobilissimus , first described to science in 1949 .
Erigeron flabellifolius is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names fan - leaf fleabane .
Mychonoa is a genus of moths of the Yponomeutidae family .
Liolaemus gravenhorstii , commonly known as Gravenhorst 's tree iguana , is a species of lizard in the family Iguanidae .
The Labyrinthulomycetes ( ICBN ) or Labyrinthulea ( ICZN ) , are a class of protists that produce a network of filaments or tubes , which serve as tracks for the cells to glide along and absorb nutrients for them .
The family Dipluridae , known as funnel - web tarantulas , are a group of spiders in the infraorder Mygalomorphae , that have two pairs of booklungs , and chelicerae ( fangs ) that move up and down in a stabbing motion .
Rhyticeros is a genus of medium to large hornbills ( Bucerotidae family ) found in forests from Southeast Asia to the Solomons .
Micromeryx is an extinct genus of musk deer that lived in the Miocene .
†Partula remota was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Bolma aureola , common name the golden turbo shell or the scaly star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Cornus piggae is an extinct species of dogwood known from fossil fruits found in Late Paleocene sediments exposed in the state of North Dakota , USA .
Herichthys is a small genus of cichlid fishes .
Grammoplites is a genus of flatheads native to the western Pacific Ocean and the Indian Ocean .
Agave stricta ( common names hedgehog agave , rabo de léon ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to Puebla and Oaxaca in Southern Mexico .
Echinorhynchidae is a family of acanthocephalan parasitic worms from the order Echinorhynchida .
Portunus is a genus of crab which includes several important species for fisheries , such as the blue swimming crab , Portunus pelagicus and the Gazami crab , P. trituberculatus .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Buxetroldia bisaccata , described as new to science in 1997 .
Odostomia laevigata , common name the ovoid odostome , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The Charaxinae , the leafwings , are a nymphalid subfamily of butterflies that includes about 400 species , inhabiting mainly the tropics , although some species extend into temperate regions in North America , Europe , China , and southern Australia .
Elacatinus horsti , the Yellowline goby , is a species of goby native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea .
Tiger parrots are members of the genus Psittacella in the Psittaculidae family .
Vicente 's poison frog ( Oophaga vicentei ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family that is endemic to the Veraguas and Coclé Provinces of central Panama .
Stillingia spinulosa is a species of flowering plant in the euphorb family known by the common name annual toothleaf .
Streptomyces canchipurensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from a limestone habitat in Manipur in India .
Athearnia anthonyi is a rare species of freshwater snail in the family Pleuroceridae .
Adiantum myriosorum is a fern species very similar to Adiantum pedatum .
Senecio inaequidens , known as narrow - leaved ragwort and South African ragwort , is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae .
Streptomyces echinoruber is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which was isolated from soil in Argentina .
It contains the single species Gylla crotalistria , which is found in Brazil .
The minute tree - fungus beetles , family Ciidae , are a sizeable group of beetles which inhabit Polyporales bracket fungi or coarse woody debris .
Lactobacillus salivarius is a probiotic bacteria species that has been found to live in the gastrointestinal tract and exert a range of therapeutic properties including suppression of pathogenic bacteria .
Aspergillus clavatus is a species of Aspergillus with conidia dimensions 3 - -4.5 x 2.5 - -4.5 μms .
Aralia cordata is a species of Aralia in the Araliaceae family .
Sympycnus elegans is a fly species in the genus Sympycnus .
Hormathiidae is a family of sea anemones in the class Anthozoa .
Myrialepis is a monotypic genus of flowering plant in the palm family native to Southeast Asia , where the only species Myrialepis paradoxa is colloquially called rotan kertong , or simply rattan .
Similiparma lurida also known as the Canary damsel is a species of marine fish of the family Pomacentridae .
Oligoryzomys is a genus of rodents in the tribe Oryzomyini of family Cricetidae .
Lepidotarphius perornatella is a species of sedge moths , and the only species in the genus Lepidotarphius .
Cleobora mellyi , the Tasmanian ladybird or southern ladybird is a ladybird species endemic to Tasmania and also found in the southern states of mainland Australia .
Pulchrodiboma ochreovittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pulchrodiboma .
The Beyşehir bleak ( Alburnus akili ) , known in Turkish as gökçe balığı , was a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family , now presumed extinct .
Lantana montevidensis is a species of lantana known by many common names , such as : trailing lantana , weeping lantana , creeping lantana , small lantana , purple lantana or trailing shrubverbena .
Leus ramuli is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Leus .
It was described by Latreille , in 1809 , and contains the species Amphiderita pyrospila .
Volutidae , common name volutes , are a taxonomic family of predatory sea snails that range in size from 9 mm to over 500 mm , marine gastropod mollusks .
Succineidae are a family of small to medium - sized , air - breathing land snails ( and slugs ) , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs .
Pseudohomaloptera is a genus of ray - finned fish in the family Balitoridae .
Mauritia arabica , common name the Arabian cowry , is a species of cowry , a sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Tyrannochromis nigriventer is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers rocky shallows .
Carandaisuchus is an extinct genus of caiman .
Orthotrichum scanicum is a species of moss in the Orthotrichaceae family .
Carolinochelys is an extinct genus of sea turtle from Oligocene of United States .
Frondipedia charma is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Frondipedia .
Dracontium is a genus of flowering plants similar to those of Amorphophallus .
Nebria vanvolxemi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Portugal .
Pachydictyum globosum is a species of freshwater sponge in the family Malawispongiidae .
Homonotus sanguinolentus , the Bloody Spider - hunting Wasp is a European species of Pompilid wasp .
Maytenus cymosa ( also called Caribbean mayten ) is a species of plant in the Celastraceae family .
Lipaphis erysimi is a species of aphid of the family Aphididae .
Megachile bruchi is a species of bee in the family Megachilidae , making it a cousin of the alfalfa leafcutter bee ( Megachile rotundata ) .
Trochaclis antarctica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ataphridae .
Flaveria sonorensis is a rare Mexican plant species of yellowtops within the sunflower family .
Dermanyssus gallinae ( also known as the red mite , poultry mite , red poultry mite , roost mite and chicken mite ) is an ectoparasite of poultry and other bird species .
Anomotodon is an extinct genus of shark related to the extant goblin shark ( Mitsukurina owstoni ) .
Lycodryas is a genus of lamprophiid snakes .
Margarella whiteana is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae , the top snails .
As with many described extinct taxa , it is the only known species in its genus Caririemys .
Mosquitoes are small , midge - like flies which comprise the family Culicidae .
Sphallenum tuberosum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Sphallenum .
Raorchestes travancoricus , variously known as the Travancore bushfrog , Travancore bubble - nest frog , or Travancore tree frog , is a species of frog in the family Rhacophoridae .
Truncilla truncata , common name the Deertoe , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
Pinecone fishes are small and unusual beryciform marine fish of the family Monocentridae .
Aponogeton crispus is an aquatic plant species .
The species Grapsus grapsus and G. adscensionis were not separated until 1990 .
Pilina unguis is an extinct species of Paleozoic Silurian monoplacophoran .
Longichela orobica is an extinct species of prawn which lived in the Norian , and is the only species in the genus Longichela .
Meiacanthus phaeus is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Mentzelia pectinata is a species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common name San Joaquin blazingstar .
Leiomitra is a genus of liverworts .
Zeltnera muehlenbergii is a species of annual herb commonly known as Monterey centaury and Muhlenberg 's centaury .
Lilium martagon ( martagon lily or Turk 's cap lily ) is a Eurasian species of lily .
Akkermansia muciniphila is a species of human intestinal mucin - degrading bacterium , the type species for a new genus , Akkermansia , proposed in 2004 by Muriel Derrien and others .
Ascocentrum ampullaceum is a species of orchid found in central China , Assam India , Bangladesh , the Himalayas , Nepal , Bhutan , Sikkim , Andaman Islands , Myanmar , Thailand , Laos and Vietnam .
Roystonea is a genus of eleven species of monoecious palms , native to the Caribbean Islands , and the adjacent coasts of Florida and Central and northern South America .
Lupinus dalesiae is a species of lupine known by the common name Quincy lupine .
Aralosaurini is a tribe of basal lambeosaurine hadrosaurs endemic to Eurasia .
The bullseye snakehead or great snakehead ( Channa marulius ) is a large species of snakehead native to South and Southeast Asia , as well as southern China .
Scaevatula pellisserpentis is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Pupinella is a genus of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cyclophoroidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Monoscutidae are a family of harvestmen with 32 known species that all occur in or near Australia and New Zealand .
Manfreda scabra is one of the larger Manfreda species , with rosettes growing 0.7 - -1 metre ( 2.3 - -3.3 ft ) in height and 1.5 - -2 metres ( 4.9 - -6.6 ft ) in width .
Linanthus watsonii ( syn . Leptodactylon watsonii ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Watson 's prickly phlox .
Probelesodon is an extinct genus of chiniquodontid cynodont .
Inocybe maculata , commonly known as the frosty fibrecap , is a species of mushroom in the Inocybaceae family .
Fimbristylis miliacea , the grasslike fimbry , is a species of fimbry that probably originated in coastal tropical Asia but has since spread to most continents as an introduced species .
Paraschistura naseeri is a species of stone loach endemic to Pakistan .
The Hausa mouse ( Mus haussa ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Plagiocephalus lobularis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Plagiocephalus of the family Ulidiidae .
Rice tenrecs are the two species in the Malagasy genus Oryzorictes .
Clubiona vegeta is a sac spider species found in Europe , Central Asia , North Africa and the Canary Islands .
Conus papilliferus , common name the papilla cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies.p Like all species within the genus Conus , these snails are predatory and venomous .
The Phoridae are a family of small , hump - backed flies resembling fruit flies .
Mammillaria magnimamma , common name Mexican Pincushion , is a species of plant in the Cactaceae family .
Cucumbers may also be pollinated by bumblebees and several other bee species .
The Blephariceromorpha are an infraorder of nematoceran flies , including three families associated with fast - flowing , high - mountain streams , where the larvae can be found .
Grevillea elbertii is a tree species in the family Proteaceae .
Pictocolumbella ocellata , common name : the lightning dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Shorea affinis is a plant species in the Dipterocarpaceae family endemic to Sri Lanka .
Muhlenbergia torreyana is a species of grass known by the common names New Jersey muhly , Torrey 's muhly , and Torrey 's dropseed .
Dipterocarpus hispidus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Chrysiptera rex is a species of damselfish known by the common name king demoiselle .
Pommereulla is a genus of Indian and Sri Lankan plants in the grass family .
Angolatitan ( `` Angolan giant '' ) is a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Upper Cretaceous and the first dinosaur discovered in Angola .
Ormosia howii , the Hainan ormosia , is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family native to southern China .
Calliotropis ottoi , common name Otto 's spiny margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliotropidae .
Odontoglossum naevium , the Spotted Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid found from Colombia to Guyana .
Vasconcellea quercifolia ( commonly known as the oak leaf papaya ) is a species of Vasconcellea found in Bolivia and Ecuador .
Ophiclinus is a genus of clinids native to the coastal waters around Australia .
The Bordered Knob - tipped shadowdamsel , ( Drepanosticta submontana ) is a species of damselfly in the family Platystictidae .
Beschorneria yuccoides is a species of succulent plants belonging to the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Agavoideae .
Sivapithecus ( Shiva 's Ape ) is a genus of extinct apes .
Corumbataia britskii is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in small tributaries of the Sucuriú River , upper Paraná River Basin in the state of Mato Grosso do Sul .
Callionima denticulata is a species of moth in the family Sphingidae , which is known from Panama , Mexico , Costa Rica , Nicaragua , Bolivia , Peru and western Venezuela .
The Karoo lark ( Calendulauda albescens ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Centrophorus is a genus of squaliform sharks .
Praonethomimus tuberosithorax is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Praonethomimus .
Echinometra viridis , the reef urchin , is a species of sea urchin in the family Echinometridae .
Abralia andamanica is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod native to the Indian Ocean and Pacific Ocean .
Afronemacheilus is a genus of stone loaches endemic to Ethiopia .
Pyrrhalta is a genus of beetles in the leaf beetle family , Chrysomelidae .
Chikila is a genus of amphibian in the order Gymnophiona ( caecilians ) .
Tenrhynea is a genus of Southern African plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the sunflower family .
Efraasia ( pronounced `` E - FRAHS - ee - A '' ) is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur .
It contains the single species Deua imbutana , which is found on Haiti .
Hordelymus is a genus of European , north African , and southwest Asian plants in the grass family .
Campylomyces is a genus of wood - rotting fungi in the family Gloeophyllaceae .
Encephalartos dolomiticus is a species of cycad that is found near Penge in the Wolkberg in southeastern Limpopo Province , South Africa at elevations of 1100 - -1500 meters .
Iris juncea ( commonly called the rush iris ) is a smooth - bulbed bulbous iris species .
Chaerophyllum procumbens is listed as an endangered species by the state of New York .
Adelosebastes latens is a species of rockfish native to the northern Pacific Ocean where it is found on the Emperor Seamounts at depths of from 900 to 1,200 metres ( 3,000 to 3,900 ft ) .
Rhinella bergi is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae that is found in Argentina , Brazil , and Paraguay .
Waianae Range labordia ( Labordia kaalae ) is a species of flowering plant in the Loganiaceae family .
Gonystylus pendulus is a species of plant in the Thymelaeaceae family .
Alligatorium is an extinct genus of atoposaurid crocodylomorph .
Monetaria caputserpentis , common name the serpent's - head cowry , is a species of cowry , a sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Trichomycterus maracaiboensis is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Venezuela , where it occurs in the San Juan river , a tributary to the Motatán river in the Lake Maracaibo basin .
Ischiopsopha plana is a species of beetles from the family Scarabaeidae , subfamily Cetoniinae , tribe Schizorhinini .
The Kashmir Rock Agama ( Laudakia tuberculata ) is a species of agamid lizard found in N Pakistan , India ( W Himalaya , Kashmir , Punjab ) , Nepal ( Kathmandu ) , Afghanistan , and China ( Tibetan Plateau ) .
Malagassodynerus is a genus of potter wasps endemic to Madagascar .
Elaphoglossum serpens is a rare species of fern that grows only on Cerro de Punta , the highest mountain in Puerto Rico .
Lycaste aromatica , common name The Sweet Scented Lycaste , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Lycaste , belonging to the Orchidaceae family .
Pyracantha rogersiana ( Asian firethorn ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Rosaceae , native to western China .
Ribes speciosum is a species of gooseberry with elongate , red flowers that resemble those of fuchsia ; its common name is fuchsia - flowered gooseberry .
Archolaemus is a genus of glass knifefishes .
Labidochromis mbenjii is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur in the area around the Mbenji Islands .

Aardonyx ( Afrikaans aard , `` earth '' + Greek onux , `` nail , claw '' ) is a genus of prosauropod dinosaur .

Eubranchus cingulatus is a species of sea slug or nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Eubranchidae .
Ixodes canisuga , the dog tick , is a species of tick in the family Ixodidae that can be found in Russia and throughout Europe where it feeds on foxes , cats , dogs , horses , badgers and sheep .
Eurycantha horrida , the thorny devil walking stick , is a species belonging to the stick insects ( order Phasmatodea ) and to the family Phasmatidae .
Hypsicalotes is a genus of the family Agamidae having a single species Hypsicalotes kinabaluensis found in Indonesia and Malaysia .
Stonogobiops is a genus of gobies native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .

Nelumbo lutea is a species of flowering plant in the monotypic family Nelumbonaceae .

Sargocentron spiniferum , common name sabre squirrelfish , giant squirrelfish and spiny squirrelfish , is a large Indo - Pacific species of squirrelfish belonging to the family Holocentridae .
The genus Paradisaea consists of seven species of birds - of - paradise ( family Paradisaeidae ) .
Trientalis is a small genus of flowering plants containing three species known as starflowers or wintergreens .

Tubularia is a genus of hydroids that appear to be furry pink tufts or balls at the end of long strings , thus causing them to be sometimes be called `` pink - mouthed '' or `` pink - hearted '' hydroids .
Woolley 's false antechinus ( Pseudantechinus woolleyae ) , also known as Woolley 's pseudantechinus , is a species of small carnivorous marsupial belonging to the family Dasyuridae .

Cyphocarpus is a genus of flowering plants in the Campanulaceae .
The Giluwe rat ( Rattus giluwensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Hesperelaea is a plant genus with only one species , probably now extinct .
Albizia berteriana ( Bertero Albizia ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Chaerophyllum bulbosum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by several common names , including turnip - rooted chervil , tuberous - rooted chervil , bulbous chervil , and parsnip chervil .

Nigritella is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
Sitticus fasciger is a species of spider from the Salticidae family indigenous to north and west Asia but now introduced to North America .

Tetrapteron graciliflorum is a species of evening primrose known by the common name hill suncup .

Platystrophia is an extinct genus of brachiopod that lived from the Ordovician to the Silurian in Asia , Europe , North America , and South America .
Sardinella richardsoni ( Richardson 's sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella from the South China Sea in the northwest Pacific .
Brodiaea terrestris ( dwarf brodiaea ) is a species of plant in the genus Brodiaea that is native to California and Oregon .
Acacia obliquinervia , known colloquially as mountain hickory , is a species of Acacia native southern New South Wales and Victoria in eastern Australia .
Onychogomphus forcipatus , the small pincertail or green - eyed hook - tailed dragonfly , is a species of dragonflies belonging to the family Gomphidae .
Sepia bathyalis is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean , specifically northwestern and southwestern Madagascar .
Moraea bellendenii is a species of plant in genus Moraea that was named after John Bellenden , the English botanist .
Asperitas inquinata is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Dyakiidae .
Maratus volans is a species in the jumping spider family , belonging to the peacock spider genus .
Griselda 's lemniscomys or Griselda 's striped grass mouse ( Lemniscomys griselda ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Huahine gull ( Chroicocephalus utunui ) , also known as the Society Islands gull , is an extinct bird , a species of gull of which subfossil bones were found at the Fa'ahia archeological site on Huahine , in the Society Islands of French Polynesia .
Allium siskiyouense is a North American species of wild onion known by the common name Siskiyou onion .

Guihaia is a genus of two species of palms found in China and Vietnam .
The bird family Sulidae comprises the gannets and boobies .

Genlisea aurea is one of the largest carnivorous species in the genus Genlisea ( family Lentibulariaceae ) .
Coccyzidae is a family of birds comprising 18 new world cuckoos , ranging from Canada to Argentina .

Leucisca is a genus of crabs in the family Leucosiidae .
Stenodema laevigata is a species of bugs from a Miridae family , common in the United Kingdom , and throughout the rest of Europe .

Callionima acuta is a species of moth in the family Sphingidae , which is known from Peru and Bolivia .
Orthodera novaezealandiae , known as the New Zealand mantis or the New Zealand praying mantis , is a species of praying mantis which is , as both the scientific name and common names suggest , indigenous and endemic to New Zealand .

Amphiprion latezonatus , also known as the wide - band anemonefish , is a species of anemonefish found in subtropical waters off the east coast of Australia ..
Endodonta apiculata is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Endodontidae , an endemic family of land snails from the Hawaiian islands .
Iconaster longimanus , the icon star or double star , is a species of starfish in the family Goniasteridae .
Ficus scobina is one of several fig species commonly known as sandpaper fig . It is native to northern Australia , from the Kimberleys across to north Queensland .

Neovison is a genus of mustelids , including the extinct sea mink and the extant American mink .
It contains only one species , Planovalvata roseivena , which was described by Hampson in 1894 .

Umbonia crassicornis is a common and widespread member of the insect family Membracidae , and one of numerous species colloquially referred to as thorn bugs .
Dioryctria yatesi , the mountain pine coneworm , is a species of snout moth in the genus Dioryctria .
Stichodactyla gigantea , commonly known as the giant carpet anemone is a species of sea anemone that lives in the Indo - Pacific area , with a diameter usually no larger than 50 centimetres ( 1.6 ft ) and a maximum of 80 centimetres ( 2.6 ft ) .

Microsoreae is a tribe of ferns with clathrate scales , thin exospores , and monomorphic fronds .
Alicia mirabilis ( commonly known as Berried Anemone ) is a sea anemone species in the genus Alicia which changes shape as night falls expanding its column and tentacles to catch its food .

Thamnophilus is a genus of antbird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Agallidwipa is a genus of leafhopper from Madagascar
Delphinium recurvatum is a species of larkspur known by the common names Byron larkspur , recurved larkspur , and valley larkspur .
Cryphonectria is a fungal genus in the order Diaporthales .
Sedum radiatum is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family known by the common name Coast Range stonecrop .
Eucalyptus cameronii , the diehard stringybark is a species of eucalyptus of eastern Australia .
Megalorhipida pseudodefectalis is a species of moth in the genus Megalorhipida , known from Argentina , Brazil , Chile , and Paraguay .
Amphimallon burmeisteri is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Croatia , France , Hungary , Italy , Kosovo , Montenegro , Serbia , Slovenia and Voivodina .
Halichoeres chrysus , commonly called the canary wrasse , golden wrasse or yellow wrasse , is a fish species in the wrasse family native to central Indo - Pacific area .
Boninthemis is a monotypic genus of dragonflies in the family Libellulidae containing the single species Boninthemis insularis .
Diploria clivosa , the knobby brain coral , is a colonial species of stony coral in the family Mussidae .
Beroe cucumis is a species of comb jelly in the family Beroidae .
Allium plummerae is a species of plant native to southern Arizona ( Pima and Cochise Counties ) in the United States and to Sonora in Mexico .
Peltopleuriformes were an extinct order of prehistoric bony fish .
Cyathea acrostichoides is a species of tree fern native to the Maluku Islands and Western New Guinea , where it grows in forest and disturbed sites at an altitude of 650 - -1100 m. The trunk is erect and usually 1 - -3 m tall .
Berycopsis is an extinct genus of beardfish from the Cretaceous period .
Farlowella venezuelensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Guarapiche River basin and the lower Orinoco River basin .
Ixodes kaiseri is an Old World species of ixodid tick that parasitizes badgers , foxes , steppe polecats , raccoon dogs , and common hedgehogs in forest habitats and along heavily overgrown riverbanks and depressions in steppe habitats ; they have also been collected from domestic dogs visiting these habitats .
Cyrtodactylus aravallensis is a species of gecko found in the Delhi Ridge in India .
Aplocheilus parvus , the dwarf panchax , is a species of killifish native to India and Sri Lanka .
Lucidella plicatula is a species of land snail with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Helicinidae .
Joinvillea plicata is a flowering plant species in the genus Joinvillea found in New Caledonia .
It was named by O'Keefe and Wahl in 2003 and the type species is Tatenectes laramiensis .
Isocarpha ( pearlhead ) is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Cyclopterus lumpus , the lumpsucker or lumpfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Cyclopteridae ( lumpsuckers ) .
Atelurinae is a subfamily of primitive insects belonging to the order Thysanura .
Amphimallon ochraceum is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Italy , Spain and the Britain I.
Apostichopus japonicus is a species of sea cucumber in the family Stichopodidae .
Myrmecomantis atra , common name ant mantis , is a species of praying mantis that relies upon ant mimicry for protection even as an adult .
Riostegotherium was an extinct genus of xenarthra from the late Paleocene of Brazil .
Chromodoris quadricolor is a species of very colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusc .
Dryopteris cycadina ( shaggy shield fern or black wood fern ) is a species of deciduous or semi - evergreen fern in the family Dryopteridaceae , native to northern India , China , Taiwan and Japan .
Omma is a genus of beetles in the family Ommatidae .
Ebomegobius goodi is a species of brackish water goby native to a stream in Cameroon .
Allium spirale is a plant species native to Korea , Primorye , and parts of China .
Euophrys monadnock is a species of jumping spider which occurs in the United States and Canada .
Cirsium eriophorum or woolly thistle is a herbaceous biennial species of the genus Cirsium .
Roupala montana is a species of shrub or tree in the Proteaceae which is native to much of the Neotropics .
Gekko ernstkelleri is a species of gecko found on the northwest peninsula of the island of Panay in the Philippines .
Aborichthys tikaderi is a species of stone loach endemic to Arunachal Pradesh , India where it is only known from streams in the Namdapha Wildlife Sanctuary .
Aspius is a genus of Eurasian cyprinid fish , with two recognized species .
The Bolivian tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys boliviensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Stenocara gracilipes , also known as the Fogstand Beetle , is a species of beetle that is native to the Namib Desert of southern Africa .
Haitia is a small genus of two species in the Loosestrife family of plants named for Haiti , the country where it was first collected .
Aconchulinida is an order of amoeba in the sub - class Filosia .
Daphnephila sueyenae is a species of gall midge first associated with leaf galls on Lauraceae species , particularly Machilus thunbergii in Taiwan .
The North American beaver ( Castor canadensis ) is one of two extant beaver species .
Scirpophaga innotata , also called the rice white stemborer , is a species of moth of the Crambidae family .
Carabus hummeli stolidus is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Russia .
Grammatidae is a small family of fishes in the order Perciformes known commonly as basslets .
Bersama swynnertonii is a species of plant in the Melianthaceae family .
Menegazzia dielsii is a species of lichen from New Zealand .
Erebia cyclopius is a species of butterfly of the Satyrinae subfamily in the Nymphalidae family .
Acacia lanigera , commonly known as woolly wattle or hairy wattle , is a tree species that is endemic Australia .
Ponerinae is a subfamily of ants in the Poneromorph subfamilies group , with about 1,600 species in 47 extant genera , including Dinoponera gigantea - one of the world 's largest species of ant .
Selenemys is an extinct genus of pleurosternid turtle from the Late Jurassic of Central West of Portugal .
Perdicella carinella is a species of tropical , tree - living , air - breathing , land snails , arboreal pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
Oligoryzomys fornesi , also known as Fornes ' colilargo , is a species of rodent in the genus Oligoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Jaxtasuchus is an extinct genus of armoured doswelliid archosauriform reptile known from the Middle Triassic ( Ladinian stage ) of the Erfurt Formation , Germany .
Paramphilius is a genus of loach catfishes found in Africa .
Cataulacus simoni , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which is a widespread species that can be found from China , India , and Sri Lanka .
Mimulus alsinoides is a species of monkeyflower known by the common names wingstem monkeyflower and chickweed monkeyflower .
Entyloma dahliae is a species of smut fungus in the family Entylomataceae .
Eleocharis acicularis is a species of spikesedge known by the common names needle spikerush and least spikerush .
Demodex folliculorum is a species of face mite .
Thrinaxodon is an extinct genus of cynodont , most commonly regarded by its species T. liorhinus which lived in what are now South Africa and Antarctica .
Boophis calcaratus ( sometimes called the bright - eyed frog ) is a species of treefrog found in Madagascar .
Acanthocyclops hypogeus is a species of copepod in the family Cyclopidae .
Incodynerus is an andean neotropical genus of potter wasps currently containing 10 recognized species
Streptomyces arenae is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Illinois in the USA .
Birkenia is a genus of extinct anaspid fish from Middle Silurian strata of Northern Europe , and Middle Silurian to possibly Earliest Devonian strata of Arctic Canada .
Euphthiracaridae is a family of mites in the order Oribatida .
Nanorana annandalii ( common names : Annandale 's paa frog , Annandale 's frog , Boulenger 's hill frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Squawfish or pikeminnows are cyprinid fish of the genus Ptychocheilus consisting of four species native to western North America .
Stenelmis canaliculata is a species of beetle from Elminae subfamily which can be found throughout Western Europe .
Nesodynerus is a genus of potter wasps endemic to the Hawaiian archipielago .
Flabellisphinctes is small , evolute ammonite genus from the upper Middle Jurassic ( Callovian ) that lived between 160 and 154 Ma ago .
Calliotropis is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Calliotropidae .
Eugnathogobius is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean region .
Sium burchellii , known commonly as dwarf jellico , is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae .
Mimosiphonops is a genus of amphibian in the Siphonopidae family .
Dasyponyssidae is a small family of mites in the order Mesostigmata .
Spirula spirula is a species of deep - water squid - like cephalopod mollusk .
Agnotocastor galushai is an extinct species of beaver .
Xeronema is a genus of flowering plants containing two species :
Floerkea is a monotypic genus of plants in the meadowfoam family containing the sole species Floerkea proserpinacoides , which is known by the common names false mermaid , false mermaidweed , and floerkea .
Prothoe franck , the blue begum , is a butterfly species found in Assam in northeastern India and throughout a large part of southeast Asia .
Daphnia occidentalis is a species of crustacean in the family Daphniidae .
Siederia is a genus of small moths .
Pardofelis is a genus of the cat family Felidae .
Castilleja levisecta ( The Golden Piantbrush ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common name golden paintbrush , or golden Indian paintbrush , listed under the Endangered Species Act in 1997 .
Valdosaurus ( `` Weald Lizard '' ) is a genus of bipedal herbivorous iguanodont ornithopod dinosaur found on the Isle of Wight and elsewhere in England .
The Gonyaulacales are an order of dinoflagellates .
Neoglyphidodon oxyodon is a species of damselfish in the family Pomacentridae .
Sabal uresana , commonly known as the Sonoran palmetto , is a species of palm tree that is native to the foothills of the Sierra Madre Occidental in northwestern Mexico ( states of Chihuahua and Sonora ) .
Carabus bessarabicus is a species of ground beetle from Carabidae family that can be found in Moldova , Russia and Ukraine .
Gentiana alba ( called plain , pale , white , cream , or yellow gentian ) is a herbaceous species of flowering plant in the Gentian family Gentianaceae , producing yellowish - white colored flowers from thick white taproots .
Pirhosigma is a moderately small neotropical genus of potter wasps .
Downingia ornatissima is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name folded calicoflower .
Lyonia lucida is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common names fetterbush lyonia , hurrahbush , and staggerbush .
Tetraodon schoutedeni is a species of pufferfish native to Africa 's Congo Basin .
Protorothyris is an extinct genus of Early Permian protorothyridid known from Texas and West Virginia of the United States .
Schistura maejotigrina is a species of stone loach , a freshwater fish , from northern Thailand .
Myrsine australis , commonly known as Red Matipo or Mapou is a species of shrub within the family Primulaceae .
Canarium australianum is a species of trees , native to Australia and Papua New Guinea , of the plant family Burseraceae .
Hypsurus caryi , the Rainbow seaperch or Rainbow surfperch is a species of surfperch found along the Pacific coast of North America from Cape Mendocino , California to northern Baja California , Mexico .
Phlomidoschema is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described as a genus in 1941 .
Kunming Nase , Xenocypris yunnanensis , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Xenocypris .
Lepidorhombus is a genus of turbots native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean .
Adelomelon riosi , common name Rios 's volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
The mitochondrial genome of Branchiostoma lanceolatum has been sequenced , and the species serves as a model organism for studying the development of vertebrates .
Sabellaria spinulosa is a species of marine polychaete worm in the family Sabellariidae , commonly known as the Ross worm .
Sclerocactus wetlandicus is a rare species of cactus known by the common name Uinta Basin hookless cactus .
Aphantopus is a butterfly genus of the Satyrinae .
Apsisaurus is an extinct genus of Early Permian varanopid synapsid known from Texas of the United States .
Procranioceras is an extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Palaeomerycidae , endemic to North America from the Miocene epoch , 16.3 - -13.6 Ma , existing for approximately 2.7 million years .
Glarichelys is an extinct genus of sea turtle which was originally considered to be from the middle Oligocene epoch but has more recently come to be considered from the Eocene epoch .
Lasiacis ( smallcane ) is a genus of Neotropical plants in the grass family , found in the Americas from Mexico and Florida south to Argentina .
Prunus mahaleb , the mahaleb cherry or St Lucie cherry , is a species of cherry tree .
Sarcanthopsis is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to various islands of the western Pacific .
Erigeron aequifolius is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Hall 's daisy and Hall 's fleabane .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Petrakiella insignis .
Allium sabulosum is a Eurasian species of wild onion native to European Russia , Kazakhstan , Kyrgyzstan , Iran , Tajikistan , Turkmenistan , Uzbekistan and Xinjiang .
Sicyopus auxilimentus is a species of goby endemic to the Philippines where it is only known to occur in Lagu Lagu Creek on Leyte Island .
Timanophon is an extinct genus of procolophonine procolophonid parareptile from early Triassic deposits of Arkhangelsk , Russia .
Iridomyrmex bigi is a species of ant that is native to several regions of Australia .
Diploschema rotundicolle , citrus stem borer is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Esenbeckia runyonii is a species of flowering tree in the citrus family , Rutaceae , that is native to northeastern Mexico , with a small , disjunct population in the Lower Rio Grande Valley of Texas in the United States .
Acanthocinus princeps , known commonly as the ponderosa pine bark borer , is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae .
The avian genus Quiscalus contains six of the ten species of grackle , gregarious passerine birds in the icterid family .
Casuarina obesa , commonly known as Swamp She - oak or Swamp Oak , is a species of Casuarina that is closely related to C. glauca and C. cristata .
Myriophyllum indicum is a species of water milfoil .
Anastrepha fenestrata is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Anastrepha .
Ataxocerithium huttoni is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Cerithiidae .
Porocephalichthys dasyrhynchus , the Shaggy cusk , is a species of viviparous brotula found in reefs around Rottnest Island , Australia .
Aulodesmus mossambicus is a species of millipedes belonging to the family Gomphodesmidae .
Vancouveria chrysantha is a species of flowering plant in the barberry family known by the common names golden inside - out flower and Siskiyou inside - out flower .
Cainia is a genus of fungi in the family Cainiaceae .
Sclerocactus polyancistrus is a species of cactus known by several common names , including redspined fishhook cactus , Mojave fishhook cactus , pineapple cactus , and hermit cactus .
Boulengerella is a genus of pike - characins from tropical South America , found in the Amazon Basin , Orinoco , and rivers of the Guiana Shield .
Synodontis punu is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Republic of the Congo and Gabon , where it is known from the Nyanga , Kouilou - Niari and Ngounié river basins .
Piperia elongata is a species of orchid known by the common names denseflower rein orchid , chaparral orchid and wood rein - orchid .
Chiromantes eulimene is a species of crab found in the mangrove swamps of south - eastern Africa ( South Africa and Mozambique ) .
Kangaroo rats , small rodents of genus Dipodomys , are native to western North America .
Isichthys henryi is a species of freshwater elephantfish in the family Mormyridae and the only member of its genus .
The Mexican bean beetle , Epilachna varivestis , is a species of lady beetle which is a notorious agricultural pest .
Xylodromus depressus is a brown coloured species of beetle in the rove beetle family , that can be found in Albania , Austria , Belgium , Bulgaria , the Czech Republic , France , Germany , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Poland , Portugal , Romania , Russia , Slovakia , Switzerland , the Netherlands , and Ukraine .
The Puerto Rican sharp - shinned hawk , ( Accipiter striatus venator ) , falcón de sierra or gavilán pecho rufo in Spanish , is an endemic subspecies of the North American sharp - shinned hawk , occurring only in Puerto Rico .
Nebria sajana is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Altai and Western Sayans .
Cochranella is a genus of glass frogs , characterized by lacking humeral spines in males , and having a lobed liver .
Prostanthera phylicifolia , commonly known as Spiked Mint - bush , is a species of plant in the Lamiaceae family .
Paraclinus rubicundus is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Atlantic coast of Brazil where it inhabits algae - covered reefs at depths of from near the surface to 25 metres ( 82 ft ) .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Chlamydosauromyces punctatus .
Ilex aquifolium ( holly , common holly , English holly , European holly , or occasionally Christmas holly ) , is a species of holly native to western and southern Europe , northwest Africa , and southwest Asia .
Vriesea funebris is a species in the genus Vriesea .
Pseudostenidea rufescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudostenidea .
Lenzites warnieri is a species of fungus in the family Polyporaceae found in parts of Europe , Asia , and northern Africa .
Hylarana garoensis ( commonly known as Boulenger 's Garo hill frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Gomphos is an extinct genus of early lagomorph from the early Eocene some 55 million years ago of China and Mongolia .
It was formerly classified as a subspecies of the Himalayan cuckoo ( C. saturatus ) with the name Oriental cuckoo used for the combined species .
Cephalaria alpina , commonly known as the yellow cephalaria , alpine scabiouse or yellow scabiose , is a species of flowering plant in the family Caprifoliaceae native to the Alps in Europe .
Rehmannia is a genus of six species of flowering plants in the order Lamiales , endemic to China .
Haworthia zantneriana is a species of the genus Haworthia in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , endemic to the southern parts of the Western Cape and Eastern Cape Provinces in South Africa .
It contains only one species , Procacitas orientella , which is found in Japan ( Hokkaido , Honshu , Shikoku ) , Russia ( Sakhalin , Irkutsk , Primorye ) and North Korea .
Streptanthus cordatus is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name heartleaf twistflower .
Sphaerium beckmani is an extinct species of fossil freshwater pea clams from the Late Cretaceous deposits of North America .
Thalassiosirales is an order of centric diatoms .
Ophiopogon planiscapus is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae .
Lipotriches pulchriventris is a species of bees in the genus Lipotriches , of the family Halictidae .
Khaya senegalensis is a species of tree in the Meliaceae family that is native to Africa .
The superfamily Papilionoidea ( from the genus Papilio , meaning `` butterfly '' ) contains all the butterflies except for the skippers , which are classified in superfamily Hesperioidea , and the moth - like Hedyloidea .
Melanopais gemmaria is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Melanopais .
Mindarus harringtoni is an extinct species of aphid .
Bhesa paniculata is a species of plant in the Centroplacaceae family .
Dipodium brevilabium is an orchid species that is endemic to Western Papua in Indonesia .
Claea niulanjiangensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Claea .
Philidris jiugongshanensis is a species of ant in the genus Philidris .
Cyperus fuscus is a species of sedge known by the common name brown galingale , or brown flatsedge .
Mikaniopsis is a genus of African flowering plant in the groundsel tribe within the sunflower family .
Astragalus tyghensis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Tygh Valley milkvetch .
Morrinhosuchus is an extinct genus of notosuchian crocodyliform from the Late Cretaceous Adamantina Formation of Brazil .
Members of the genus Lophius , also sometimes called monkfish , fishing - frogs , frog - fish and sea - devils , are well known off the coasts of Europe .
Gracianella is a genus of fossil brachiopods .
The Cyatheaceae are the scaly tree fern family and include the world 's tallest tree ferns , which reach heights up to 20 m. They are also very ancient plants , appearing in the fossil record in the late Jurassic , though the modern genera likely appeared in the Cenozoic .
Anisopodus nigripes is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Bates in 1885 .
It contains only one known species , Dracomonticola virginea , native to Lesotho and South Africa .
Sorbaria is a genus of around 9 species of flowering plants belong to family Rosaceae .
Kartidris is an Indomalayan genus of terrestrial ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Ptychatractus ligatus , common name the ligate false spindle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ptychatractidae .
Aichryson is a genus of about 15 species of succulent , subtropical plants , mostly native to the Canary Islands , with a few in the Azores , Madeira and Morocco , and one in Portugal .
Aclididae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks , in the superfamily Eulimoidea .
Caladenia pectinata , commonly known as the King spider orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Thoosuchus is an extinct genus of basal trematosauroid trematosaurian temnospondyl .
Quercus franchetii , commonly known as the zhui lian li evergreen oak , is a species of oak in the section Quercus sect .
Agyneta pogonophora is a species of sheet weaver found in Angola and Seychelles .
Alchemilla stricta is a species of lady 's mantle that is endemic to Turkey .
Cyriocosmus elegans is a spider species in the genus Cyriocosmus and the family Theraphosidae ( tarantulas ) found in Venezuela , Trinidad and Tobago .
Broughtonia is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) native to the Bahamas and the Greater Antilles .
Lepidoblepharis buchwaldii is a species of gecko endemic to Ecuador .
Oxymeris strigata , common name : the Zebra Auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Acinacodus is an extinct genus of amphidontid `` eutriconodont '' which existed in Shestakovo 1 locality in Western Siberia , Russia during the early Cretaceous period .
Aegialitis is a genus of two shrubby mangrove species , with one native to Southeast Asia and the other native to Australia and Papua New Guinea .
Schmidtea lugubris is a species of freshwater flatworm , a dugesiid triclad that inhabits the freshwater of Europe .
Sicyases is a genus of clingfishes native to the coasts of the southeastern Pacific Ocean .
Celsinotum candango is a species of crustacean .
Myriotrochidae is a family of sea cucumbers .
Branchinecta gigas is a species of fairy shrimp that lives in western Canada and the United States .
Chinlechelys ( /tʃɪnltʃɛliːs/ meaning Chinle turtle ) is an extinct genus of primitive turtle .
Cirsium helenioides , called melancholy thistle , is an Asian and Arctic species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Lythrum is a genus of 38 species of flowering plants native to the temperate world .
Balsamorhiza sericea is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower tribe of the plant family Asteraceae known by the common name silky balsamroot .
Ilex vomitoria , commonly known as yaupon or yaupon holly , is a species of holly that is native to southeastern North America .
Thiobacillus is a genus of Gram - negative Betaproteobacteria .

Aplocheilichthys sp . nov . ' Baringo ' is a species of fish in the Poeciliidae family .

Gilia capitata is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names blue - thimble - flower , bluehead gilia , blue field gilia , and globe gilia .
Solenopsis saevissima , commonly known in Brazil as formiga ruiva ( red ant ) , is one of more than 185 species in the genus Solenopsis .
Carabus nanschanicus is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Qinghai and Sichuan provinces of China .
The Seram imperial pigeon ( Ducula neglecta ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Adelobasileus cromptoni is a species of an extinct genus of mammal - like synapsid from the Late Triassic ( Carnian ) , about 225 million years ago .
Astragalus gambelianus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Gambel 's dwarf milkvetch .
Euphorbia leucocephala , with many common names including little Christmas flower , white lace euphorbia , snow bush , snow flake , snows of Kilimanjaro and white Christmas bush is a species of plant in the Euphorbiaceae family .
Sinularia is a genus of soft coral .
Sarcomelicope is a genus of plant in family Rutaceae .
The Galápagos dove ( Zenaida galapagoensis ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Grevillea kennedyana is a sprawling shrub of the Grevillea species .
Ancherythroculter is a genus of cyprinid fishes that occur in eastern Asia in China and Vietnam .
Tabanus lineola , also known as the striped horse fly , is a species of biting horse - fly .
Palmadusta humphreyii , common name : the Humphrey 's Cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
The Andean hillstar ( Oreotrochilus estella ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Miniopterus gleni is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae and it belongs to the class Mammalia .
Thoressa is a genus of skipper butterflies .
Motyxia is a genus of cyanide - producing millipedes ( collectively known as Sierra luminous millipedes or motyxias ) that are endemic to the southern Sierra Nevada , Tehachapi , and Santa Monica mountain ranges of California .
Diestrammena bifurcata is a species of cricket in the Rhaphidophoridae family .
Pseudocalotes microlepis , also known as Burmese false bloodsucker or small - scaled forest agamid , is a species of agamid lizard in the genus Pseudocalotes found in southern China ( Hainan , Guizhou ) , Thailand , Laos , Myanmar and Vietnam .
Tityus fasciolatus is a species of scorpion from the family Buthidae .
Bulbophyllum beccarii is by far the largest species in the genus Bulbophyllum and one of the largest in the orchid family .
Garcinia intermedia is a species of tropical American tree which produces tasty fruit .
Magninia tonkinea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Magninia .
Xianglong ( meaning `` flying dragon '' in Chinese ) is a genus of Cretaceous lizard discovered in the Zhuanchengzi , near Yizhou , Yixian , Liaoning Province of China .
Owenodon is a genus of iguanodontian dinosaur known from a partial lower jaw discovered in Early Cretaceous - age rocks of Durlston Bay , Dorset , United Kingdom .
Raphidiophryidae is a family of mostly freshwater centrohelids .
Plagioeciidae is a family of bryozoans , containing many genera once assigned to Diastoporidae .
Cranopsis cucullata , common name the hooded keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Phelsuma sundbergi ladiguensis is a diurnal subspecies of Phelsuma sundbergi .
Pedicularis sceptrum - carolinum is a plant species in the genus Pedicularis .
Hybolasiopsis abnormalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hybolasiopsis .
Doumea angolensis is a species of loach catfish endemic to Angola where it is found in the Benguela interior and the Quanza River system .
Neoclytus acuminatus , the red - headed ash borer , is a common North American species in the longhorn beetle family ( Cerambycidae ) .
Petrobrasaurus is a genus of herbivorous sauropod dinosaur .
Salmo chilo is a salmonid fish , a relative of trout first described as a distinct species in 2012 from the Akdere Stream , a tributary of the Ceyhan River in Turkey .
Burkholderia phymatum is a species of proteobacteria that is capable of symbiotic nitrogen fixation with the legume Machaerium lunatum and Mimosa pudica .
Hypleurochilus bananensis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern central Atlantic ocean .
Terebrirostra is an extinct genus of brachiopod from the Cretaceous of Europe .
Conus exiguus , common name Cabrit 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Entoliidae , also referred to as the entoliids , are a taxonomic family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the order Pectinoida .
Torreyochloa pallida is a species of grass known by the common names pale false mannagrass and weak manna grass .
Deferribacter desulfuricans is a species of sulfur- , nitrate- and arsenate - reducing thermophile first isolated from a deep - sea hydrothermal vent .
The large flowering plant genus Grewia /ˈɡruːiə/ is today placed by most authors in the mallow family Malvaceae , in the expanded sense as proposed by in the APG .
Tilletia is a genus of smut fungi in the Tilletiaceae family .
Fissidentales is a formerly recognized order of mosses .
Hesperostipa is a genus of grasses in the family Poaceae .
Galium glabrescens is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name Castle Lake bedstraw .
Palaeontinoidea is an extinct superfamily of cicadomorph hemipteran insects .
Elsinoaceae is a family of sac fungi , widely distributed in the tropics .
Streptomyces griseoluteus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Tokyo in Japan .
Silonia childreni is a species of schilbid catfish endemic to India where it occurs in the Krishna , Godavari and Cauvery River systems of the Western Ghats .
Drosera rosulata is a perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to southwest Western Australia .
Koeleria pyramidata is a Eurasian plant species in the grass family .
Archachatina marginata , common name the Giant West African Snail or Banana rasp snail , is a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinidae .
Calicalicus is a genus of bird in the Vangidae family .
Farlowella hasemani is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in Pará .
Portenko 's shrew ( Sorex portenkoi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae that is endemic to Russia .
Drosera sulphurea , the sulphur - flowered sundew , is a scrambling perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Melanophylla is a genus of flowering plants endemic to Madagascar .
Phyciodes phaon ( the Phaon crescent or mat plant crescent ) is a species of butterfly endemic to northern Florida .
Microhyla maculifera ( common name : Sabah rice frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Indrella ampulla is a species of tropical terrestrial air - breathing gastropod mollusk in the family Ariophantidae .

Coptosoma scutellatum is a species of true bugs belonging to the family Plataspidae , subfamily Plataspinae .
Sepiola pfefferi is a species of bobtail squid native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean .
The Angolan talapoin ( Miopithecus talapoin ) , also known as the southern talapoin , is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae .
Atractaspis duerdeni , commonly known as the beaked burrowing asp or Duerden 's burrowing asp , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Allothereua maculata is a species of centipede found in Australia known as the house centipede -- a name applied elsewhere to other species .
Argiope trifasciata ( banded garden spider ) is a species of spider found around the world .
Mucurilebias leitaoi is a species of rivuline fish endemic to Brazil where it occurs , or formerly occurred , in the basin of the Mucuri River .
Callinectes is a genus of crabs , containing 16 species , including the Atlantic blue crab , C. sapidus :
Quercus peduncularis is a Mesoamerican species of plant in the beech family .
The Aquifoliales are an order of flowering plants , including the Aquifoliaceae ( or holly ) family , and also the Helwingiaceae ( 2 - 5 species of temperate Asian shrubs ) and the Phyllonomaceae ( 4 species of Central American trees and shrubs ) .
Layia fremontii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Frémont 's tidytips .
Sagamichthys is a genus of tubeshoulders .
Dioon mejiae is a species of cycad that is native to Honduras and Nicaragua .
Haplochromis velifer is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Nabugabo , Uganda .
Toxopneustes is a genus of sea urchins from the tropical Indo - Pacific .
Aussiedraco is a genus of basal ornithocheiroid pterodactyloid pterosaur from the early Cretaceous of Australia .
Sindoscopus australis is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of Chile where it can be found in shallow waters with a sandy substrate .
Megachirella is an extinct genus of lepidosauromorph reptile from the Middle Triassic and contains one species , Megachirella wachtleri , from the Dolomites of northern Italy .
Parachartergus fraternus is a neotropical , swarm founding , polistine wasp species that is distributed throughout Central and South America .
Tibouchina heteromalla , known by the common name silverleafed princess flower in English is a species of evergreen flowering plant in the genus Tibouchina of the family Melastomataceae .
Alasmidonta viridis , common name the Slippershell mussel , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Goodfellow 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys goodfellowi ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Pseudosedum is a genus in the family Crassulaceae .
Frostius pernambucensis , or the Frost 's toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Malarguesaurus is a genus of titanosauriform sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Mendoza Province , Argentina .
Thaumatococcus daniellii is a plant species from Africa , known for being the natural source of thaumatin , an intensely sweet protein which is of interest in the development of sweeteners .
Ranunculus eschscholtzii is a species of buttercup known by the common name Eschscholtz 's buttercup .
Kirk 's dik - dik ( Madoqua kirkii ) is a small antelope native to Eastern Africa and one of four species of dik - dik antelope .
Sagina nodosa ( Knotted Pearlwort ) is a species in the genus Sagina , native to northern Europe .
Macrotrema caligans is a species of swamp eel native to Malaysia and Thailand .
Sicyopterus stimpsoni , commonly known as the Nopoli rockclimbing goby , oopu nopili , or Stimpson 's goby , is a species of amphidromous goby endemic to Hawaii .
Calycadenia spicata is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name spiked western rosinweed .
First described as Banksia nivea , it was transferred to Dryandra as Dryandra nivea by Robert Brown in 1810 , and remained in that genus until 2007 , when all Dryandra species were transferred to Banksia by Austin Mast and Kevin Thiele .
Mopalia spectabilis , commonly known as the Red - flecked Mopalia , is a species of chiton .
Hyloscirtus albopunctulatus is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
Carex vulpinoidea is a species of sedge known by the common name fox sedge or American fox - sedge .
Pleuropogon refractus is a species of grass known by the common name nodding semaphoregrass .
Kenichthys is a genus of sarcopterygian fish from the Devonian period , and a member of the clade tetrapodomorpha .
Delias ganymedes is a species of pierine butterfly endemic to the Philippines .
Hypleurochilus geminatus , the Crested blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean .
Elophila feili is a species of moth in the Crambidae family which can be found in Spain and Portugal .
Anomoeodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish from the Late Cretaceous .
Sinutropis is a genus of fossil sea snails , extinct euomphalid archaeogastropods from the Upper Silurian .
Amentotaxus yunnanensis ( Yunnan Catkin Yew ) is a species of conifer in the yew family , Taxaceae .
Triplophysa daqiaoensis is a species of stone loach in the genus Triplophysa .
Friedrich von Huene reassessed it in 1932 as belonging to a new genus , that he named Plateosauravus .
Clavelina coerulea is a species of tunicates belonging to the family Clavelinidae .
Rossia bullisi , also known as the Gulf bobtail squid , is a species of bobtail squid native to the tropical western Atlantic Ocean , specifically the northern Gulf of Mexico and Straits of Florida .
Drosophila melanogaster is a species of fly ( the taxonomic order Diptera ) in the family Drosophilidae .
Miltonia clowesii , the Clowes ' Miltonia , is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Brazil .
Pelophryne ( Flathead Toads ) is a genus of true toads endemic to Philippines , Borneo , Malaya , Singapore and Hainan Island , China .
Perimecoceras is similar in general form to the oncoceratid genus Oonoceras from which it may have been derived , but differs in having a longer body chamber in proportion and in having concave segments to its siphuncle .
Mirabilis macfarlanei is a rare species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common name MacFarlane 's four o'clock .
It contains only one species Stanempista schawerdae , which is found in Spain .
Puntius cauveriensis , the Cauvery barb , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Cauvery River in Karnataka , India .
Nicotiana × sanderae is a hybrid of the tobacco species Nicotiana alata and Nicotiana forgetiana .
Penicillium lapatayae is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from Tierra del Fuego in Chile .
Dawndraco is a genus of pteranodontid pterosaur from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Aleurodicus dispersus , the spiralling whitefly , is a species of small , white sap - sucking insect , a true bug in the order Hemiptera .
Apteribis is an extinct genus of flightless birds in the ibis subfamily that was endemic to the Hawaiian Islands in the Pacific Ocean .
Tarigidia is a genus of South African and Puerto Rican plants in the grass family .
Densovirinae is a subfamily of single - stranded DNA viruses in the family Parvoviridae .
Amathia vidovici is a species of colonial bryozoan with a tree - like structure .
Magnistipula conrauana is a species of plant in the Chrysobalanaceae family .
The Maikhanellidae are a family of Early Cambrian monoplacophora with a limpet - like morphology .
The Griffis angelfish , Apolemichthys griffisi , is a species of marine angelfish from the Pacific Ocean .
Plectrypops is a genus of soldierfish containing two extant species , with one species in the Indo - Pacific , and another in the western Atlantic and the Caribbean .
Mutinus elegans , commonly known as the elegant stinkhorn , the dog stinkhorn , the headless stinkhorn , or the devil 's dipstick , is a species of fungus in the Phallaceae family .
Calathea ornata ( also called variously Striped , Pin - stripe , or Pin - stripe calathea ) is a species of perennial plant in the family known as the prayer plants .
Germainia is a genus of Chinese , Asian and Australian plants in the grass family .
Zamites is a genus of fossil tree known from the Mesozoic of North America , Europe and India through the Oligocene of North America .
Caladenia barbarossa , commonly known as the common dragon orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Rhaebo hypomelas ( common name : Choco toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Eurolimnornis is the name given to a monotypic genus of pterosaurs from the Early Cretaceous .
Navarretia heterandra is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Tehama pincushionplant , or Tehama navarretia .
Lasthenia minor is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name coastal goldfields .
Acanthosybra lineolata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acanthosybra .
Tuditanomorpha is a suborder of microsaur lepospondyls .
Phaius australis , also known as the lesser swamp orchid and southern swamp orchid , is a species of orchid found in Australia .
Quercus microphylla is a Mexican species of oak in the beech family .
Leucogenes is a genus of plants in the sunflower family , native to New Zealand .
Anathallis is a genus of orchids , comprising about 97 species native to Mexico , Central America , South America and the West Indies .
Dendropsophus ebraccatus , commonly known as the hourglass treefrog or pantless treefrog , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Parinari costata is a species of plant in the Chrysobalanaceae family that can be found in Indonesia , Malaysia , the Philippines , and Singapore .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Ascocephalophora petasiformis .
Trichodina is a genus of ciliate protists that is ectocommensal or parasitic on aquatic animals , particularly fish .
Mesoleuctra is a genus of stoneflies that lived in the Jurassic period .
Pancratium canariense or the Canary Sea Daffodil is a species of bulbous plant endemic to the Canary Islands .
Montano virus ( MTNV ) is a single - stranded , enveloped , negative sense RNA hantavirus species of the Bunyaviridae family .
Oxalis latifolia is a species of flowering plant in the woodsorrel family known by the common names garden pink - sorrel and broadleaf woodsorrel .
The Ammonitida is an order of more highly evolved ammonoid cephalopods from the Jurassic and Cretaceous time periods , commonly with intricate ammonitic sutures .
