Nothaphoebe pahangensis is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae .
Myriacantherpestes is an extinct genus of spiny millipedes from the Pennsylvanian subperiod of the Carboniferous period , known from fossils in Europe and North America .
Craugastor chrysozetetes is an extinct species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Fritillaria orientalis is a Eurasian species of monocotyledon plant of the lily family .
Gephyroglanis gymnorhynchus is a species of claroteid catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Aruwimi River .
Shorea bentongensis ( also called White Meranti ) is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae .
Diandrya composita is a species of cestode parasite that is known from marmots ( Marmota spp . )
Marleyella is a genus of righteye flounders native to the western Indian Ocean where found at depths ranging from the shallows to more than 400 m ( 1,300 ft ) .
Hamites ( `` hook - like '' ) is a genus of heteromorph ammonite that evolved late in the Aptian stage of the Early Cretaceous and lasted into the Cenomanian stage of the Late Cretaceous .
Gerrhosaurus is a genus of lizards native to southern and eastern Africa .
Lyelliceratidae is a family of ammonites belonging to the family Gaudryceratidae .
Carelia turricula are an extinct species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Agapanthia suturalis is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that can be found in Sicily , Spain , the Near East , North Africa and Turkey .
Apostasia wallichii is a species of orchid that was described in 1830 in a book by Nathaniel Wallich , using a description excerpted from a manuscript by Robert Brown .
Cuerna is a genus of insect in the leafhopper family described in 1924 and accepted in 1925 .
Oenocarpus is a genus of pinnate - leaved palms ( Arecaceae ) native to Trinidad , southern Central and tropical South America .
Xiphopenaeus is a genus of crustaceans in the suborder Dendrobranchiata , the shrimps and prawns .
Garra barreimiae , the Oman garra , is a cave - adapted species of ray - finned fish in the family Cyprinidae .
The Pribilof Island shrew ( Sorex pribilofensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Psilocybe yungensis is a species of psychedelic mushroom in the Strophariaceae family .
Cirripectes stigmaticus , the red - streaked blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny from the Indo - Pacific .
Cryptantha muricata is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name pointed cryptantha .
Arborotites stuckenbergi is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Arborotites of the family Ulidiidae .
Banksieaephyllum is a plant genus that encompasses organically preserved fossil leaves that can be attributed to the Proteaceae tribe Banksieae , but can not be attributed to a genus .
The Pristigasteridae are a family of fish related to the herrings , including the genera Ilisha , Pellona , and Pristigaster .
Odontomachus cornutus is a species of ant in the Ponerinae subfamily .
Avena sterilis ( Animated oat , Sterile oat , Wild oat , Wild red oat , Winter wild oat ; syn . Avena ludoviciana Durieu ; Avena sterilis ssp . ludoviciana ( Durieu ) Gillet & Magne in Federal Noxious Weed Disseminules of the U.S. ) is a species of grass weed , and its seeds are edible .
Misumena nigromaculata is a species of flower crab spider endemic to Madeira .
Liopleurodon ( /ˌlaɪoʊˈplʊərədɒn/ ; meaning ' smooth - sided teeth ' ) is a genus of large , carnivorous marine reptile belonging to the Pliosauroidea , a clade of short - necked plesiosaurs .
Camissonia benitensis is a species of evening primrose known by the common name San Benito evening primrose .
Hesioninae are a subfamily of phyllodocid `` bristle worms '' ( class Polychaeta ) .
Korthalsia is a clustering genus of flowering plant in the palm family spread throughout Southeast Asia .
Conus ermineus , common name the turtle cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Rhodactina himalayensis is a species of secotioid fungus in the family Boletaceae , and the type species of genus Rhodactina .
Seabriella fasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Seabriella .
Bitis arietans somalica ( Somali : Abeeso ) also known as the Somali puff adder , is a venomous viper subspecies found only in Somalia , eastern Ethiopia and northern Kenya .
Brickellia laciniata ( splitleaf brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Dicolectes spinicollis is a species of leaf beetle native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo , observed by Burgeon in 1941 .
The designated holotype for the genus and type species , Mapusaurus roseae , is an isolated right nasal ( MCF - PVPH-108.1 , Museo Carmen Funes , Paleontología de Vertebrados , Plaza Huincul , Neuquén ) .
The Cuban blackbird ( Dives atroviolaceus ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Noltea is a monotypic genus of flowering plants .
Biomphalaria alexandrina is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Mammacyon is an extinct genus of medium - sized amphicyonid caniformian carnivoran mammals endemic to North America during the Oligocene to Miocene living from 30.8 - -20.6 Ma and existed for approximately 10.2 million years .
Clinus is a genus of clinids found in the southeastern Atlantic and western Indian ocean .
Leptodactylus viridis ( common name : Jim 's white - lipped frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Dyspanopeus texanus ( formerly Panopeus texanus or Neopanope texana ) is a species of crab known as the Texas mud crab .
Potamobatrachus trispinosus is a species of toadfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Araguaia and Tocantins Rivers .
Dianthus japonicus is a species of herbaceous perennial plant in the genus Dianthus .
Hamaxiella brunnescens is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Hamaxiella of the family Tachinidae .
Megacephala pseudofulgida is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Mandl in 1963 , and is endemic to Goias , Brazil .
Opisthiolepis is a genus of a sole described species of large trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Hollandaea sayeriana , sometimes named Sayer 's silky oak , is a species of Australian rainforest small trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Dichocrocis clytusalis , the kurrajong bag moth , is a species of moth of the Crambidae family .
Juncus hemiendytus is a species of rush known by the common name Herman 's dwarf rush .
Mimulus bigelovii is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Bigelow 's monkeyflower .
Clinanthus is a genus of bulbous plants in the family Amaryllidaceae , found in western South America , from Ecuador to north west Argentina .
Dictymia brownii , known as the Strap Fern , is a species of fern found in and near rainforest in eastern Australia .
Hysterophora maculosana , the bluebell conch , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Puntius viridis is a species of barb native to the Manimala River in Kerala , India .
Coccoloba uvifera is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family , Polygonaceae , that is native to coastal beaches throughout tropical America and the Caribbean ; including southern Florida , the Bahamas , the Greater and Lesser Antilles and Bermuda .
Calochortus minimus is a California species of flowering plants in the lily family known by the common name Sierra mariposa lily .
Anarsia molybdota is a species of moth of the Gelechiidae family .
Cyanea glabra is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name smooth cyanea .
Eriophyes is a genus of acari .
Sorbus anglica , the English whitebeam , is a species of whitebeam tree in the Rosaceae family .
Hemicalypterus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the late Triassic period ( approx . 221.4 to 205.6 Ma ) .
Physaria thamnophila ( syn . Lesquerella thamnophila ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Zapata bladderpod .
Albizia is a genus of about 150 species of mostly fast - growing subtropical and tropical trees and shrubs in the subfamily Mimosoideae of the family Fabaceae .
Raoellidae , previously grouped within Helohyidae , is an extinct family of semiaquatic digitigrade artiodactyls in the clade Whippomorpha .
Sagisma is a fossil genus of aquatic plants .
Pappophorum is a genus of plants in the grass family , native to the Western Hemisphere .
The green fan - throated lizard ( Ptyctolaemus gularis ) is a species of agamid lizard found in Bangladesh , China ( Tibet ) , India ( Northeast- Arunachal Pradesh , Assam , Khasi Hills , Mizoram ) and Myanmar ( Kachin , Chin ) , and possibly in Bhutan .
Palaeolepidopterix is an extinct genus of small primitive metallic moths within the extant family Micropterigidae or extinct family Eolepidopterigidae , containing one species , Palaeolepidopterix aurea .
Bambusa bambos , the Indian thorny bamboo , is a species of clumping bamboo native to southern Asia ( India , Bangladesh , Sri Lanka , Assam , and Indochina ) .
Sphacelotheca reiliana , also known as Sporisorium reilianum , is a species of biotrophic fungus in the family Microbotryaceae .
Bos planifrons ( flat - fronted cattle ) was a bovine species from the Siwaliks of India and Pakistan .
Schlumbergera truncata , the false Christmas cactus , is a species of plant in the Cactaceae family .
Bauhinia forficata , commonly known as Brazilian orchid tree , Pata de Vaca , is a species of flowering tree in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is native to Argentina , Brazil and Peru .
Aphonopelma eutylenum is a species of spider in the family Theraphosidae , found in United States ( California ) .
Paraspastis circographa is a moth of the Depressariidae family and only species in the Paraspastis genus .
Pervagor spilosoma is a species of filefish from reefs in the Hawaiian Islands .
Gnaphosa opaca is a ground spider species found from Europe to Central Asia .
Plesiocystiscus gutta is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod in the family Marginellidae , sometimes instead placed in the eponymous family Cystiscidae .
Chloromyia formosa is a species of ' Soldier Flies ' belonging to the family Stratiomyidae .
Corynebacterium efficiens is a species of glutamic acid - producing ( from dextrin ) species from soil and vegetables .
Limopsis sulcata , common name the sulcate limopsis , is a species of very small clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Limopsidae .
Reseda minoica is a species of flowering plants of the genus Reseda found in the eastern Mediterranean region .
Raorchestes theuerkaufi is a species of frog of the genus Raorchestes found in the tea estates of Kadalar near Munnar , Idukki district , in the Western Ghats of Kerala in India .
Lissotes latidens , commonly known as the Wielangta stag beetle or broad - toothed stag beetle , is a species of stag beetle which is only found in an area centred in Wielangta Forest in eastern Tasmania .
Polistes humilis is a species of the Vespidae family that can be found throughout Australia and New Zealand .
Athrodon is a genus of extinct pycnodontid that lived in shallow seas in what is now England and France from the Late Jurassic until the genus ' extinction during the start of the late Cretaceous .
Mahonia repens commonly known as creeping mahonia , creeping Oregon grape , creeping barberry , or prostrate barberry , is a species of Mahonia native to the Rocky Mountains and westward areas of North America , from British Columbia and Alberta in the north through Arizona and New Mexico into northwest Mexico in the south .
Ginkgo dissecta is an extinct ginkgo species in the family Ginkgoaceae described from a series of isolated fossil leaves .
Mysticoncha harrisonae is a species of small sea snail that resembles a sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Velutinidae .
Fallotaspis is a genus of redlichiid trilobite genus found in Early Cambrian - aged strata of the United States and Morocco .
The Florida box turtle ( Terrapene carolina bauri ) is a subspecies of turtle belonging to the family Emydidae .
Priotrochus kotschyi , common name the Kotschy 's gibbula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Festuca armoricana , the Breton fescue , is a species of grass endemic to Europe .
Lioptilodes altivolans is a species of moth in the genus Lioptilodes , known from Peru .
Prosictodon is an extinct genus of pylaecephalid dicynodont from Middle Permian of South Africa .
Borojevia aspina is a species of sponge in the genus Borojevia from Brazil .
Pannoniasaurus is an extinct genus of tethysaurine mosasauroid known from the Late Cretaceous Csehbánya Formation ( Santonian stage ) of Hungary .
Hypanartia , commonly called mapwings , is a genus in the Nymphalidae family found from Mexico to South America .
Raillietina is a genus of tapeworms that includes helminth parasites of vertebrates , mostly of birds .
Halicampus is a genus of pipefishes of the family Syngnathidae , containing 12 described species .
Ficus neriifolia is a species of fig ( Ficus ) .
Sonorella grahamensis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
Paphiopedilum bellatulum , commonly known as the Egg - in - a - nest Orchid , is a species of orchid found from southeastern Yunnan , Guizhou and southern Guangxi of China to Indochina .
Euphlyctis is a genus of frogs in family Dicroglossidae found in southwestern , southern , and southeastern Asia .
Root - knot nematodes are plant - parasitic nematodes from the genus Meloidogyne .
Galerida is a genus of birds in the family Alaudidae .
Anabarilius grahami is a species of cyprinid fish .
Ranunculus hydrocharoides is a species of buttercup known by the common names frogbit buttercup , or frog's - bit buttercup .
Ignavusaurus is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur that lived during the Early Jurassic in what is now present - day Lesotho .
Ananteris balzani is a scorpion species found in Argentina , Paraguay and Brazil .
Aspasma minima is a species of clingfish found in the Pacific Ocean near the shores of southern Japan .
Philodendron erubescens is a species of flowering plant in the family Araceae , native to Colombia .
Harrisia scutellaris is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Harrisia of the family Tachinidae .
Sisyrinchium elmeri is a species of flowering plant in the iris family known by the common name Elmer 's blue - eyed grass .
Synodontis rufigiensis is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania where it is found in the Rufiji River basin .
Mahonia annamica is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1908 .
Herichthys deppii , also known as the Nautla cichlid , is a species of cichlid native to the Nautla and Misantla rivers of Mexico .
Atrosalarias is a genus of combtooth blennies found in the western Pacific Ocean and western Indian Ocean .
Conozoa hyalina was a species of insect in family Acrididae .
Conus tulipacommon name the tulip cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Thelaziidae is a family of spirurian nematodes , which form the mid - sized lineage of the superfamily Thelazioidea .
Onohippidium ( onos ' donkey ' + hippidium ' small horse ' ) is an extinct genus of horse that lived in the Americas during the Pleistocene .
Arctomecon californica is a species of poppy known by several common names , including California bearpoppy , Las Vegas bearpoppy , golden bearpoppy , and yellow - flowered desert poppy .
Trochulus striolatus , previously known as Trichia striolata , common name the `` strawberry snail , '' is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Cheirodon galusdae is a species of fish in the Characidae family endemic to Chile .
Ougapia spaldingi is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Rhytididae .
Phalacroma is a genus of trilobite in the order Agnostida , which existed in what is now the Czech Republic .
Dendya clathrata is a species of the genus Dendya .
Oligoryzomys fulvescens , also known as the fulvous colilargo , fulvous pygmy rice rat , or northern pygmy rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oligoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Mitra nubila , common name the particolored mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Dusa is an extinct genus of prawn , in the order Decapoda , containing five species .
Raorchestes akroparallagi ( sometimes known as the variable bush frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Sectoria is a small genus of stone loaches native to eastern Asia .
The genus Zingiber is native to Southeast Asia , China , the Indian Subcontinent , and New Guinea .
The Arctic redpoll ( Acanthis hornemanni ) , known in North America as the hoary redpoll , is a bird species in the finch family Fringillidae .

Rhipaeosaurus is an extinct genus of nycteroleterid parareptile known from the mid Middle Permian of European Russia .

Lepidium oxycarpum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names forked pepperweed and sharp - fruited pepperweed .
Tropidonophis doriae , commonly known as the barred keelback , is a species of snake belonging to the family Colubridae .
Squamanita paradoxa , commonly known as powdercap strangler , is a species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family .
Atheris mabuensis , or the Mount Mabu forest viper , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Cnemidophorus arubensis is a species of whiptail lizard in the genus Cnemidophorus .
Metapone greeni is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which can be found from Sri Lanka .
Lottia gigantea , common name the owl limpet , giant owl limpet or solitary giant owl limpet , is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Lottiidae .
Chelmonops truncatus , the truncate coralfish or eastern talma , is a species of butterflyfish in the genus Chelmonops endemic to Australia .
Sporobolus virginicus , known by numerous common names including seashore dropseed , marine couch , sand couch , salt couch grass , saltwater couch , coastal rat - tail grass , and nioaka , is a species of grass with a wide distribution .
Eleginops maclovinus , the Patagonian blenny , Falkland 's mullet or rock cod , is a species of notothenioid fish found in coastal and estuarine habitats around southernmost South America , ranging as far north as Valparaíso on the Pacific side , and Uruguay on the Atlantic side .
Pyramidella adamsi , common name the Adams ' pyram , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Himalayan toad , Duttaphrynus himalayanus , is a species of toad that is widely distributed throughout the Himalayan mountains .
Erigeron austiniae is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name sagebrush fleabane .
Acropora aspera is a species of staghorn coral in the family Acroporidae .
The Trigonoceratidae is a family of coiled nautiloid cephalopods that lived during the period from the Early Carboniferous ( Mississippian ) to the Early Permian .
At present it contains the single species Quatsinoporites cranhamii .
Luciellidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
In Mississippi , stands of Sarracenia alata rival in size those of any other Sarracenia species .

Tonestus lyallii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Lyall 's goldenweed , Lyall 's serpentweed and Lyall 's tonestus .
Hoehnea is a genus of plants in the family Lamiaceae , first described with this name in 1939 .
Omobranchus ferox , the gossamer blenny or the fang - toothed blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found brackish waters in Africa and Asia .
Laccospadix is a monotypic genus of flowering plant in the palm endemic to Queensland .
Eodiscina is a suborder of trilobites , a well known group of marine arthropods .
Penstemon tenuiflorus , commonly known as eastern whiteflower beardtongue , is a species of flowering plant in the veronica family .
Euhomalocera is a genus of moth in the family Schreckensteiniidae .
The Redwing genus Pterolobium ( from Gr . Pteron , wing and lobos , pod or capsule , alluding to the winged fruit ) consists of some 11 species of perennial flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Junodia vansomereni is a species of praying mantis found Uganda .
Astragalus leucolobus is a species of milkvetch known by the common names Bear Valley milkvetch and Bear Valley woollypod .

Alisma orientale is a flowering plant species in the genus Alisma found in Asia .

Cnemaspis pava is a species of diurnal gecko endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Heterosteidae is an extinct family of moderately large to giant , flattened , benthic arthrodire placoderms with distinctive , flattened , triangular skulls that are extremely broad posteriorly , but become very narrow anteriorly .
Tornidae is a family of very small and minute sea snails with an operculum , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Orchis simia , commonly known as the monkey orchid , is a greyish pink to reddish species of the Orchis genus .
Paracercion is a small genus of damselflies in the family Coenagrionidae . They are commonly known as Lilysquatters .
Masdevallia angulifera is a species of orchid endemic to the Western Cordillera and the Central Cordillera of Colombia in northern South America .
Trichiotinus piger , the hairy flower chafer or bee - like flower scarab , is a species of beetle .

Trichospira is a genus of flowering plants in the evil tribe within the daisy family .

The Conopidae , usually known as the thick - headed flies , are a family of flies within the Brachycera suborder of Diptera .
Hauffiopteryx is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur known from Germany , Luxembourg and Somerset of the United Kingdom .
Scolopendra viridicornis is a species of centipede in the family Scolopendridae that can be found on Indo - Burma border where its venom is used for medicine .
Neritina zebra , commonly known as the zebra nerite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
Miltonia spectabilis , the Outstanding Miltonia , is a species of orchid occurring in extreme eastern Brazil and has been erroneously reported to occur in Venezuela .
The northern sea nettle ( Chrysaora melanaster ) , also called a brown jellyfish , is a species of jellyfish native to the northern Pacific Ocean and adjacent parts of the Arctic Ocean .
Amphorateuthis alveatus is a species of bobtail squid native to the Indian Ocean .
Clausena smyrelliana , commonly known as Smyrell 's clausena or Gregs wampi , is a species of evergreen shrub to 6 m tall , in the family Rutaceae , native to eastern Australia .

Hakea lorea , commonly known as bootlace oak or cork tree , is a species of shrub or small tree in the family Proteaceae found in central and northern Australia .

Archeosolenocera straeleni is an extinct species of prawn , the only species in the genus Archeosolenocera .

Echinometra mathaei , the burrowing urchin , is a species of sea urchin in the family Echinometridae .
Vincent 's bush squirrel ( Paraxerus vincenti ) is a species of rodents in the family Sciuridae , named in honour of Jack Vincent .
Acer ashwilli is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a group of fossil leaves and samaras .
Epocilla aurantiaca is a species of jumping spider found from India to Malaysia .
Smilosicyopus is a genus of gobies native to Asia and Oceania .
Taeniolabis ( `` Ribbon Lips '' ) is a genus of extinct multituberculate mammal from the Paleocene of North America .
Sesleria insularis is a species of perennial grass in the Poaceae family , with culms 30 - -65 cm long .
Emiliania huxleyi , often abbreviated `` EHUX '' , is a species of coccolithophore with a global distribution from the tropics to subarctic waters .
Spiriferida is an order of extinct articulate brachiopod fossils which are known for their long hinge - line , which is often the widest part of the shell .
Borhyaena is an extinct genus of South American metatherian , living between 20 and 15 million years ago .
Paradinandra suecica is a species of fossil plant from the Cretaceous of Sweden .
Phanerostylis is a genus of Mexican plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Hyperolius bolifambae ( commonly known as Bolifamba reed frog ' ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .

Marsdenia elliptica ( jungle netvine ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Apocynaceae .
Tomzanonia is a genus of orchids , ( family Orchidaceae ) , consisting of a single species , Tomzanonia filicina endemic to the Massif de la Hotte in Haiti .
Magnoliopsida is a valid botanical name for a class of flowering plants .
Microhyla fusca ( common names : brown rice frog or Dalat pigmy frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Achiroides is a genus of small freshwater soles native to Southeast Asia .
Ballota ( horehound ) is a genus of flowering evergreen perennial plants and subshrubs in the family Lamiaceae .
California roaches seem to be a resilient species that takes advantage of the intermittent waters of central California under conditions too difficult for other fishes .
Perrierbambus is a genus of Madagascan bamboo in the grass family .
Anchorius lineatus is a species of beetle in the family Biphyllidae , the only species in the genus Anchorius .
Zupaysaurus ( /ˌzuːpeɪˈsɔrəs/ ; `` ZOO - pay - SAWR - us '' ) is a genus of early theropod dinosaur living during the Rhaetian stage of the Late Triassic to Hettangian stage of the Early Jurassic of what is now Argentina .
Leptospira ( Greek leptos , `` fine , thin '' and Latin spira , `` coil '' ) is a genus of spirochaete bacteria , including a small number of pathogenic and saprophytic species .
Inula britannica , the British yellowhead or meadow fleabane , is a Eurasian species of plants in the genus Inula within the daisy family .
Gastrocopta is a genus of minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Vertiginidae , the vertigo snails .
Rafflesia bengkuluensis is a relatively new parasitic plant species of the genus Rafflesia .
Cautethia simitia is a species of moth in the family Sphingidae .
Pellia is a small but widespread genus of liverworts in the cool and temperate regions of the northern hemisphere .
Curetis siva , the Shiva 's sunbeam , is a species of lycaenid or blue butterfly found in Asia .

Sorbus decipiens , the sharp - toothed whitebeam , is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Jumellea is an orchid genus with around 40 species native to Madagascar , the Comoros , the Mascarenes , and eastern Africa .

Rhynchalastor is a moderately large afrotropical genus of potter wasps with 25 species currently known .

Paratropis tuxtlensis is a species of spider in the family Paratropididae ( baldlegged spiders ) .
Dicranopalpus is a genus of harvestmen with twelve known recent species .

Chlorissa viridata , the small grass emerald , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Leibnitzia lyrata , common name Seemann 's sunbonnet , is a plant species widespread across much of Mexico and also found in the US states of Arizona and New Mexico .
Cantharellus guyanensis is a tropical South American species of mushroom - forming fungus in the chanterelle genus ( Cantharellus ) , first described by Camille Montagne from French Guiana in 1854 .
Chione is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Rubiaceae containing the single species Chione venosa .

Juncus nevadensis is a species of rush known by the common name Sierra rush .
